title: "too good" fruit dip
directions: Whip cream cheese with mixer until smooth.
Blend in orange juice.
Add Marshmallow Creme.
Whip again until smooth.
Chill before serving.

title: 8 biscuits
directions: Cut Crisco into flour.
Pour in buttermilk.
Mix with spoon to form a soft ball.
Roll out and cut with biscuit cutter.
Makes 8 biscuits.
Put in Crisco oil; turn upside down in oil.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes or until done.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Spray a 9 x 13-inch casserole with Pam.
Melt margarine.
Add 1/2 stuffing mix in bottom of casserole.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Top with the other 1/2 package of stuffing mix and bake for 45 minutes at 375°.
This recipe can be halved.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Cook 30 minutes.
Serve on warm buns.

title: ornament dough
directions: Sift together flour and salt in a large bowl.
Add water slowly.
Knead until smooth.
Roll dough out on floured surface to 1/4-inch thick.
Use cookie cutters to cut shapes.
Poke a hole in top for thread or ribbon for hanging ornaments.
Bake at 200° for 45 minutes.
When completely cool, these can be painted or shellac.
Great fun for the kids at Christmas or anytime.

title: oriental chicken
directions: Season chicken with salt and pepper.
Mix all ingredients together.
Place chicken with other ingredients in baking pan. Bake at 350° until chicken is done and tender (about 30 minutes). If needed, stir small amount of water to juices while cooking.
If desired, a small amount of flour or cornstarch may be stirred into juices to thicken.

title: confetti torte
directions: Beat egg whites with cream of tartar until foamy.
Gradually beat in sugar and continue beating until very stiff and glossy. Fold in vanilla.
Turn 2 (8-inch) cake pans upside down.
Cover with brown paper.
Spread with meringue. Bake in 275° oven for 1 hour.
Cool.

title: cranberry apple casserole
directions: Combine apples,
cranberries
and
2 tablespoons flour. Toss to coat fruit.
Add 1 cup white sugar.
Mix well and pour into buttered
2-quart casserole.
Combine oatmeal, nuts, 1/2 cup flour, brown sugar and margarine.
Mix well and spoon over fruit mixture.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: lemon congealed salad
directions: Drain juice from pineapple and save.
Prepare lemon jello as directed and pour into a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Allow to jell a little.
Add pineapple to jello and stir well.
Let it jell completely.
Mix 1 cup pineapple juice, flour and beaten eggs in saucepan over low heat for 10 minutes.
Cool.
Spoon over jello layer.
Then spoon whipped topping over this layer.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Put back into refrigerator.

title: beef stew casserole
directions: Put all ingredients in covered casserole or roaster and bake for 5 hours at 250°.
Makes its own gravy.
Serves 6.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients together in a bowl.
Dip the chicken, first in butter, then in bread crumb mixture.
Place in baking dish.
Drizzle any extra butter over chicken and sprinkle with any remaining crumb mixture.
Bake at 350° for approximately 35 to 45 minutes until tender.

title: mini cream cheese biscuits
directions: Beat cream cheese and butter at medium speed of an electric mixer until creamy.
Gradually add flour, beating at low speed until blended.
Spoon dough into ungreased mini muffin pans, filling full.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until golden.
Serve immediately.
Yields:

title: huntington chicken
directions: Cook spaghetti or macaroni in boiling salted water for 2 minutes, stirring.
Turn off heat; cover and let stand 10 minutes. Arrange layer of chicken, then pasta, then cheese, until all is used in baking dish.
Cover with broth; sprinkle with crumbs. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes; you can add a little chopped onions.

title: chicken giovanna
directions: Cut chicken into halves.
Put a slice of ham and cheese on each half.
Roll tightly, starting with narrow end.
Secure with toothpicks.
Melt butter and mix with bread crumbs.
Roll chicken in this mixture.
Place in shallow buttered baking dish and bake for 40 minutes at 400°.
Makes 4 servings.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix sugar, oil and eggs.
Add pumpkin.
Add all dry ingredients.
Pour into greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: rice and sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage with onion; drain.
Add soup and milk and cook until thick.
Mix in casserole with rice, salt and pepper to taste. Place in 350° oven for about 20 minutes.
(I cook my rice first in my casserole using 1 cup rice, a little salt and 2 cups of boiling water.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Then fold in sausage mixture and finish off uncovered.)

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Crush vanilla wafers.
In another bowl, cream the oleo and add sugar and eggs, one at a time.
Beat well. Add wafers and milk. Mix well. Add coconut and pecans. Bake 1 1/4 hours in a 325° oven.

title: carrots and cheese
directions: Crush corn flakes and mix with 1 tablespoon melted butter. Set aside.
Brown onion in remaining butter and add to flour, salt and milk, making a white sauce.
Cook until thick, remove from burner and add cheese until melted.
Stir in carrots with sauce. Pour into a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle corn flakes as topping.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Mix and bake 20 minutes at 400°.

title: german butter cookies
directions: Cream butter with sugar.
Add raw egg yolks and beat good. Push cooked yolks through grater and mix in batter.
Combine flour and dry ingredients.
Add to batter.
Add pecans now, if desired. Roll out to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut with cookie cutters.
Brush with egg white; sprinkle with colored sugar heavily.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: beer biscuits
directions: Stir and drop in greased muffin pans.
Bake at 400°.
Muffins, 18 minutes or loaf pan, 24 minutes.
Can easily be frozen for later use.
Makes 16 to 18 muffins or small loaf of bread.

title: apricot cake
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Cream shortening and sugar, creaming well.
Blend in eggs and egg yolks.
Beat one minute, then add 1/4 of dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Blend in milk. Combine apricot nectar and lemon extract and add alternately with remaining dry ingredients to greased mixture.
Blend thoroughly. Pour into 3 greased, floured pans.
Bake about 25 minutes in 350° oven.

title: parmesan vegetable toss
directions: In a large bowl, combine mayonnaise, Parmesan cheese, sugar, basil and salt.
Add broccoli, cauliflower, onion and water chestnuts; toss.
Cover and refrigerate for several hours or overnight.

title: apple bean bake
directions: In large skillet, melt butter.
Add cubed apples and cook until tender.
Add sugars and stir until sugars are melted.
Stir in catsup and spices; mix well.
Add beans and gently mix well. Pour mixture into 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour. Serves 8.

title: holiday fruit drops
directions: Sift together into bowl and reserve flour, soda and salt. Cream butter, sugar and eggs.
Add buttermilk, vanilla and flour mixture, mixing well.
Stir in chopped nuts, candied cherries and pitted dates.
Drop by teaspoon on lightly greased cookie sheet. Top each with a nut half if desired.

title: sour cream chicken enchiladas
directions: Mix ingredients except tortillas, reserving half of cheese and onions.
Fill and roll tortillas.
Place fold side down in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese and onions.
Bake 30 minutes in 350° oven (covered).

title: date nut balls
directions: Place sugar, dates and butter in a double boiler.
Cook slow for approximately 10 minutes until sticky.
Remove from heat.
Add pecans, Rice Krispies and vanilla.
Let cool.
Fill 1 teaspoon full, roll in a ball and roll in powdered sugar.

title: lemon angel pie
directions: Whip egg whites, cream of tartar and salt until foamy.
Slowly beat in 1 cup sugar until meringue is stiff and glossy.
Spread into well-buttered and floured 9-inch pie pan.
Bake at 300° for 40 minutes, until dry and crisp.

title: aunt jane's pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. Cream together the butter, the margarine and the oil. Gradually add sugar and eggs; beat well. Add the baking powder and flour.
Mix well. Add the milk and all flavoring. Mix well. Bake in a greased angel food pan 1 1/2 hours.

title: health bread
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: chicken-broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter.
In large casserole dish, mix Cheez Whiz and cream of mushroom soup.
Add butter, celery and onion while warm.
Mix in rice, broccoli and chicken.
Sprinkle pimiento on top.
Cover and bake 30 to 40 minutes or until golden in color.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: club day chicken casserole
directions: Mix stuffing with hot water and melted butter.
Place half in a buttered pan.
Mix chicken, onion, celery, mayonnaise, salt and spread over stuffing.
Top with remaining stuffing.
Beat eggs and milk; pour over mixture.
Spread mushroom soup over the top. Sprinkle with cheese.
Put in refrigerator overnight.
Bake, uncovered, for 50 to 60 minutes.
Bake at 325°.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: five star broccoli salad
directions: Mix broccoli and onion together and set aside in refrigerator. Mix mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar together and set aside.
One hour before serving, stir in bacon, sunflower seeds and raisins. Then add mayonnaise mixture, mixing well.
Refrigerate.
Right before serving, stir in 1 cup grated mild or medium Cheddar cheese.
This is an excellent salad and very colorful.

title: italian pasta-bean soup mix
directions: If Packaged for Gift:
Put beans into a 3 to 3 1/2-cup jar with tight fitting lid.

Put pasta in a sandwich size plastic bag and place on top of beans. Put remaining ingredients into sandwich bag or make a pouch using cheesecloth, plastic wrap or fine netting. Close tightly or tie with a ribbon. Put packet in with beans and pasta or tie to jar.
Be sure to include the following cooking directions.

title: beale spoon bread
directions: Pour hot water over corn meal.
Stir and cook on low heat about 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add butter; cool slightly and add milk, salt and egg yolks.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold in gently.
Add baking powder, stirring just enough to mix.
Place immediately in buttered casserole in preheated oven at 400° for about 25 minutes.
Serve at once.

title: chicken and noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles in boiling salted water until tender.
Drain. Combine with other ingredients and place in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: cocoa syrup
directions: Combine cocoa, sugar and salt in saucepan.
Mix well and stir in cold water to make a smooth paste.
Blend in hot water and vanilla.
Simmer 4 to 5 minutes, stirring until thick and smooth. If more rich syrup is wanted, use 1 cup hot milk for hot water. Store and use as you would any other chocolate syrup.

title: shane's chili recipe
directions: Brown hamburger.
Add remaining ingredients, let simmer a little then eat.
Can substitute ground venison for hamburger.

title: brazil nut fruitcake
directions: Mix together nuts, dates and cherries.
Sift dry ingredients over them and mix.
Add eggs and vanilla; mix again.
Pour into lined loaf pan.
Bake 1 3/4 to 2 hours at 300°.

title: carrot cake
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar and oil.
Mix dry ingredients (flour, spices) together and add to egg mixture.
Add mashed carrots. Beat in nuts by hand.
Bake in a 13 x 9-inch pan at 375° for 1 hour.

title: s & w rigatoni fagioli
directions: Heat olive oil in a large skillet.
Saute chicken, stirring frequently, until cooked. Add onion and garlic.
Saute 2 to 3 minutes.
Stir in S & W ready-cut tomatoes and basil. Simmer 3 to 5 minutes, stirring occasionally. Add rigatoni and
S & W white beans; toss well to coat. Season with salt and pepper.
Remove from heat.
Garnish with Parmesan cheese.
Serves 3 to 4.

title: summer pasta with sauce
directions: Toss with hot pasta.
If desired, cilantro, artichoke hearts, mushrooms or other vegetables may be added.

title: smooth 'n melty pie
directions: Blend cream cheese, mints and sugar until smooth.
Add half and half, beating until fluffy.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into crust and chill well.

title: rose's hot chicken
directions: Blend 1 tablespoon soy sauce and cornstarch in a bowl; mix in chicken and set aside.
Combine remaining 2 tablespoons soy sauce sherry, sugar and white vinegar; set aside.
Heat Planters peanut oil in wok or large skillet over high heat.
Add red pepper, cook until pepper turns black; add chicken and stir-fry 2 minutes. Remove and set aside.
Stir-fry scallions and ginger for 1 minute. Return chicken to wok and cook 2 minutes, stirring constantly. Add soy mixture; cook 1 minute longer, stirring constantly.
Serve over hot rice (use Uncle Ben's converted rice).

title: aunt manie's pound cake
directions: Cream sugar, margarine and Crisco until blended well.
Add eggs, one at a time, until blended.
Add flour alternately with milk, beating constantly.
Add vanilla and stir in.
Place in greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 25 minutes.
Cool thoroughly and remove from pan.
Keep in cake keeper.
May be frozen.

title: cracker salad
directions: Beat egg whites.
Add sugar and beat some more.
Fold in crackers and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes in a 9 x 12-inch dish.
Let cool and spread with topping.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Mix together with flour and pat into a 9-inch pie pan with fingers.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.
Cool.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix
all
ingredients together.
Spray pan with cooking spray. Put
in pan and top with ketchup.	Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: hush puppies
directions: Sift cornmeal and other dry ingredients together.
Mix beaten eggs and other liquid ingredients.
Add all together and drop by spoonfuls in deep fat, 350°.
Brown and drain on paper towel.

title: rolled stuffed fillets
directions: Cook onion in butter until tender (not brown).
Stir in crumbs and seasonings.
Blend in 1/2 cup of mayonnaise.
Cut fillets in 5 (8-inch long) strips (Taste O' Sea brand is already cut).
Spread with stuffing and roll up.
Place in greased casserole or baking cups, uncovered.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Spread with remaining mayonnaise.
Bake for 20 minutes longer.
Garnish with parsley.
This is rich.

title: baked apples
directions: Core apples; peel a strip from the top of each.
Place apples in 2-quart casserole.
Combine the raisins, brown sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Spoon into center of apples.
Bake in a 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes or until apples are tender, basting occasionally with the cooking liquid.
Serve warm with ice cream, light cream or yogurt, if desired.
Serves 4.

title: toll house pie
directions: Mix; pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: picnic perfect chocolate cake
directions: Mix all ingredients except eggs well 2 minutes.
Add eggs, beat, pour in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch or 2 round pans. Bake at 325° until done, approximately 45 to 50 minutes.
(This is a very dark moist chocolate cake.)

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until light and foamy.
Add sugar, oil, zucchini and vanilla and mix lightly, but well.
Combine the flour, salt, baking soda, baking powder and cinnamon.
Add to egg zucchini mixture.
Stir until well blended.
Add nuts.
Pour into lightly greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Batter fits 2 (9 x 5) loaf pans, 3 (8 x 3) loaf pans or 7 (5 x 3) mini loaf pans.

title: fudge pie
directions: Melt margarine.
Sift sugar, cocoa and flour together.
Beat eggs, milk and vanilla.
Add liquids to dry ingredients.
Blend well.
Pour in unbaked crust.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix sugar and oil together.
Sift together flour, baking powder, soda, salt and cinnamon together.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well, then add carrots, pineapple and remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: easy cheesy biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In a medium bowl, combine the flour, cream and cheese.
Mix well until the mixture forms a ball.
Roll out on a lightly floured surface to the thickness of about 1/2-inch.
Cut with a 1 1/2 or 2-inch biscuit cutter.
Dip each biscuit in the melted butter.
Place on an ungreased cookie sheet, spacing the biscuits about 1-inch apart.
Bake for 10 to 15 minutes until lightly browned.

title: brown sugar squares
directions: Cream sugar and margarine; add 1 egg yolk (unbeaten).
Add sifted flour with salt.
Pat thin on ungreased cookie sheet. Brush on unbeaten egg white.
Sprinkle chopped nuts over this and press in the dough.
Bake 25 minutes in a 325° oven.
Cut into squares immediately after baking.

title: slow cooked pepper steak
directions: Cut beef into 3 x 1-inch strips.
Place in crock-pot.
Combine the next 4 ingredients and pour over beef.
Cover and cook on low 5 to 6 hours.
Add tomatoes and green peppers; cook on low for 1 hour longer.
Combine the cold water and cornstarch to make a paste.
Stir into liquid in slow cooker and cook on high until thickened.
Serve over noodles or rice.

title: boiled fruit cake
directions: Boil together water, sugar, shortening, raisins, cinnamon, cloves, apples and salt.
Cool.
Add dry ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: saucepan brownies
directions: Melt shortening and butter in an 8 x 8-inch metal cake pan. Add cocoa and stir until well blended.
Stir in vanilla and sugar. Add eggs and mix well.
Add flour, salt and nuts.
Spread evenly in same pan.
Bake 25 minutes in a 350° oven.
Frost with chocolate frosting while still warm.

title: cranberry salad deluxe
directions: Melt cranberry sauce; add salt, sugar and gelatine which has been soaked in cold water.
Add to hot mixture and cool.
When nearly set, add walnuts, celery, apple and pineapple.
Chill until firm.

title: blackberry cobbler (or peach)
directions: Stir all ingredients together and bake at 375° in greased pan 30-40 minutes.
Makes its own crust.

title: buckeyes
directions: Melt butter and mix with peanut butter. Mix in powdered sugar. Roll into small balls. Melt paraffin wax and morsels in double boiler. Put toothpick in peanut butter balls and dip in melted chocolate. Place on wax paper.

title: green wonders
directions: Mix all ingredients. Make small balls and freeze. Remove as needed. Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350° on ungreased cookie sheet.

title: old-fashioned brownies
directions: Melt shortening and chocolate together.
Mix sugar and eggs; add to shortening mixture.
Sift flour with salt and baking powder; add to other ingredients.
Then mix in vanilla and nutmeats.
Bake in a lightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 325° for 25 minutes.
(If desired, leave out white sugar and use 1 1/2 cups brown sugar.)

title: orange balls
directions: Cream butter, sugar and orange juice together.
Add remaining ingredients.
Shape into balls and dip in powdered sugar or coconut.
Makes 36 balls.

title: chicken paprikas
directions: Melt shortening in deep heavy skillet or Dutch oven.
Add onions and saute until golden.
Remove from pan.
Add chicken pieces, browning lightly.
Sprinkle with seasonings and return onions to pan.
Add water, cover and simmer until tender, about 1 hour.
Remove chicken and keep warm.
Pour off about half of the drippings.
Stir flour into sour cream.
Add to drippings in pan, simmer gently until thoroughly heated.
But do not boil. Pour over chicken.
Serve with dumpling noodles.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chess squares
directions: Mix the cake mix, butter and 1 egg.
Spread into pan.

title: basic biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 400 degree. Dissolve yeast in warm water; set aside. Mix dry ingredients together, Cut in shortening, Add yeast and buttermilk and mix well. Turn dough onto lightly floured surface and roll out to desired thickness. Cut with small biscuit cutter and place on greased baking sheet. Bake for 12 minutes or until golden brown.

title: fluffy 2 step easter cheesecake
directions: Beat cream cheese and sugar in large bowl with whisk or mixer on high speed until smooth. Gently stir in whipped topping. Spoon into prepared graham cracker crust. Refrigerate 3 hours and top with pie filling.

title: old fashioned ice cream
directions: Beat eggs and sugar together.
Add cream and flavoring.
Fill freezer within 2 or 3 inches of top with whole milk.
This will make one gallon.

title: orange sherbet
directions: Mix milk and Orange Slice in churn.
Churn according to churn's directions.

title: long boy sandwich
directions: Cut bread lengthwise into thirds.
Spread cut sides of bottom portions with butter.
Top with lettuce leaves.
Roll each slice of meat up as for jelly roll.
Arrange 8 rolls crosswise on lettuce on each sandwich.
Spread center portion of bread with butter; place over meat rolls.
Top with lettuce leaves.
Arrange 3 tomato slices on lettuce on each sandwich.
Combine deviled ham, cream cheese and relish.
Top tomato slices with deviled ham mixture; cover with top slices of bread.

title: super quick chili
directions: Brown hamburger and onion in dish by microwaving on High until pink is gone.
Add soup, tomato sauce and seasonings; cover. Microwave on High 5 minutes.
Reduce to simmer (6) for 10 minutes. Cover with crushed tortilla chips or Fritos.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 1 1/2 cups boiling water.
Combine 1 cup cold water and enough ice cubes to make 2 1/2 cups.
Add to gelatin with lemon juice; stir 2 minutes.
Let stand until slightly thickened.
Fold in drained pineapple and shredded carrots.
Chill.

title: broccoli
directions: Combine ingredients and put into casserole.
Sprinkle cheese on the top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: cabbage and noodles
directions: Cook noodles and drain.
Cook shredded cabbage for 5 minutes and drain.
Saute onions until they are transparent.
Place cabbage, wide noodles and sauteed onions together in a large pan and mix.
Cover pan and allow cabbage and noodles to simmer for a few minutes, until done.

title: isabel's california potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes with skins on.
Chill and then grate.
Make sauce from other ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Cook until cheese melts, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat.
Put potatoes in greased casserole and pour sauce over potatoes.
Make crumb topping using corn flakes or crackers mixed with margarine. Bake for 45 minutes in preheated 350° oven.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Cook cranberries, water and sugar until berries are soft.
Let cool!
Make jello, using only hot water called for.
Stir all ingredients together and refrigerate.

title: honey granola bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Line an 8 or 9-inch square baking pan with foil. Lightly grease foil. Beat butter, honey and vanilla in a large bowl with electric mixer until well blended. With mixer on low speed, add egg, flour, granola and raisins and beat just until blended. Spread in prepared pan. Bake 25 to 30 minutes until pick inserted near center comes out clean. Cool in pan on rack. Drizzle glaze over top. When glaze has set, lift foil by ends to cutting board. Cut into bars. Makes 24.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Roll pizza dough out on pizza tin or cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly brown.
Combine Cool Whip and softened cream cheese on cooled crust.
Top with fruits of your choice (grapes, blueberries, orange sections, kiwi, cantaloupe, strawberries).

title: rice crispy cereal crust
directions: Combine ingredients and press into bottom of 8-inch pie pan. Chill while preparing filling.
Carbohydrate 2.5 g, protein .3 g, fat 3.7 g, calories 45.
Serving size 1/8 crust = 1/4 fruit exchange, 1 fat exchange.

title: chess pie
directions: Mix together and pour into crust.
Cook at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: tea cookies
directions: Beat butter, sugar and vanilla until smooth and creamy.
Mix in flour and salt.
Add nuts, mixing well.
Cover and chill at least 1 hour or until dough is stiff enough to shape into marble-sized balls.
Place cookies on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes or until set, but not brown.
While still warm, roll in powdered sugar.
Let cool and roll again.

title: hot dog wrap ups
directions: Wrap each hot dog with a small piece of bacon.
Place in slightly greased pan.
Sprinkle with brown sugar and a little water, just about 4 tablespoons, more if needed.
Bake about 20 minutes at 350°.
They are done when bubbling.

title: artichoke spread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Drain artichoke hearts and chop.
Add all other ingredients and place in a buttered shallow baking dish. Cook in oven for 20 to 25 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool for 5 to 8 minutes.
Serve with crackers or baguette slices.

title: cheese dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: banana cream pie
directions: Or you can use 1 large package of Jell-O pudding and pie filling (banana cream, French vanilla or vanilla).
You can use instant but the type you cook is better.

title: raspberry sauce(hindbaersovs)
directions: Thaw frozen raspberries and place in covered saucepan.
Bring to a boil and simmer 5 minutes.
Strain and discard pulp.
Blend cornstarch and water and add it to the juice, stirring constantly. Cook until mixture boils and thickens.
Chill until serving time.

title: hash brown supreme
directions: Combine potatoes and melted butter.
Stir in sour cream, soup, onion, shredded cheese, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan well.
Combine corn flake crumbs with butter and sprinkle on top of mixture once placed in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Cover mixture with foil.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Uncover and bake an additional 20 minutes.

title: sherried chicken(serves 6)
directions: Wash and dry chicken.
Trim off fringe fat, if any.
Arrange the chicken pieces skin side up in a shallow ovenproof nonstick pan.
Bake in a preheated 450° oven 20 to 25 minutes, until the skin is crisp and well rendered of fat.
Drain and discard fat. Add remaining ingredients to pan.
Lower heat to 350°.
Continue baking, basting occasionally, until chicken is tender (about 30 minutes).
Spoon pan juice over chicken to serve.
Four servings, 205 calories each.

title: pina colada cake
directions: Bake cake as directed.
Punch hole in cake while hot and spread Eagle Brand milk over.
Let cool 10 minutes.
Put 1 can creamy coconut spread over cake.
Let cool completely.
Spread Cool Whip over cake.
Add one can Angel Flake coconut.
Keep refrigerated.

title: fat man pie
directions: Mix and spread in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Mix well.
Bake for 30 minutes at 375°.

title: farmer's breakfast(we use for saturday night supper)
directions: Boil potatoes until done.
Brown bacon and remove.
Save about 2 tablespoons grease in skillet.
Cut up potatoes and onion; add black pepper and brown in grease.
Add drained tomatoes and eggs and a little more black pepper.
Cover and cook until set.
May need to cook some with lid off.

title: squash casserole #1
directions: Cook
onions
in butter until light brown.
Combine all ingredients
and pour into well-greased baking dish.
Top with additional bread crumbs and dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sloppy cheese
directions: Make your favorite Sloppy Joe recipe and simmer until done. Add Velveeta cheese.
Stir until melted.
Place on buns.
Wrap in foil and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: down south barbecue
directions: Crock-pot:
Put 1/2 sliced onions on bottom of crock-pot, then add meat, cloves and water with remaining sliced onions on top. Cover and cook overnight or 8 to 10 hours on low.
Remove bone and fat from meat.
Put meat back in crock-pot.
Add chopped onion, Tabasco and barbecue sauce.
Cover and cook 1 to 3 hours on high or 4 to 8 hours on low, stirring 2 to 3 times.
Serve from crock-pot on large toasted buns.

title: peanut butter brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 17 x 11-inch jelly roll pan.
In large bowl, combine sugar, flour, cocoa and baking powder.
In medium size bowl with wooden spoon, beat together the butter and peanut butter until light and fluffy.
Gradually beat in eggs and milk.
Add peanut butter mixture to flour mixture; stir until smooth and well combined.
Spread evenly into greased pan.
Bake brownies about 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 30 brownies.

title: kentucky hot brown
directions: In a 4-quart, heavy saucepan, melt butter.
Over medium heat, mix in flour until smooth.
Add milk slowly, stirring constantly, until thick.
Add Tabasco sauce and Parmesan cheese.
Remove from heat.
Take out 1/2 cup sauce and add the two beaten egg yolks. Mix well and return to the remainder, stirring constantly.
Add Colby and American cheeses; stir until melted.
Remove from heat.

title: pea casserole (english)
directions: Saute onions, bell pepper and celery in margarine. Combine with other ingredients. Top with bread crumbs. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pistachio fruit salad
directions: Mix all and refrigerate.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Cook roast and cut into small pieces.
Dice potatoes, onion, carrots and celery.
After meat is tender add all other ingredients, except tomato juice, to meat and meat stock.
When everything is cooked add juice and boil.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: spinach salad
directions: Cut stems off spinach leaves.
Rinse well.
Mix and refrigerate salad oil, sugar, catsup, vinegar, Worcestershire sauce and onion. Salt to taste.
Top with crisp bacon and hard-boiled eggs.

title: miniature chicken salad puffs
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Fill pastries with salad.
Garnish with slices of green and ripe olives and fresh parsley.
Yield: 36.

title: sunny island salad
directions: In large bowl, sprinkle lemon juice over banana.
Add chicken, pineapple and strawberries; toss to mix.
Place lettuce leaves on individual serving plates.
Top with salad.
Sprinkle with sesame seed.
Serve with dressing and crackers.
Makes 4 main dish servings.

title: chocolate pate
directions: Chop chocolate; place in bowl.
Heat butter and cream to scald.
Pour over chocolate.
Stir to melt.
Add cinnamon, Kahlua, vanilla and cashews.
Pour into lightly greased mold (loaf pan); chill.

title: microwave baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Cover and cook 10 minutes.

title: chris' granola
directions: Place all ingredients into large bowl.
Mix well and spread onto cookie sheets.
Spread to about 1/2-inch thick.
Bake at 300° for about 60 minutes, turning or stirring every 15 to 20 minutes until golden brown or dry.

title: rich egg bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Scald milk and allow to cool and set aside.
Add to yeast mixture the sugar, oil, eggs and salt. Add scalded milk alternately with flour.
Mix as you would for any bread dough.
Allow to rise 2 hours.
Turn onto floured board and knead until smooth and not sticky.
Divide dough into 2 loaves and place in greased pans.
Allow to rise again.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes or golden brown on top.
This dough may also be used for cinnamon rolls or doughnuts.

title: harvest popcorn
directions: In a large roasting pan, combine popcorn, shoestring potatoes and nuts.
Set aside.
In a small bowl, combine melted margarine, Worcestershire sauce, lemon pepper seasoning, garlic powder and onion powder.
Pour over popcorn mixture, stirring until evenly coated.
Bake in preheated oven at 325° for 8 to 10 minutes, stirring mixture once.
Cool.
Stir in airtight containers.

title: drop teacakes
directions: Mix all ingredients together and drop on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° or 325° for approximately 15 minutes.

title: heavenly pie
directions: Melt candy bar in large bowl.
Add Cool Whip and mix together until the candy bar has been completely dissolved.
Pour into crumb pie shell.
Let set in refrigerator until cool.
Garnish with whipped cream and almonds.

title: blueberry jello salad with topping
directions: Scald the jello in the boiling water; add pineapple and blueberries.
Chill.

title: von's soft molasses cookies
directions: Beat Egg; add Sugar, Shortening, Molasses and Water.
Sift dry ingredients and add to mixture.
Mix well and chill.
Drop by teaspoon and bake at 375 for 10 minutes.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Combine egg, milk, 2/3 cracker crumbs, salt and pepper.
Stir in corn, onion and pimiento; mix well.
Turn into 1-quart casserole.
Toss melted butter with remaining 1/3 cup cracker crumbs; sprinkle atop corn mix.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 75 minutes.

title: mostaccioli sauce
directions: Brown ground beef and onions.
Drain grease.
Add to other ingredients.
Cook 10 minutes.
Pour over noodles.

title: milk noodles
directions: Combine eggs and 1 cup of milk in a bowl; mix well.
Add sifted flour and salt; mix well.
Stir in just enough milk until stiff dough forms; knead well.
Roll into a thin rectangle on a lightly floured surface; dust with additional flour and cut into thin strips.

title: apple nut cake #2
directions: Mix the apples, eggs, sugar, cinnamon, oil, and chopped nuts together.
Mix flour, baking soda, and salt together.
Then combine all ingredients.
Grease a Bundt pan.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: seafood casserole
directions: Saute first 4 ingredients in butter; add all but milk and white sauce.
Stir until well mixed and warmed thoroughly.
Add milk and white sauce last.
Pour into a greased baking dish.
Bake in 325° oven for 45 minutes.
Can be served with rice.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour over 2 to 3 cups berries in unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 375° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: layered salad
directions: Place a layer of lettuce. Add each vegetable in layers. Top off vegetables with more lettuce. Spread over lettuce 2 cups mayonnaise. Sprinkle 2 tablespoons sugar over mayonnaise. Add the Mozzarella cheese. Let set for 24 hours. Sprinkle bacon bits before serving, if desired.

title: pork chops supreme
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Season chops with salt and place in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan or other large, shallow baking pan.
Top each chop with onion and lemon slices.
Put 1 tablespoon brown sugar and 1 tablespoon catsup on top.
Cover and bake one hour.
Uncover and bake 30 minutes longer, basting occasionally.
Serves 4.

title: no-fat tuna pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta in boiling water for 10 to 12 minutes.
Drain and rinse with cold water.
In a large bowl, combine yogurt, honey, lemon juice, vinegar and spices.
Stir in pasta and remaining ingredients.
Serve at room temperature.
If salad needs to be made ahead of time, store in refrigerator.
But let set at room temperature 15 minutes before serving.

title: jimmie nichols' fish camp relish
directions: Place sugar, salt, vinegar and peppers in pan; let come to a boil.
Put in onions and let come to a boil again.
Now put in tomatoes; allow to heat.
Do not let the tomatoes boil.
Place in jars and seal.
Makes 20 pints.

title: beef enchiladas
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine beef, 1/2 cup cheese and onions; set aside.
Combine soups and enchilada sauce.
Dip tortillas in hot oil to soften a few seconds on each side.
Top each tortilla with one heaping tablespoonful of meat mixture; roll up.
Place seam side down in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Pour sauce over top and top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Serves 6.

title: chocolate meringue pie
directions: Cook all ingredients in medium saucepan over medium heat. When ready it will be very thick.
May need to use a wire whisk to smooth.
Pour in baked pie shell.

title: oven parmesan chips
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Cut washed, unpeeled potatoes into 1/8-inch thick slices and place in a single layer on lightly buttered baking sheets.

title: mexican pizza
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 12-inch pizza pan.
Sprinkle with cornmeal.
Stir baking mix and water until soft dough forms.
Turn onto surface dusted with baking mix; roll in baking mix to coat. Shape into ball.
Knead 10 times.
Press dough evenly on bottom and up sides of pan.
Bake for 10 minutes.

title: wine cake
directions: Beat all ingredients together.
Bake 45 minutes at 350° in Bundt pan.

title: taco bake
directions: Brown the ground beef with the onion and drain.
Add the salsa, water and Taco seasoning mix.
Stir well and cook 5 minutes over medium hear or until thickened.
Add the olives and the corn. Put in a lightly sprayed 9 x 13 baking dish.
Prepare the Jiffy mix and add the cheese and green chilies to the mixture.
Stir and pour over the meat mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30-35 minutes.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Beat and cook at 350°.

title: salted peanut (spanish) cookies
directions: Cream together sugar, brown sugar and shortening.
Add beaten eggs, then add sifted flour.
Add baking soda, baking powder, vanilla, oatmeal, cornflakes and peanuts.
Mix well.
Roll in size of small walnut.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° until well brown.

title: barbecue beef brisket
directions: Pour liquid smoke over meat and rub on all sides. Sprinkle with celery salt, garlic salt, onion salt and meat tenderizer. Cover with foil and leave in the refrigerator overnight.

title: zucchini squares
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Spread in lightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: sweet pickles
directions: Cut and drain pickles very good.
Put, in a large container, 1 layer of pickles and then sugar, until finished.
Place bag of spice in between.
Stir twice a day for 3 days.
Put into jars.

title: chicken delight
directions: Place rice, hot water and
mushroom soup in a 9x13 pan, stir. Layer chicken breast on top of mixture. Sprinkle onion soup mix over chicken. Cover with foil and bake at 350 degrees for 1 1/2 hours.

title: breakfast bake
directions: Crumble sausage in skillet.
Cook until brown, stirring occasionally.
Drain.
Grease a 13 x 9-inch Pyrex dish.
Line bottom with bread that has been cubed.
Top with cooked sausage and grated cheese.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Top with 1 cup mild Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: beef and broccoli stir-fry
directions: Slice steak diagonally into 1/4-inch thick strips.
Place in bowl with garlic, ginger and soy sauce.
Refrigerate, covered, 20 minutes.
Cut broccoli flowerets.
Peel stem and slice 1/4-inch thick.
Heat 1 1/2 teaspoons of oil in large saucepan.
Add beef and marinade.
Stir-fry until brown 2 to 3 minutes.
Remove from pan and set aside.
Swirl remaining oil around pan.
Add beef broth and onion.
Stir-fry for 6 to 8 minutes.
Add beef broth as needed to prevent sticking.
Stir in meat; heat through.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chicken and artichokes with cream
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Drain artichokes and arrange in greased baking dish.
Place chicken on top.
Combine soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with cheese. Combine bread crumbs and butter.
Sprinkle over casserole.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cherry cheese pie
directions: Cream together the cream cheese, sugar, vanilla and salt. Fold whipped cream into mixture.
Pour into pie shell.
Cover with pie filling and chill.
Makes 1 pie.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Drain sauerkraut and cut into short pieces.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Cover and chill for 8 hours or overnight.

title: freezer pickles
directions: Let cucumbers, onion and salt stand for 2 hours, then drain well.
Combine remaining ingredients; bring to a boil for 1 minute, then let it cool.
Add to cucumbers and onion.
Let set in refrigerator for 2 to 3 days.
Put into containers and freeze. Can also be kept in refrigerator.

title: heath bar coffee cake
directions: Mix margarine, flour and sugar until crumbly.
Take out 1/2 cup of mixture.
Add Heath bars and pecans to 1/2 cup mixture and set aside.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Combine all ingredients, except chocolate syrup and chocolate chips.
Beat for 2 minutes at medium speed.
Pour 3/4 of batter into greased Bundt pan.
Add chocolate syrup to remaining batter and mix well.
Pour on top of mixture in pan and swirl through. Sprinkle chocolate chips on top and bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: corn bread
directions: Combine all ingredients except cheese and pepper.
Pour 1/2 of ingredients into pan, then add cheese and pepper.
Pour in remainder of ingredients and bake 35 to 45 minutes at 400°.

title: ribbon salad(nice for holidays)
directions: Mix 1 1/4 cups water with one package jello.
Pour 3/4 cup jello mixture in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Let set.
Add 3 tablespoons sour cream in remainder.
Spread over the set jello.
Continue with remainder of 4 flavors.

title: ranch stuffed potatoes
directions: Scoop out inside of baked potatoes.
Set potato skins in baking pan.
In mixing bowl, combine potato insides, sour cream and dry Ranch dressing mix.
Fill potato skins with mixture. Sprinkle with shredded Cheddar cheese and bake 12 to 15
minutes at 375°.

title: no bake chocolate-peanut butter balls
directions: Mix sugar, margarine and milk and boil for 1 minute exactly, stirring constantly, then take off stove. Add remaining ingredients. When mixed together, spoon onto cookie sheet and place in refrigerator until hard.

title: apple cranberry pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
In large bowl, combine sugars, cornstarch and cinnamon.
Add fruit.
Mix well.
Turn into pastry lined pan.
Cover with top crust and cut slits.
Seal edges.
Bake 40 minutes or until golden brown.

title: hoppin' john
directions: Heat peas and water to boiling in a medium saucepan.
Cover and remove from heat.
Let stand for 1 hour.
Fry bacon; drain. Add with onion and hot pepper to peas.
Cover and simmer until peas are tender, 1 to 1 1/2 hours; stir in rice, salt, black pepper, tomatoes and green pepper.
Cover and simmer, stirring occasionally until rice is tender, about 25 minutes.
Add additional water, if necessary.

title: wasps nest cake
directions: Mix pudding and milk and cook until it begins to thicken.
Mix with yellow cake mix.
Pour into long pan. Pour butterscotch morsels over top.
Bake at 350°
for 30 to 35 minutes.
Moist and good!
Keep refrigerated.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Saute onions in butter.
Add meat; brown.
Add other ingredients.
Simmer covered 20 minutes.
Cook noodles.
Drain. Serve beef over noodles.

title: melt-in-your-mouth nut streudel
directions: Beat the cream cheese and butter or margarine.
Add flour and mix well. Shape into ball.
Cover and chill 1 to 2 hours.
Cook sugar and milk over medium heat until milk boils and sugar dissolves. Stir occasionally. Add nuts.
Remove from heat.
Cool until spreadable. Roll out dough on lightly floured surface to form an 18 x 12-inch rectangle.
Cut in half lengthwise.
Spread each with nut filling.
Starting from a long side, roll up each strip, jelly roll style.
Cut rolls crosswise in half.
Place seam side down on ungreased cookie sheet. Cut into 1/2-inch thick slices without separating.
Bake in a 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes or until done.
Let cool slightly. Remove and cool on racks.
Dust with powdered sugar. Separate slices into cookies. Cover and refrigerate or freeze.
Makes about 60.

title: hot shrimp dip
directions: Melt cream cheese
in microwave.
Cut up shrimp and put in softened cream
cheese.
Add
other
ingredients
and
whip together.
Pour in	greased casserole.
Bake 35 to 45 minutes, until bubbling at 350°.
Serve hot with wafers or crackers.
A chafing dish can be used.

title: sour cream pineapple pudding
directions: Combine pudding and milk.
Mix thoroughly.
Add sour cream and Cool Whip; mix well.
Layer with pineapple and wafers.

title: greetings apple pie
directions: Place apples in unbaked pie shell (two).
Top with juice; add sugar, spices and oleo.
Cover with other pie crust.
(Use in strips or slit holes).
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix
together cheese, sour cream, sugar, lemon extract, egg yolks,
flour
and
2 tablespoons butter in a large mixing bowl. Beat egg whites stiff and fold in last.

title: tasty lamb shanks
directions: Wipe shanks with damp paper towel.
Remove excess fat. Sprinkle with salt.
Brown meat in hot fat in a heavy skillet or Dutch oven.
Combine remaining ingredients except flour and water. Pour over browned shanks.
Cover snugly and cook over low heat for 1 1/2 hours or until tender.
Skim off fat.
Combine flour and water; add to sauce and shanks.
Cook until sauce is slightly thickened.
Serve with rice.
Serves 6.

title: chocolate chip kiss cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Remove wrappers from chocolate pieces. In a large bowl, beat butter, sugars and vanilla; blend well.
Add flour; blend until smooth.
Stir in small chocolate chips.
Mold scant tablespoonful of dough around each chocolate Kiss, covering completely.
Shape into balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until set.
Cool slightly.
Remove from sheet to wire racks.
Cool completely.
Drizzle topping over each cookie.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: sue's one pan meal
directions: Brown beef and onion until brown.
Drain.
Mix chili powder, salt and pepper to meat.
Set aside.

title: beefy baked beans
directions: Cook ground beef and onion until meat is browned, stirring to crumble meat; drain well.
Combine meat mixture and remaining ingredients.
Stir well.
Place in 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: fruit square cake
directions: Cream together sugar, eggs and butter.
Add flour; mix well. Pour the pie filling into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mark batter slightly with knife; put a tablespoon of filling on each marked square. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Cut so fruit filling is in center of each square; sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: easy apple crisp
directions: Put apples in pan.
Sprinkle flour mixture evenly over top. Add nuts and bake at 350° for about 35 to 50 minutes.
Makes 8-inch square pan.
Serve with ice cream.

title: harvest time apple squares
directions: Combine flour, brown sugar, 1/2 cup sugar and cinnamon; cut in spread until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Stir in walnuts. Reserve 2 cup crumb mixture; press remaining mixture onto bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: sandwich spread
directions: Blend together and store in pint jar.
Can add 2 tablespoons butter.

title: seafood salad
directions: Boil your macaroni.
In a large bowl, add the macaroni. Sprinkle a little sugar on it and stir.
Cut up your celery and onions very fine (add to bowl and stir).

title: peanut clusters
directions: Melt the first 3 ingredients in a double boiler.
When smooth, add the peanuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on aluminum foil.
Cool.

title: smoked venison
directions: Cut meat to fit smoker rack.
Rinse, drain and dry meat with a towel.
Be sure it is dry.
Rub meat with oil, then liberally apply seasoning.
Place meat on rack over water pan which has been filled with equal parts Coke and water.
Cook approximately 8 to 10 hours.
When done, bone is easily removed from meat.
Slice and serve with your favorite barbecue sauce.

title: green banana salad
directions: Boil green bananas until they are easy to peel.
Remove peel; cut into cubes.
Roast cloves of garlic and chop into pieces.
Add to bananas.
Chop scallions, using only the leaves (green storkes).
Mix dressing, salt and pepper together; add to banana. Serve.

title: raspberry salad
directions: Start to whip whipping cream and add the package of cream cheese.
Set aside.
Mix the water and jello.
Add the frozen berries and let set.
After the cream and cream cheese are mixed, put on top of set jello.
Add colored mini-marshmallows.

title: blue ribbon sugar cookies
directions: Blend sugar and shortening.
Add the egg and milk; mix well. Add the dry ingredients and the vanilla.
Roll the cookie dough into 1-inch balls.
Flatten with a glass bottom that has been pushed into the cookie dough, then in sugar.
Sprinkle decorative candies or sugars on top to decorate.
Bake at 400° for 5 to 7 minutes.

title: strawberry buttermilk salad
directions: Mix pineapple and jello; heat to boiling and then let cool. When cool, mix in buttermilk, nuts and Cool Whip.
Pour into bowl or mold and chill until firm.

title: chicken fritters
directions: Bring to a boil the butter, salt, pepper and chicken broth. Add flour all at once to the boiled mixture, stirring constantly until mixtures leaves side of pan.
Cool 3 to 5 minutes.
Beat in eggs, one at a time, beating until smooth and glossy after each addition.
Mix in chicken.
Drop by teaspoonfuls into hot fat. Drain on paper towels.

title: ham barbecue
directions: Mix all of the ingredients together and bring to a boil. Reduce heat and add the ham.
Simmer until the ham is thoroughly heated through.

title: soul gumbo
directions: Note: If fresh shrimp is used, it must be peeled and deveined.

title: cajun quiche
directions: Sprinkle cheese evenly over unbaked pie shell.
Add chopped shrimp and crabmeat.
Then add green onions.
Mix eggs, whipping cream, salt and pepper.
Pour over shrimp.
Preheat oven to 400°. Place pie on cookie sheet and bake 40 minutes.
Let stand a few minutes if not completely "set" in center.

title: benedictine sandwich spread
directions: Pare, grate and drain cucumber.
Combine cucumber with remaining ingredients.
A favorite sandwich spread or can be thinned with milk or sour cream to make a delightful vegetable or chip dip.

title: hamburger dills
directions: Wash and slice cucumbers 1/8 to 1/4 inch thick.
Soak for 1 hour in ice water.
Add ice cubes or crushed ice.
Mix water, vinegar, sugar and salt; bring to boil.
Pack cucumbers into clean, hot jars with 3 sprigs of dill, 2 garlic cloves and onion.
Pour boiling hot pickling syrup over cucumbers, leaving 1/2 inch headspace.
Wipe off jar mouth and seal.
Process in boiling water bath canner for 15 minutes.
(Count processing time as soon as hot jars are placed into actively boiling water.)

title: cheddar cheese ball
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Shape into a ball. Sprinkle with chopped walnuts.
Refrigerate to set.
Serve with crackers.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Mix sugar and pineapple; bring to boil.
Add jello.
Mix well. Let cool.
Blend in Cool Whip and cottage cheese.
Let set 2 hours in fridge before serving.

title: bow tie pasta with sausage and creamy tomato sauce
directions: Cook sausage over medium heat, breaking up clumps.
Pour fat from skillet.
Add tomatoes and garlic.
Reduce heat to medium-low.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Skim off excess fat. Add cream.
Increase heat and boil, stirring constantly, 2 minutes or until sauce is thickened and creamy.
Stir in parsley, salt and pepper.

title: sweet fruitcake
directions: Heat oven to 350 degrees, grease and flour (or spray with Pam) a tube pan.
In large bowl, combine eggs and water. Add remaining ingredients, stir by hand until combined.
Pour into prepared pan. Bake for 75 to 85 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan for 30 minutes, loosen edges and remove from pan.
Cool completely, wrap in foil or plastic wrap and store in refrigerator.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Mix all together and refrigerate.

title: old-fashioned chicken soup
directions: Remove liver.
Place clean, cut up vegetables in pot, except for onion, which is put in whole.
Place chicken in pot.
Cook 1 1/2 hours.

title: hot dish
directions: Brown hamburger and onions.
Add other ingredients and pour into casserole.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Take off lid and add 1 can bean sprouts.
Bake another 1/2 hour.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken breasts until tender.
Take off bone.
Cut in small bite-size pieces.
Place chicken with broth in large baking pan.
Add cream of chicken soup and all vegetables.
Top with Bisquick (recipe on box). Bake 1 hour.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: highlander pancakes
directions: Pour milk over oats; let stand 5 minutes.
Mix together flour, baking powder, salt and lightly stir in eggs into oats mixture. Add honey then add dry ingredients and oil, stirring until blended.
Cook on a hot lightly greased griddle.

title: crumb crust
directions: Mix with fork.
Spread and press into pie pan.
Microwave on Roast 7 to 9 minutes (glass pan only) or 350° oven until golden brown.
Cool and fill with favorite filling.

title: company broccoli
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook rice in water, butter and salt as usual.
After cooked, add remaining ingredients.
Stir until Cheez Whiz is melted.
Pour into greased casserole.
Bake until bubbly, approximately 30 minutes.

title: orange juice cookies
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except coconut.
Form into balls and roll in coconut.
Refrigerate 12 hours or overnight.

title: best ever fudge frosting
directions: Mix ingredients and bring to a full boil.
Boil for 1 minute. Cool by placing pot in sink and running cold water around it. Beat until thick enough to spread.

title: celery dressing
directions: Put all ingredients in blender.
Keep refrigerated.

title: king's arms tavern peanut soup(servings 10 to 12)
directions: Saut onion and celery in butter until soft, but not brown. Stir in flour until well blended.
Add chicken broth; stir constantly and bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and pure in food processor or blender.
Add peanut butter and half and half, stirring to blend thoroughly.
Return to low heat and heat until just hot, but do not boil.
Serve; garnish with chopped peanuts.

title: strawberry candy
directions: Mix together.
Form balls (works better with hands wet).
Roll in large package strawberry Jell-O.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except 1/4 cup melted butter and cereal. Place in a large rectangular buttered cooking dish in a smooth, thin layer.
Mix melted butter and cereal and sprinkle on top. Bake 45 to 55 minutes at 350°.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Add enough mayonnaise to moisten. Chill until ready to serve.

title: chicken cutlet casserole
directions: Spray a 13 1/2 x 9-inch pan with Pam. Cut chicken into bite size pieces.
Lay on bottom of pan. Cover with Swiss cheese, cream of chicken soup, wine and stuffing mix. Melt butter and drizzle over stuffing. Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 6.

title: goo-losh
directions: Brown meat and onion until brown.
(Don't drain.)
Add tomatoes and all other ingredients in a crock-pot or deep dish. Simmer 4 hours.
Best if eaten next day.

title: snowballs
directions: Sift flour and salt together.
Mix butter, vanilla and sugar thoroughly.
Blend in flour mixture; add nuts.
Roll into balls and cook on 350° for 10 minutes.
While still hot, roll cooked balls in powdered sugar.

title: sharon's teriyaki marinade
directions: Combine mix with whisk; marinate 6 hours in Ziploc bag, then use for basting.
This can be used for chicken or any steak, grilled or broiled.
Try it on roast chicken in the oven, basting occasionally.

title: english pork pie
directions: Prepare pie dough (2 crusts).
Cube pork (fresh).
Roll in flour and put into bottom crust in pie pan.
Sprinkle in 1 teaspoon flour, nutmeg and salt.
Cover with water; put on top crust and crimp.
Carefully put in preheated oven.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: turkey soup
directions: Using turkey gravy or broth as a base, add all other ingredients to it and stir together.
Cook on low heat for 2 to 3 hours.

title: old-fashioned chocolate ice cream
directions: Allow the gelatin to soak in the water in a saucepan for 5 minutes.
Add the milk and heat, stirring until the gelatin is dissolved.
Remove from heat and add the chocolate syrup, sugar and salt.
Cool; add the creams and the vanilla.
Freeze in crank freezer (can use electric).
Makes 4 quarts.

title: corn and pork chop casserole
directions: Brown meat and alternate potatoes, corn and pork chops. Sprinkle with salt and pepper on each layer.
Cover with approximately 1 1/2 cups milk.
Dot with butter, cover and bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: caramel candy bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Heat caramels and milk in 2-quart saucepan over low heat; stir frequently until melted.
Mix flour, oats, brown sugar, baking soda, egg and salt. Cut in margarine with fork until crumbly.
Press 1/2 of mixture into pan.
Bake 10 minutes.
Sprinkle nuts, then chips over baked layer.
Drizzle caramel mixture over top.
Sprinkle with remaining crumb mixture.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool completely.
Store in refrigerator.
May microwave when ready to eat.

title: apple slices
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine 3 cups flour and salt; cut in shortening with a pastry blender. Mix egg yolk with milk and add to the flour.
Stir just until the dough clings together.
Divide in half.
Roll half into a 15 x 10-inch rectangle and transfer to a jelly roll pan that has been buttered.
Toss together the apples, sugar, butter, flour and cinnamon.
Distribute over the dough.
Roll out remaining dough and cover filling.
Brush with slightly beaten egg white.
Bake 40 minutes.
Combine powdered sugar and water.
Drizzle over pastry while warm.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Cream peanut butter and margarine until smooth.
Add confectioners sugar and mix with hands.
Shape into balls (small ones about the size of marbles).
Melt chocolate by putting in small bowl; place this bowl into larger one with hot water from tap.
Stir until chocolate melts.
Dip balls into chocolate and place on waxed paper.

title: congealed strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jello in 2 cups boiling water.
Add fruits undrained.
Refrigerate for several hours to congeal.

title: persimmon cookies
directions: Cream 1/2 cup butter with 1 cup sugar, then add 1 beaten egg and 1 cup persimmon pulp.
Persimmon pulp needs 1 teaspoon soda dissolved in it first.
Set aside and combine the following.

title: campsite stew
directions: In large skillet, brown beef and onion; drain off fat.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Cover and cook over low heat for 20 to 25 minutes, stirring the mixture occasionally.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chicken pie
directions: Put vegetables, chicken and soup in 1 pie shell.
Season with salt and pepper.
Put the other pie shell on top of the mixture and puncture top shell 5 or 6 times with a fork.
Bake at 425° until pie shells are brown, about 30 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: pink salad
directions: Mix all together and chill.

title: cucumbers
directions: Mix together.
Place in a jar and refrigerate.
Keeps very well.
Do not add any water to this recipe.

title: daddy gene's pie
directions: Place ice cream in mixing bowl.
Stir just enough to soften. Fold in peanut butter, then Cool Whip.
Spoon into graham cracker crusts.
Freeze 4 to 5 hours before serving.
Makes 2 pies.
Will keep several weeks in freezer.

title: lemon bars
directions: Mix 2 cups plain flour, oleo and 1/2 cup powdered sugar together.
Mix well.
Press into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Mix eggs, 2 cups sugar, dash of salt and lemon juice.
Mix 4 teaspoons plain flour and 1 teaspoon baking powder together and add to egg mixture.
Pour into crust and bake for 25 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar while hot.
When cool, cut in squares.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Combine cucumbers, onions, green peppers and whole garlic cloves.
Add salt; cover with ice and mix thoroughly.
Let stand 3 hours.
Drain well; remove garlic.
Combine remaining ingredients; pour over cucumber mixture.
Bring to a boil.
Fill hot jars; adjust lids.
Process in boiling water bath for 5 minutes.
Makes 12 pints.

title: cheese and vegetable chowder
directions: In hot margarine in 3-quart saucepan cook vegetables, covered, stirring occasionally, 20 to 25 minutes or until tender.
Remove from heat.
Stir in flour; mix well.
Cook 1 minute, stirring occasionally.
Add chicken broth to vegetable mixture.
Bring to boiling, stirring constantly.
Gradually stir in cheese.
Cook over medium heat, stirring until cheese has melted.
Gradually add milk. Season with salt and pepper.
Bring just to boiling, but do not boil.
Sprinkle with parsley; serve with croutons.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: stuffin surprise
directions: Mix all ingredient and stuff bird.
Roast at 325°, basting frequently.
Turkey is done when popcorn blows his ass out.

title: pimento cheese spread
directions: Grate cheese and put aside. Mash pimentos with fork into very small pieces. Drain juice. Mix cheese and pimentos, then add mayonnaise and sugar. Salt and pepper to taste.

title: frosty fruit punch
directions: Prepare orange juice and pineapple juice according to package directions.
Prepare lemonade using 3 cans of water.
Combine juices; chill at least 2 hours.
When ready to serve, pour mixture into punch bowl.
Add ginger ale, stirring gently to combine.
Add sherbets to mixture in small scoops.
Yields about 1 1/4 gallons.

title: chili chicken
directions: Boil chicken in water until done (approximately 1 hour).
When cool, cut chicken into chunks and place in bottom of 13 x 9-inch greased pan.
Cut tortillas into strips and lay on top of chicken.

title: hamburg au gratin
directions: Brown hamburg; pour off grease.
Add potatoes and water. Simmer for 1/2 hour.
Add more water, if needed.

title: strawberry frozen yogurt pie
directions: Fold Cool Whip and yogurt together.
Add strawberries.
Put in graham cracker crust.
Freeze about 4 hours.
Let stand at room temperature for about 20 minutes before cutting.
Top with strawberries.
Makes 2 pies.

title: bean and bacon casserole
directions: Place diced bacon and onions in skillet.
Cook until bacon is translucent but not crisp.
Add onion, catsup, mustard, and molasses and cook until heated and bubbling.
Place remaining ingredients in a shallow 2-quart baking dish.
Pour bacon mixture over top, mix gently, and top with bacon slices.
Bake at 350° about 45 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: instant cocoa mix(for hot chocolate)
directions: Mix all ingredients together and store in airtight container. Add 1 or 2 heaping teaspoons to a cup of hot milk.

title: beat and eat frosting
directions: Put egg white, cream of tartar, sugar and vanilla in bowl. Add water and beat with mixer until it forms peaks.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until light and foamy.
Add next four ingredients, mixing lightly but well.
Combine dry ingredients and blend with egg mixture.
Add nuts.
Divide batter into 2 greased loaf pans and bake at 325° for 1 hour or until done.
Test with toothpick. Remove from pan at once and cool on rack.
May be frozen.

title: oatmeal chocolate chip cookies
directions: In a large bowl, cream together butter and white and brown sugars, then add eggs and vanilla.
In another bowl, mix flour and oatmeal (process in blender until powdered), then in the same bowl put in baking powder and soda.
Combine all ingredients in one bowl and add chocolate chips.
Drop cookie dough on a cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 6 to 8 minutes or until light brown.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: large, moist jewish apple cake
directions: Measure the first 6 ingredients into one bowl and mix well. Use a large tube pan (10-inch), greased and floured.
Peel and slice apples and mix with cinnamon and sugar mixture.
Pour half of cake mixture in pan and cover with half of apples.
Add rest of batter and top with rest of apples.
Bake at 350° for 1 3/4 hours. Test and bake longer if needed.

title: velveeta crock-pot dip
directions: Brown hamburger and sausage.
Drain.
Cube the cheese.
Drain pimento.
Put all ingredients in crock-pot.
Heat on high, stirring occasionally until cheese melts.
Then cook on low 3 to 4 hours.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Line dish with foil (have enough foil to cover top of dish). Skin chicken and cut up.
Rub in oil and soy sauce.
Place in dish.
Put celery, onions and bell pepper (sliced) on top.
Grate Cheddar cheese on top and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Pour rest of oil over chicken.
Cover and seal foil around the edges. Cook 1 hour at 350°.
Uncover and brown 10 minutes at 400°.

title: beef curry
directions: On rack in broiling pan, broil beef cubes, turning to brown all sides until rare, about 6 minutes. Set aside.

title: orange wine punch(nice for a brunch)
directions: Place fruit in a bowl. Pour liqueur over fruit; cover. Set aside for 2 or 3 hours. To serve, slowly stir in wine.
Makes 9 to 10 cups.

title: gooey cake
directions: Mix cake mixes, 2 eggs and 1 stick of butter.
Press in bottom of 9 x 12-inch pan.
Combine 1 stick butter, powdered sugar, 2 eggs and cream cheese together.
Pour over cake.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: squash casserole
directions: Boil together squash and onion; then mix in chicken soup and grated carrots.
Pour into buttered dish.
Top with stuffing crumbs.
Dab with margarine.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: crustless pumpkin pie
directions: In a large bowl, whisk egg and egg whites.
Mix all other ingredients, except evaporated milk.
Slowly stir in evaporated milk until blended.
Pour into sprayed 9-inch pie plate.
During baking, the Bisquick will settle to make it's own thin crust. Bake at 425° for 15 minutes, reduce heat to 350° and bake an additional 30 minutes.
Serve with 2 Tbsp. fat free Cool Whip.
Serves 8.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, except chips, and mix well.
Turn into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with crushed chips.
Bake in 400° oven for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken breasts until tender.
Place cooked chicken in bottom of baking dish.
Add chicken soup thinned with a little water or milk.
Add peas and sauteed onion mixed into stuffing mix. Bake at 350° until heated through.

title: tomato soup cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients together: flour, soda, baking powder and spices.
Cream shortening and sugar until fluffy.
Add dry ingredients and tomato soup alternately in small amounts.
Beat thoroughly after each addition.
Stir in nuts and raisins.
Pour into greased loaf pan or tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: messy shrimp
directions: Combine all in a Dutch oven or pot.
Toss well.
Set aside for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Place pot over medium heat and allow mixture to come to a boil.
Stir, cover and cook 5 minutes or until shrimp turns pink.

title: chicken pie
directions: Layer chicken in greased casserole.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over chicken.
Top with pie crust.
Bake at 350° to 375° until browned.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Place carrots, whole or cut up in aluminum foil or foil pan. Add enough water to cover bottom of pan.
Dot carrots with butter and sprinkle brown sugar over top.
Season with a little salt and ginger.
Seal pan with foil and place on barbecue.
Whole carrots take about 20 minutes.
Cook until carrots are tender.
Watch carefully and add water as necessary.

title: layered cranberry-yogurt fruit nut mold
directions: Mix gelatin with sugar and 1 cup cranberry juice cocktail over a low heat until gel is dissolved.
Add 1 cup of juice and set aside.
Drain strawberries and pineapple.
Reserve fruit.
Measure 3/4 cup of juice.
Add juice to gel mixture.
Add whole berry cranberry sauce; stir well.
Pour 1/2 mixture in 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Chill slightly.
Add strawberries and bananas.
Chill until firm.
Spread yogurt and nuts on mixture.
Let gel thicken slightly.
Add pineapple and second banana to gel.
Spoon on yogurt.
Layer and chill.

title: waterless beets and onions
directions: Shred raw beets; place in saucepan with margarine.
Cover with sliced onions.
Sprinkle with sugar, salt and pepper.
Cover with lettuce leaves that have been wetted down.
Cover and simmer 20 to 25 minutes or until tender.
Discard lettuce.
Sprinkle with vinegar or lemon juice before serving.

title: chicken broccoli
directions: Cook broccoli until almost tender.
Layer in buttered Pyrex casserole the broccoli, chopped onion and chopped chicken breasts. Spread mixture evenly on top.
Sprinkle with Ritz cracker crumbs.
Cook at 350° until cheese has melted.

title: easy sausage balls
directions: Combine baking mix and milk in bowl; mix well.
Add sausage and Cheez Whiz; mix well.
Drop by spoonfuls onto baking sheet. Bake at 425° for 15 minutes or until brown; drain.
Yield: 72 servings.

title: baked carrots
directions: Cut the carrots in a diagonal before cooking.
Cook until tender and drain.
Melt cheese and stir in soup.
Mix with carrots and pour into casserole.
Top with buttered crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: joshua's broccoli casserole
directions: Blend mayonnaise, soup and egg in a bowl.
Add onion, broccoli and stuffing.
Fold together.
Put in greased casserole.
Dot with margarine on top; sprinkle with cheese.
Cook for 45 minutes at 325°.

title: cranberry orange relish
directions: Blend the cranberries and oranges in food processor. Add sugar, salt and pecans.

title: potato casserole
directions: Thaw hash browns and mix with green pepper and onion.
Stir in soup and sour cream.
Mix part of cheese into potatoes and salt and pepper.
Spoon into large baking pan.
Spread remaining cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until browned.

title: ugly duckling pudding cake
directions: Blend together well all ingredients except brown sugar and nuts in a large bowl.
Pour into a greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle with brown sugar and nuts.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes or until cake springs back when lightly pressed.
Do not underbake.
Cool in pan 15 minutes.
Spoon hot butter glaze over warm cake.

title: cornbread
directions: In a large bowl, combine dry ingredients.
Then add the egg, milk and oil.
Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes or until the top is golden brown.
After removing the cornbread from the oven, spread butter over the warm cornbread.

title: hamburger hot dish
directions: Use 1 to 2 lb. raw hamburger.
Pat into a large casserole dish. Slice potatoes on top of hamburger.
Slice onions on top of potatoes.
Add 1 can cream of chicken soup.
Add 1 can creamed corn.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 350°, uncovered.

title: chicken veronique
directions: Skin, halve and bone chicken breasts.
Cut into strips; set aside.
In skillet, melt butter over medium-high heat.
Saute mushrooms and onions 2 minutes.
Add chicken strips and saute for 5 minutes.
Blend chicken broth and flour; add to chicken in pan until thick and bubbly.
Cook and stir 1 minute.
Stir in grapes and wine.
Heat through.
Serve over hot rice.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: zucchini drop cookies
directions: Beat thoroughly soda, sugar, egg and oleo; add zucchini.
Add dry ingredients.
Stir in raisins and nuts.
Drop on greased sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Can be frosted.
Also, are good frozen unfrosted to have for a later date.

title: hot cocoa mix
directions: Mix all together; keep in airtight container, in freezer.
Use 2 heaping tablespoonfuls per cup; add hot water.

title: skillet chili mac
directions: Brown meat.
Add all remaining ingredients except cheese sauce; mix well.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat.
Cover.
Simmer 8 to 10 minutes or until macaroni is tender.
Remove from heat. Stir in cheese sauce.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: potato and leek soup
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and simmer 40-50 minutes until vegetables are tender. Mash vegetables with a fork. Serve in individual bowls. Stir in 1 tbsp. or whipping cream and garnish with parsley. This soup is also excellent served cold.

title: old mission salad
directions: Halve avocado; remove pit and peel.
Slice avocado into container of electric blender; add oil, lemon juice, garlic, sugar, salt and mustard.
Cover; whirl until smooth.
Scrape dressing into small serving bowl.
Pare oranges, removing rind and white membrane.
Cut into 1/4-inch thick crosswise slices.
Cut onion into 1/8-inch slices.
Line large chilled salad plate with lettuce leaves.
Arrange orange slices overlapping with onions on lettuce. Spoon some of the avocado dressing over top.
Garnish with olives. Serve with remaining dressing.

title: easy fudge
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter.
Blend together and then add cocoa, vanilla and powdered sugar.
Put into a 9-inch buttered pan and let stand until firm.

title: cranberry sauce
directions: Wash and clean cranberries.
Place cranberries in baking pan. Add sugar and brandy, reserving 2 tablespoons sugar and 1/4 cup brandy.
Stir and mix well; cover with foil.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour; stir every 20 minutes. Remove from oven and add remaining 2 tablespoons sugar and 1/4 cup brandy.
Stir and chill. May be refrigerated for up to 2 weeks.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add 6 eggs one at a time, beat well after each addition.
Add to above; vanilla wafers, crushed, 1/2 cup milk, Flaked coconut, chopped pecans.
Pour into greased and floured tube.
Bake at 275 for 1 1/2 hours or till done.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Mix and place in large casserole dish.
Cover with cornflake crumbs.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: rocky road candy
directions: Microwave chocolate and butterscotch chips 2 to 3 minutes. Stir in marshmallows and peanuts.
Pour in 8 x 8-inch pan. Refrigerate until firm.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Scald 2 cups milk with butter.
Combine all other ingredients except peanut butter.
Gradually add scalded milk.
Cook until thickened.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Top with meringue.
Bake until browned.

title: english muffin delight
directions: Mix together.
Toast muffin; spread with margarine, then with cheese mixture.
Cut in half.
Delicious!

title: plain cake
directions: Cream flour, baking powder, salt and butter until it looks like whipped cream.
Beat separately the eggs and sugar until creamy.
Mix these 2 mixtures together and beat.
Add vanilla. Bake at 350° for approximately 1 1/2 hours (depending on your oven).

title: brownies
directions: Melt oleo and chocolate in top of double boiler.
Add sugar, then eggs.
Mix well.
Add vanilla, flour and pecans.
Bake in 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan, about 25 minutes at 300°.

title: quick caramel frosting
directions: Melt butter in pan; then add brown sugar and milk.
Heat to boiling.
Boil for 5 minutes; then cool for 10 minutes.
After cooled, add confectioners sugar until smooth; then add vanilla. Beat until spreading consistency.

title: smothered potatoes
directions: Dice potatoes.
Cut onions.
Add seasoning and cook potatoes until they are done.

title: hot sausage and cheese hors d'ouevres
directions: Split open sausages and scrape out contents.
Mix sausage with biscuit mix and cheese.
Form into balls and bake on a cookie sheet at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: holubtsi(stuffed cabbage)
directions: In large skillet, saute onion in butter or margarine until golden.
Rinse rice under cold water; drain.
Add 6 cups water to 2-quart pot.
Add rice and let cook, uncovered, until boiling. When boiling, reduce heat to low flame.
Simmer, covered, until rice absorbs water.
Do not overcook!
Remove from heat when rice is done.

title: baked dip
directions: Mix the first eight ingredients together and put in 1-quart greased casserole.
Mix remaining ingredients; sprinkle over top of dip.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Serve warm with crackers.

title: potato soup
directions: In large pot, cook potatoes, carrots and celery in water until tender, about 20 to 30 minutes.
Drain, reserving liquid and setting vegetables aside.
In the same kettle, saute onion in bacon fat until soft.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper; gradually add milk, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Gently stir in cooked vegetables.
Add 1 cup or more of reserved cooking liquid until soup is desired consistency.

title: martha washington candy
directions: Melt margarine and pour over nuts. Combine milk, sugar and coconut. Add nuts and form into balls.
Let set for 4 to 6 hours or overnight.
Melt chocolate and paraffin over hot water.
Using a toothpick, dip balls in chocolate.
Let drip and place on wax paper.
Fill in holes and let cool.
Store in refrigerator or freezer.

title: saucy beef and rice
directions: You will need one large oven bag.

title: smoked salmon alfredo
directions: Melt butter in medium saucepan over low heat.
Stir in milk and Alfredo sauce.
Mix well.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes.
Mix in peas, salmon and pasta.
Heat about 2 minutes.

title: spicy chicken salad
directions: Stir taco seasoning mix with mayo and sour cream.
In a large bowl, combine remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate four hours. Serve over lettuce.
Add corn chips and tomatoes. Serves 8.

title: peanut butter fondue
directions: Mix well.
Place over very low heat until mixture is smooth and creamy.

title: apple snow salad
directions: Cook pineapple, sugar, eggs, water and lemon juice on low heat until thick.
Chill.
Stir in apples, nuts and whipped cream. Pour into 8 x 10-inch glass dish.
Freeze until firm.
Let stand 10 minutes at room temperature before serving.

title: coconut pie
directions: Stir sugar, milk and coconut together.
Beat eggs with spoon by hand before adding. Then add eggs and margarine.
Pour in 2 unbaked pie shells. Bake at 375° on bottom rack in oven until done.

title: mary peck's crab dip
directions: Drain crab; shred in bowl.
Add all ingredients and mix.
If not moist enough, add more chili sauce.
Chill in fridge.
Serve with crackers.

title: baked custard
directions: Combine eggs, sugar and salt.
Slowly add milk and vanilla, blending well.
Pour mixture into a 1-quart casserole or individual custard cups; sprinkle with nutmeg.
Place casserole or cups in a shallow pan with a small amount of water.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes, or until knife inserted halfway between center and edge comes out clean.
Serve warm or chilled.
Yields 4 servings.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, margarine and milk.
Bring to a boil and cook 1 minute.
Add rest of ingredients and mix well.
Spoon onto wax paper and let stand until firm.
Add nuts if desired.

title: corn chowder
directions: In soup pot, cook salt pork, stirring occasionally until brown and crisp.
Remove pork bits.
(Instead of pork fat you can use 2 tablespoons butter.)
To pork fat, add onion and cook until tender, stirring occasionally.
Add potatoes and boiling water; cover. Simmer about 10 minutes or until potatoes are fork-tender.
Add corn, salt, pepper, milk and pork fat; heat well on low.
Serve sprinkled with paprika.
Serve 6.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well. Pour into greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: shrimp ball
directions: Let cream cheese soften until workable.
Mix all ingredients together well by hand.
Shape into ball.
Decorate top with whole shrimp.
Chill at least 2 hours before serving.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Peel eggplant and cut in slices.
Dip eggplant in lemon juice. Cook in boiling salty water until tender.
Drain.
Mush eggplant in small pieces.
Add onions and bell pepper.
Beat egg and combine with milk, black pepper and cracker crumbs.
Mix all ingredients together and bake in a greased baking dish at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: german potato pancakes
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls and saute until browned.
Often served with warm applesauce.

title: gene's special calzone
directions: Let pizza dough rise overnight and punch down as needed.
Roll out pizza dough into a rectangle.
Spread out one layer of salami in a circular pattern completely covering dough.
Cover salami completely with one layer of boiled ham and then cover the ham with layer of hot ham.
