Cover these meats in circular pattern with Provolone.
Pick up one end of dough and fold to the midpoint and then fold the same side once more to the end.
Tuck in sides of calzone so nothing leaks when baked.
Beat a whole egg and brush over calzone so it will brown.
Sprinkle poppy or sesame seeds on top and cut three small slices on top to let steam escape.
Put calzone on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour, checking at 45 minutes and remove when brown. Add 5 to 10 minutes for 2 calzones.

title: two way toffee bars
directions: Cream butter or margarine and brown sugar.
Add egg and vanilla.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Blend in flour.
Spread on jelly roll pan or 2 (9-inch) square pans.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Immediately top with milk chocolate bars.
Spread over surface thinly with spatula.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Sprinkle other half with shredded coconut.
Cool, then cut in bars.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: spinach sausage quiche
directions: Cook sausage and drain.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into 9-inch pie crust.
Bake 1 1/4 hours at 375°.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Boil chicken; remove meat from bones.
Add 1 tablespoon margarine to broth and meat.

title: tomato soup with some "kick"
directions: Saute onions and garlic in oil in soup pot until soft.
Add tomatoes, dill, pepper, honey and water.
Cover and cook over low heat at a slow simmer for about an hour or 45 minutes.
You can serve this with a dollop of nonfat yogurt.

title: pizza bites
directions: Place Triscuits on a cookie sheet.
Spread pizza sauce on Triscuits.
Put pepperoni on top of sauce.
Top with Mozzarella cheese.
Place under broiler until cheese is bubbly.
Serve hot.

title: diabetic oatmeal cookies
directions: Place oatmeal in bowl.
Stir in melted margarine.
Mix and stir together dry ingredients.
Add alternately with milk and vanilla.
Bake at 350° until slightly browned.

title: oven swiss steak
directions: Cut meat into bite size pieces.
Combine 2 tablespoons flour and salt; dredge steak in flour mixture.
Brown in hot oil in large skillet; remove and place in greased baking dish.
Add 2 tablespoons flour to pan drippings; cook over medium heat for 1 minute.
Add tomatoes, celery, carrots and onion; cook until thick.
Stir in soy sauce.
Pour over steak.
Cover; bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.
Serve over rice.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs, oil, sugar and vanilla until thick and foamy.
Stir in zucchini and rest of ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Makes 2 loaves of bread.

title: sweet and sour cabbage
directions: In a large skillet, cook bacon until crisp.
Remove and set aside.
Saute cabbage and onion in drippings until tender.
Add remaining ingredients; stir until thickened.
Stir in bacon. Serve warm.
Serves 6.

title: mike's howdy-do-homemade pretzels
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease cookie sheet with shortening. Cover breadboard with pastry cloth, tucking ends underneath. Cover rolling pin with stockinet cover.
For convenience, place some flour in custard cup.
Sprinkle the covered board and rolling pin lightly with the flour and rub it until it disappears.
Mix flour, milk, cheese, butter, baking powder, sugar and salt to a soft dough in medium bowl with fork.
Gently smooth the dough into a ball on the covered board.
Knead 10 times.
Divide the dough in half.

title: foamy cream sauce
directions: Beat egg white with salt until stiff.
Beat in sugar gradually.
Add egg yolk and beat until thick.
Fold in whipped cream and flavoring.
Serve soon after making.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta as directed on the package. Add peppers and onions, mixing well.
Chill pasta mixture for 2 or more hours (overnight is best).
Add cheese and dressing to pasta.
Mix and chill for at least 30 minutes more, then serve.
This is great with any meat or by itself.
Yields 10 servings, 131 calories, 1 g. fat.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Crush crackers and mix with melted butter.
Cook broccoli. In casserole dish, alternate layers of broccoli, crackers, soup and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: baked ham with peaches
directions: Place ham in a baking pan.
Bake in 375° oven until fat browns.
Mix brown sugar, vinegar, mustard and spread over ham. Cover the baking pan.
Decrease temperature to 300° and bake 1 hour and 30 minutes.
Brush peach halves with butter and roll in corn flakes.
Place in a baking dish.
Bake at 450° until brown. Place 1 teaspoon currant jelly in cavity of each peach and arrange around ham.

title: chicken divan(serves 6)
directions: Cook chicken and cut into pieces.
Mix with mayonnaise and place in pan.
Cover with broccoli and then soup.
Mix stuffing with melted butter and sprinkle on top.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: super salad
directions: Combine ingredients in	a bowl, cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate.

title: brown sugar divinity
directions: Put first 5 ingredients in heavy pan.
Stir until sugars dissolve.
Cook without stirring to 265° on candy thermometer, or to hard ball stage.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Slowly beat in the syrup.
When mixture begins to thicken, add vanilla.
Continue beating until it holds its shape.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Store in airtight container.

title: german-style potato salad
directions: In a 4-quart saucepan, place potatoes; add water to cover. Over high heat, heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover; simmer 20 to 30 minutes until fork-tender.
Drain.
Cool slightly. Cut potatoes into slices.

title: mustard pickles
directions: Bring water, vinegar and salt to a boil.
Pack cucumbers in gallon jar with remaining ingredients.
Fill spaces in jar with dill.
Pour boiling water over pickles.
Wipe off rim and tighten lid.
Flip over on lid to seal.
Let cool and refrigerate at least one week before eating.

title: so good sticky buns
directions: Mix cinnamon and sugar; set aside.
Put marmalade and nuts in the bottom of a well-buttered Bundt pan.
Melt butter.
Dip rolls in melted butter and then dip into sugar and cinnamon.
Place in Bundt pan around the sides.
Pour excess butter and sugar on top. Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.
Cool for 15 minutes before removing from pan.

title: beef enchiladas
directions: *In the dairy case.

title: dump cake
directions: Use 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix and spread the cherry pie filling and crushed pineapple in pan.
Sprinkle box of yellow cake mix over the pie filling and pineapple.
Sprinkle coconut and nuts over top of all.
Dab the 2 sticks of butter or oleo over the top. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: pork chop and potato casserole
directions: Place chops in pan.
Season with salt and pepper.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup grated cheese over chops.
Add sliced onion next, then sliced potatoes and sprinkle rest of cheese.
Cover and bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: egg cheese
directions: Using a heavy pan, heat milk to near boiling.
Have eggs beaten until blended well.
Add buttermilk, salt and sugar.
Beat again until blended and slowly pour into hot milk, stirring slowly (preferably with a wooden spoon).
Allow to heat again a few minutes, stirring slowly until it starts to separate (that's the secret).
When whey starts to form, put in a fine wire strainer to drain.
After drained, set in refrigerator to chill.
Serve with bread and syrup or plain with syrup.

title: graham cracker cookies
directions: Line graham crackers in jelly roll pan.
Sprinkle pecans and chocolate chips over crackers.
Boil margarine and sugar for 2 minutes.
Pour over crackers.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Place bread in bottom of buttered, 8-inch square casserole. Put browned sausage on top of bread.
Add cheese.
Beat eggs; mix with milk, salt and mustard.
Cover and refrigerate overnight. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° until knife inserted in center is clean.

title: turkish meat stew
directions: Combine meat, garlic, onion, pepper and cumin.
Mix well and refrigerate 2 hours.
Brown meats and spices until done.
Add tomatoes with juice and simmer 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve over steamed rice.

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Stir well and add 12 cups flour (all-purpose).
Let rise in warm area for about 1 hour.
In baking pan, coat bottom and sides with oil.
Pinch off as needed and coat both sides of biscuits with oil.
Bake in 350° oven until top is golden brown.
Will keep in refrigerator for about 2 weeks. Keep covered with foil or wrap.

title: molded tuna salad
directions: Heat soup; dissolve the softened cream cheese in soup.
Add gelatine which has been dissolved in the cold water; set aside to cool, then add all other ingredients.
Pour into oblong pan (12 x 8-inch).
Sprinkle with paprika.
Keep refrigerated.

title: oat bran muffins
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir until moistened.
Pour into greased muffin tin.
Bake at 425° for 15 to 17 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: roasted potatoes and onions
directions: In a big plastic bag, place all ingredients; close bag tightly and shake until potatoes are evenly coated.
Empty potatoes into a shallow baking pan.
Bake at 450° for 40 minutes.
Stir occasionally.

title: sour cream potatoes
directions: Mix together.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Top with Rice Krispies.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Add sugar, salt and margarine to milk.
Stir and let cool. Separately, add yeast and 1 teaspoon sugar and 1/4 cup water. Stir and let stand 10 minutes.
Mix together eggs, yeast and milk. Add two cups flour until smooth.
Add remaining flour; cover and let rise until doubles. Make big balls.
Place on greased pan. Let rise 45 minutes.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: mint brownies
directions: Prepare brownie mix using a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat together confectioners sugar, 2 tablespoons creme de menthe and 1 stick margarine until cream.
Frost brownies with it.
Melt together chocolate chips, 3/4 stick margarine and 1 teaspoon creme de menthe; mix together until well blended.
Frost over the confectioners sugar frosting.
Cool at least one hour before cutting.

title: pistachio cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in large mixing bowl. Mix 2 minutes. Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan or 10-inch tube pan. Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes. Cool 10 minutes and remove from pan.

title: hearty soup mix
directions: Combine ingredients in a large airtight container.
Stir to evenly distribute ingredients.
Label container.
Store in a cool dry place.
Use within 6 months.
Shake before using.
Makes about 12 1/2 cups of mix.

title: bean and hamburger casserole
directions: Brown and drain hamburger.
Fry, drain and cut up bacon.
Mix all together in a large casserole dish.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour. Works well in crock-pot, too.

title: biscuit mix
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Use a pastry blender and cut in fat that is firm at room temperature until mixture looks like coarse cornmeal.
Store in tightly covered jar or can.
(This will keep about 3 months.)

title: apricot bread pudding
directions: Soak apricots in milk for 15 minutes.

title: pot roast dinner for two
directions: Brown meat in hot oil.
Season with salt and pepper.
Add water and cover and simmer for one hour.
Add vegetables and simmer another hour.

title: chinese wiggle
directions: In large sauce pan, brown hamburg.
Slice onion very thin over hamburg.
Simmer covered for 5 minutes.
Place peas on top of hamburg.
Cook and drain noodles and place on top of hamburg/onion mixture then adding tomatoes.
Put butter pieces over tomatoes. Simmer again uncovered on very low heat for about 10 minutes. It's a good casserole.
Serves 6 people.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: All first 3 ingredients to stand in small bowl for 20 minutes.
In another bowl, mix all other ingredients.
Then stir in cooled oatmeal mixture.
Add nuts or fruit if you like at bake in a 9x9 inch pan for 35 minutes or until done.
Serves 6-9.

title: seafood casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, except cracker crumbs.
Blend well. Place in baking dish; sprinkle buttered cracker crumbs evenly over casserole.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.

title: zesty meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients except catsup, brown sugar and mustard. Put in 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Use remaining ingredients for topping.

title: texas hamburgers
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Shape into 8 patties.
Chill. Brown over charcoal fire or broil on rack in broiling pan.
Serves 4.

title: baked peaches
directions: Peel peaches and put in baking dish.
Add water, sugar, mace and lemon juice.
Dot with butter.
Sprinkle lemon rind on top. Add brandy.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, covered.
Serve hot or cold.
Good with vanilla ice cream.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Pat ground chuck in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish. Salt.
Add Cheddar cheese soup.
Top with Tater Tots.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: carrot cake 2
directions: Sift together the dry ingredients.
Mix eggs, oil, and sugar. Add dry ingredients a little at a time and beat well after each addition.
Fold in carrots, pineapple, and nuts.
Bake at 350 degrees in three 9 inch cake pans.

title: tagliarini
directions: Brown meat, pepper, onion and garlic in hot shortening or oil. Add tomato paste and other vegetables and let simmer about 30 minutes.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Mix the flour, eggs and milk.
Layer in a casserole in this order:
toppings, sauce, cheese.
Pour flour mixture over all. Bake at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: fruit jello
directions: Do not add water. Mix jello, cottage cheese and Cool Whip, then add fruit cocktail and banana. Mix well and chill.

title: fresh apple pie
directions: Peel, core and slice apples.
Place them on bottom of first crust.
Sprinkle with sugar, flour and lemon juice.
Sprinkle lightly with spices.
Dot with bits of butter.
Place second crust on the pie.
Put 3 to 4 slits in top of crust.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: crabmeat mornay
directions: Melt butter in heavy pot and saute onions and parsley.
Blend in flour, cream and cheese until cheese is melted.
Add other ingredients and gently fold in crabmeat.
This may be served in a chafing dish with Melba toast or in pastry shells.

title: pasta in a pot
directions: Boil macaroni; drain and set aside.
Brown ground beef, onions, garlic, salt and pepper.
Drain.
Add spaghetti sauce, tomatoes and mushrooms to beef.
In a deep casserole, layer half of macaroni, half of sauce mixture, half of sour cream and half of cheese.
Repeat layers.
Cover and bake for 45 minutes at 350° or until cheese is melted.

title: wake-up casserole
directions: Place hash brown patties in a single layer in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with cheese and ham. In a bowl, beat eggs, milk, salt and mustard.
Pour over ham.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Uncover; bake 15 minutes longer or until edges are golden brown and a knife inserted near the center comes out clean.

title: banana bread
directions: Follow cake directions except use only 1/3 cup water.
Add other ingredients.
Pour into a large loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: pepperoncini cream cheese dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in food processor.
Serve with crackers.
Good and zingy.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Add nuts and raisins; set aside.
Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs and beat.
Stir in bananas and then flour until smooth.
Bake in a loaf pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: lazy day lasagna
directions: Cook noodles in boiling water; drain.
Add oregano to sauce. In greased 10 x 6 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish, make layers in order: 1/2 each of the noodles, cottage cheese, Mozzarella cheese slices and spaghetti sauce.
Repeat.
Bake in oven at 375° for about 30 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Serves 4.

title: ballerina bubbles
directions: Mix gently and let stand of 1 hour before using.
(I sometimes add food coloring for fun.)

title: deep-dish pizza
directions: In a large bowl, mix Bisquick and water until soft dough forms.
Beat vigorously for 20 strokes.
Form dough into ball on floured board and knead 20 times.
Pat dough into bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan and up the sides to form an edge.
Cook and stir ground beef and onion until browned; drain.
Spread tomato sauce over dough.
Sprinkle with oregano.
Spoon ground beef over sauce. Add mushrooms and other toppings of your choice.
Top with cheese last.
Bake at 425° until crust is golden brown (approximately 20 minutes); keep a close eye on pizza after first 10 minutes of baking to avoid burning!
(Depending on toppings chosen and individual oven idiosyncrasies, you may find that a slightly lower baking temperature will work better for you.)
Makes 8 servings.

title: south carolina rice
directions: Brown onion and bell pepper in 1/2 stick margarine.
Mix all ingredients together and bake in casserole 1 hour at 350°.

title: christmas rice casserole
directions: Cook onion until soft in a large skillet over medium heat. Add all ingredients except rice.
Bring to a boil.
Place rice in a greased casserole.
Pour liquid mixture on top of rice and stir well.
Cover and bake in preheated 375° oven for 30 minutes. Serves 4.

title: sugarless cookies
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoons onto cookie sheet and bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Cut top off peppers, stem ends and remove seeds.
Leave whole and scald in boiling water for 3 minutes.
Cook hamburger and onion until done.
Drain and stir in salt, cooked rice, corn and tomato sauce.
Heat thoroughly.
Stuff the peppers and place in a baking pan or Pyrex with just enough water to cover bottom of the pan (about 2 tablespoons).
Bake 30 minutes at 350° or until peppers are tender.

title: enchiladas
directions: Mix 1 can cream of chicken soup, 1/2 can broth, onion and chilies; set aside.
Fry corn tortillas until soft or warm flour tortillas.
Put a pinch of cheese, chicken or turkey and 1 tablespoon sauce in center of tortilla and roll.
Place in greased baking dish.
Top with the remaining cream of chicken and broth. Then sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: quick clam chowder
directions: In large saucepan, mix potatoes slices, sauce mix, water and milk called for on package, clam liquor, green onion and green pepper.
Heat to boil, stirring occasionally.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 25 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Stir in clams, milk and butter.
Heat through.

title: fruit punch
directions: Dilute	frozen	juice as directed on can. Add pineapple juice and
mix.
At
serving
time, add ginger ale.
Yields 40 servings.

title: minestrone soup
directions: Cook hamburger, onion, and green pepper and drain.
Puree tomatoes in blender.
Add to hamburger mixture with water, carrots, tomato sauce, broth, parsley, basil, oregano, pepper and garlic salt.
Cover and simmer for about 20 minutes.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Make small round balls.
Cook in oven at 375°, 10 minutes each side.
Let cool and serve.

title: five star casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine beans, horseradish and seasonings. Pour into 10 x 6-inch baking dish.
Arrange sausages, cut side down over beans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly. Remove from oven.
Separate onion slices into rings.
Overlap rings down middle of dish.
Makes 6 servings.

title: ham-bean bake
directions: In mixing bowl, combine ham, pork and beans, molasses, catsup, instant minced onion, Worcestershire and mustard.
Spoon into six individual casseroles.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° until heated, 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: hershey cake
directions: Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: hornet's nest cake(low cholesterol recipe)
directions: Prepare vanilla pudding in saucepan with milk.
Cook over medium heat until thick.
Cool completely.
Mix prepared pudding, egg and cake mix together.
Batter will be thick.
Spread into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Do not grease or flour pan.
Sprinkle nuts and butterscotch morsels over top of batter.
Take a spoon and press slightly.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown together ground chuck and drain.
Add pizza sauce; beat together other ingredients until smooth.
Pour on top of meat in baking dish.
Cook at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: shrimp stuffing
directions: Cook celery, green pepper and onion in butter until tender. Prepare stuffing mix. Stir in vegetables, shrimp, mayo, parsley and cayenne.

title: quick maple syrup
directions: Melt sugar in hot water. Bring to boil and remove from heat. Stir in vanilla and maple flavoring.

title: fire roasted corn and poblano tacos
directions: Heat butter in a heavy saute pan or saucepan over medium-high heat.
Cook onion 1 minute, until slightly browned on edges.
Add garlic and saute 1 minute. until slightly browned on edges.
Add garlic and saute 1 minute more.
Add poblano, corn, salt and oregano; remove from heat and stir to combine.
Then add lime juice, Chihuahua cheese and parmesan.
Stir.
Brush a griddle, comal or heavy skillet with a light coating of oil.
Bring to medium-high heat.
Place a few tortillas on hot skillet; fill tortillas, reserving part of filling for garnish.
When tortillas are softened, fold over to make tacos.
Cook until golden brown on both sides.
Garnish with extra cheese and lime wedges as desired. Makes 12 tacos.

title: venison roast
directions: Place trimmed and boned roast inside roasting bag; add seasonings, potatoes, carrots and onion.
Add water per package directions, then add additional water.
(Venison has no marbled fat, so will cook drier.)
Seal roasting bag closed.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into
a greased 9 x 12-inch dish.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: blueberry jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 2 cups boiling water.
Drain blueberries and pineapple.
Save juices.
Combine the two juices and measure 1/2 cup to add to the jello mixture.
Refrigerate jello and let set partially, then add the drained blueberries and pineapple.
Let set until firm.
Then combine sour cream, cream cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Whip together.
Spread on top of jello.
Sprinkle with nuts, if desired.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Mix in order given.
Bake at 350° in greased pan.

title: greenbriar beef stroganoff
directions: Combine 1/2 cup flour, salt and paprika and dredge meat.
Melt 2 tablespoons of butter in a large, heavy skillet and brown meat quickly.
Add mushrooms, onion and garlic and cook until tender. Remove meat and mushrooms from skillet.
Add 2 tablespoons of butter and blend in 3 tablespoons of flour.
Stir in tomato paste. Slowly add bouillon and cook, stirring constantly until thickened.
Return meat and mushrooms to skillet.
Just before serving, stir in sour cream, lemon juice and sherry.
Heat; do not boil.
Serves 6.

title: quick chili beans
directions: Brown beef in skillet with onion; drain.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil and simmer 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift all-purpose flour.
Add baking soda and salt.
Stir in whole wheat flour and mix well. Fold in bananas, vanilla and walnuts.
Pour mixture into greased bread pan.
Bake in 350° preheated oven for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: sauteed fish fillets
directions: Dip fish in
milk,
then in wheat germ.
Saute shallots in oil and butter in
a
skillet
for
2 minutes, then add the fish. Cook briefly, 3 minutes on one side and 2 on the other. Do	not cook
until
the
fish
is dry and comes apart.
When serving, toss
minced
parsley over.
Add lemon wedges on the side.	Serves 4.

title: french silk pie
directions: In mixing bowl, cream the butter; gradually add sugar.
Cream until light and fluffy.
Blend in unsweetened chocolate and vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating 3 minutes after each addition (medium speed). Turn filling into chocolate wafer crust, graham cracker crust or regular crust.
Chill several hours.
Top with whipped cream.

title: chili beans
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Mix beans, meat, onion, garlic and chili powder.
Cook in crock-pot.
Simmer for about 30 minutes (low).

title: fruit nut balls
directions: Grind in food processor.
Mix well and roll in powdered sugar or chopped nuts.
Or mix with 1 tablespoon orange juice, or 1/4 cup honey, 3 tablespoons butter and 1/2 teaspoon vanilla (mixed and barely warmed).
Then roll in nuts.

title: sweeter muffin
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes. Can add cranberries, apples, oranges, nuts, etc.

title: timko's cream of po-cheesy soup
directions: Cook potatoes until tender in water, but do not overcook. Saute onions and celery in melted butter and margarine.
Add flour and chicken bouillon and stir to blend.
Add milk and stir until thick and smooth.
Add cooked potato cubes and their cooking liquid.
Add and stir in Cheddar cheese until it melts.
If desired, add ham.
Season with white pepper.

title: mrs. caldwell's cake
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together and place in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix the remaining ingredients and place on top of mixture.
Sprinkle nuts on top and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: gazpacho
directions: To save time, put all in a food processor and let it do the chopping.
May add an avocado (diced) before serving.
Cover and refrigerate at least 1 hour. Stir before serving and add chopped onions.

title: peanut butter bar cookies
directions: Mix all the ingredients together except the Hershey bars.
Put mix in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt chocolate and spread over mixture. Crucial:
You must refrigerate 45 minutes and then cut into bars.

title: italian beef
directions: Put beef in Dutch oven with all other ingredients.
Cover with tight lid.
Cook 4 to 5 hours in 350° oven.

title: coca-cola cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.

title: orange balls
directions: Mix all 4 ingredients together well in bowl.
Then spoon out and roll into balls.
Take coconut and put 1 cup of coconut in two small bowls.
Color with food coloring, if desired, and then roll ball in it.
Place on dish and keep chilled until you serve.

title: sausage gravy
directions: Cook crumbled sausage; drain on paper towels.
Stir in onion; cook until transparent.
Stir in flour and a little of the milk. Stir and cook over medium heat for 6 minutes.
Stir in the rest of the milk.
Add seasonings; cook until thickened.
Serve over fresh baked biscuits.
Enjoy.

title: southern baked squash(small yellow squash)
directions: In a large bowl, mix squash, 3/4 cup crumbs, 6 tablespoons oleo, onion, egg, salt and pepper.
Turn into a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Dot with remaining oleo and crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: macaroni and broccoli
directions: Cut and peel broccoli stems.
Cut 1-inch pieces.
Blanch a few minutes before flowerets.
If flowerets are large, cut smaller. Chop garlic.
Saute in oil until golden.
Cook pasta.
Drain and place in bowl.
Top with garlic, oil, basil leaves and cheese.
Add broccoli.
Mix well.
Use Ronzoni ziti or fettuccini.

title: peanut butter and jelly sandwiches
directions: Take your bread and spread your jelly on both pieces of bread. Then spread peanut butter on top of the jelly.
Smash the breads together and eat it!

title: japanese fruit cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs and beat.
Add baking powder and flour which has been sifted together.
Alternate with milk.
Add flavorings.
Mix well.
Bake one layer of this in greased and floured pan.
To rest of mixture, add fig preserves, cloves, allspice and cinnamon.
Bake this in two layers in greased and floured pan.
When done, let cool and put plain layer in middle.

title: sausage-egg casserole
directions: Brown sausage and set aside to drain.
Mix all ingredients except cheese.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Add cheese; cover with foil except for last 15 minutes.
Bake 1 hour at 350°. Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: chicken frecaissee
directions: Mix flour, salt and pepper. Coat chicken in flour mixture. Heat shortening in skillet; brown chicken. Put browned chicken in baking dish. Set aside.

title: sweet minglers recipe
directions: In large microwave bowl, melt chocolate on high for one minute.
Stir and heat another 30 seconds on high or until melted. Stir in peanut better.
Gently stir Crispix cereal into chocolate-peanut butter mixture until well coated.
Place powdered sugar in 2 gallon freezer storage bag, add coated cereal to sugar and close bag.
Gently toss cereal mixture until well coated. Store in air tight container in refrigerator.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Place on low heat until thickened.
Pour in vanilla flavoring, then pour in cool, baked pie crust.

title: barbecue black-eyes
directions: In a large skillet, cook bacon strips until crisp.
Remove from pan. Add onion, celery and carrot to drippings in pan and cook until tender, stirring frequently. Add beans, liquid, barbecue sauce and mustard.
Mix lightly.
Cook over low heat 15 minutes, adding more liquid if needed.
Stir in green pepper and barbecue chips.
Let simmer 5 minutes longer.
Serve topped with bacon.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs and remaining ingredients.
Drop by rounded spoonfuls on greased baking sheet. Bake for 10 to 12 minutes at 375°.
Fill with Cream Cheese Icing.

title: one bowl brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350° (325° for glass dish).
Microwave chocolate and butter on High for 2 minutes.
Stir until chocolate is melted completely.
Stir sugar into chocolate.
Blend well. Mix in eggs and vanilla.
Stir in flour and walnuts until well blended. Spread in greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out with fudge crumbs. Do not overbake.
Cool in pan.
Cut into squares.

title: cream cheese cupcakes
directions: Put vanilla wafers in 36 to 40 paper liners. Mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla. Spoon filling in paper lined muffin pans. Bake at 300° for 25 minutes.

title: monkey bread
directions: Combine cinnamon and 1/2 cup sugar.
Quarter each biscuit. Roll in sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Place in a tube or Bundt pan. Mix margarine, 1/2 cup sugar and vanilla.
Bring to a boil.
Pour over biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Turn over on a plate. Pick with fingers and enjoy, as soon as it is cool enough to eat.

title: celery seed dressing for fruit salad
directions: Measure dry ingredients into a small mixing bowl.
Mix sugar, salt and mustard and add onion juice and a small amount of vinegar. Add oil gradually, then remaining vinegar and celery seed.

title: pizza hot dish
directions: In a medium bowl, beat eggs.
Add milk and macaroni.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish.
Set aside.

title: homemade bread
directions: In mixing bowl, dissolve yeast in water; add remaining water, sugar, salt, shortening and several cups flour.
Beat with spoon until smooth and batter falls from spoon in sheets.
Mix in (by hand) enough flour until dough cleans the bowl.

title: apple coconut crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine vanilla wafers, coconut and cinnamon.
In a shallow, 1-quart casserole, layer apples and crumb mixture.
Alternate layers, ending with apples.

title: quick rolls
directions: Place water, yeast, sugar, oil and salt in a large bowl.
Add flour, a small amount at a time, until it makes a stiff dough that can be rolled out (may take more than 3 cups).

title: peanut butter icebox cookies
directions: Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Cream shortening until light.
Add sugar slowly, gradually beating after each addition. Add brown sugar and blend peanut butter in well.
Add well beaten eggs.
Add dry ingredients a little at a time beating until smooth after each addition.
Form into two rolls.
Wrap in wax paper.
Let stand in refrigerator several hours.
Slice thin and bake 8 to 10 minutes at 425°.
Makes 5 dozen cookies.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all
ingredients.
Roll into a ball and chill until serving.
Can roll into ball with chopped pecans, if desired.

title: dad's banana bread
directions: Add sugar and oil together and set aside for a few minutes. Add the eggs and bananas to the oil and sugar mixture.
In another bowl, sift together flour, baking soda and baking powder and salt. Add to the first mixture along with the milk and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add pecans and place in 2 loaf pans that have been greased and floured.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Center may look raw after 1 hour.
If so, bake an additional 10 minutes or until done.

title: mushrooms in sour cream
directions: Wash mushrooms and slice thin (both stems and caps).
Add onions, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Turn off heat. Tightly cover pan and let sit for a few minutes (until mushrooms become limp), stirring frequently to prevent burning.
Add butter.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Beat cream cheese and mayonnaise until fluffy.
Add pineapple, strawberries, and nuts.
Fold in marshmallows and cool whip.
Chill.

title: potato candy
directions: Have powdered sugar, butter and vanilla ready.
Boil potato with skin on.
Peel and mash while hot.
Add butter and vanilla while potato is still hot.
Continue adding sugar as long as mixture will absorb it.
Mixture becomes like pie dough.
Roll out with rolling pin on wax paper sprinkled with powdered sugar. Spread with peanut butter and roll up like jelly roll.
Slice off 1/2 inch slices.
Candy should be refrigerated if not used at one sitting.
At Christmas, red or green food coloring can be used.

title: baked clams diablo
directions: Chop clams, celery, onion and garlic in food processor or by hand, very finely.
Cut bacon in slivers, fry; remove bacon and set aside.
Saute clam mixture in bacon drippings; add clam broth, seasonings and bread crumbs.
Stir over low heat until mixture reaches consistency of moist stuffing.
Spoon into clam shells. Top with bacon bits and brown under broiler.
Serve with Tabasco sauce.

title: low-fat tartar sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: low-fat, low-cholesterol breakfast casserole
directions: Cut whole wheat bread into cubes, place in large shallow pan and bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes or until toasted, stirring once.
Spray a 12 x 8-inch baking dish and dump half of the cubes therein.

title: cocoa nog
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Makes 4 cups mix.

title: pineapple-banana upside-down cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs and mix well. Sift flour, baking powder and salt. Add gradually with milk to butter mixture. Fold in mashed banana.
Melt 1/3 cup butter; sprinkle brown sugar on bottom of cake pan.
Carefully put pineapple and nuts on top. Pour batter over nuts. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: holiday broccoli soup
directions: Saute onions in butter until tender, but not browned.
Add vegetables with sauce, chicken broth, cream and pepper.
Cook over medium heat until thoroughly heated, about 5 minutes.
Makes 5 1/2 cups or 6 servings.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in 9 x 13 pan.
Mix flour, sugar, and powder.
Stir in milk.
Pour over margarine.
Spoon in peaches and juice.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: cheesy salmon patties
directions: Flake salmon with a fork.
Add milk, flour, egg and cheese, stirring well.
Shape mixture into 6 patties.
Heat oil in heavy skillet.
Cook patties in oil over medium heat for 8 minutes or until golden brown, turning once.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Sift the dry ingredients; cut in shortening.
Add grated cheese.
Add milk, enough to make a soft dough.
Put on a floured board and knead 1/2 minute.
Roll 1/2-inch thick and cut with biscuit cutter.
Bake in hot oven (450°) for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: a.m. raisin muffins
directions: Beat sugar and butter until fluffy.
Beat in egg, juice and peel, then combine with remaining ingredients.
Spoon batter into 6 large (2/3 cup size) muffin cups.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: pasta salad
directions: Prepare pasta.
Toss hot pasta with Italian dressing.
Let stand.
Prepare vegetables and pepperoni.
Combine mayonnaise, mustard and dill weed.
Set aside.
Combine pasta and vegetables. Add salt and pepper.
Add mayonnaise mixture.
Gently toss.
Add more mayonnaise if necessary.
Refrigerate 4 hours before serving. Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: fried quail
directions: Dress and split quail down the back, leaving breast together. Flatten out each bird with breast down and dust with salt and pepper on each side.
Roll in flour.
Place birds in skillet containing hot grease that will come halfway up on the birds. Brown well on all sides and then cover and turn down heat to simmer.
Simmer 30 to 40 minutes until tender.
The residue left in skillet may be used to make a cream gravy.

title: pecan puffs
directions: Beat butter until soft.
Blend in sugar until creamy.
Roll the dough into small balls.
Place them on a greased baking sheet. Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.
When cooled, roll the puffs in confectioners sugar.

title: methodist mint julep
directions: Place sugar and water in a saucepan and boil for 10 minutes. Squeeze juice from lemons and oranges.
Place juices, grated rind and mint in a juice container and add boiled sugar/water mixture. Refrigerate at least 24 hours.
Mix approximately 1 1/2 parts water to 1 part syrup.
Pour over ice in glasses.
Mixture may be kept up to 2 weeks in the refrigerator or may be frozen for later use.

title: barbecue ribs
directions: Cover ribs with water.
Add salt and peppers.
Boil until tender.
Remove ribs and drain.
Place in baking dish and add barbecue sauce.
Marinate in sauce several hours.
Grill over charcoal fire until slightly charred.

title: shoe peg corn casserole
directions: Place milk in an 8 x 8-inch Pyrex dish.
Add all other ingredients.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese. Sprinkle paprika on top.
Bake at 375° until bubbly.

title: tuna fish delight
directions: Place in ungreased baking dish in layers of tuna, sliced eggs and crushed potato chips.
Blend soup with milk, making a smooth sauce.
Pour this sauce over other ingredients.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: "cream" of broccoli soup
directions: In a large saucepan or Dutch oven, saute onion and garlic in vegetable oil until onion is clear but not browned.
Add the broth and bring to a boil.
Add the broccoli.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer until
broccoli is tender (about 10 minutes).
Remove from heat; add milk and seasoning.
Puree in blender.
Reheat in pan prior to serving.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: popcorn cake
directions: Melt margarine, marshmallows and oil in
pan over low heat, then cook for 1 minute.
Add mixture to popcorn, peanuts and M&M's.
Grease hands with butter; mix all ingredients together and put in greased tube pan.
Pack this fairly firm in pan and let stand for about 5 minutes.
Invert onto plate.
Ready to eat!

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, cornstarch and salt.
Stir in water.
Cook until thick.
Add margarine and cook until boiling.
Then blend in vanilla.
Can be made in microwave or conventional stove top. Makes 1 cup sauce.

title: potato salad dressing
directions: Dice potatoes.
Chop celery and onions.
Shred carrots.
Boil sugar and vinegar until sugar is dissolved.
Pour over ingredients and stir.
Let stand for a few minutes.

title: almond butter crunch
directions: In a large sauce pan, melt butter; add sugar, corn syrup and water. Cook; stirring occasionally, to hard-crack stage (300 degrees). Quickly stir coarsely chopped nuts; spread in ungreased 13x9 inch pan. Cool thoroughly. Turn out on waxed paper; spread top with half the chocolate; sprinkle with half the finely chopped almonds. Cover with waxed paper, invert. Spread with chocolate; sprinkle with remaining nuts. If necessary, chill to firm, crack in pieces.

title: cream cheese fruit dip
directions: Combine and blend to smooth consistency.
Serve with fresh fruit, especially strawberries.
For use as a frosting, cut liquid to a few tablespoons.
For diabetics, use sugar-free lemonade mix to sweeten.

title: celery seed dressing
directions: Blend first 5 ingredients until onion is finally chopped.
Add oil and celery seed.
Blend few seconds more.
Great with fruit. Try with bibb lettuce, mandarin oranges, almonds, avocado, etc.

title: sausage - sweet and saucy
directions: Heat equal parts of currant jelly and catsup in saucepan until mixture can be blended smooth.
Add bite-size pieces of Hillshire Farm sausage, and heat until sausage is hot.
Serve with toothpicks.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour and salt; gradually add milk.
Cook and stir until mixture thickens. Cook 2 minutes longer.
Remove from heat.
Stir small amount hot mixture into beaten egg yolks, return to hot mixture.
Cook 2 more minutes, stirring constantly. Remove from heat, add butter, vanilla and coconut.
Cool and pour into a 9-inch baked pastry shell.
Add meringue and sprinkle with coconut.
Brown in hot oven (350°).

title: poor man's supper
directions: In a skillet, cook onion until translucent.
Add crushed garlic and tomatoes.
Slice the baloney in thin slices and add to skillet.
Simmer about 20 minutes.
Add cornstarch and water mixture. Stir until thickened (about 5 minutes).
Serve with salad and crusty bread.

title: vidalia onion pie
directions: Press mixture of cracker crumbs and butter into 8-inch pie plate to form crust.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.
Saute onions in oil in skillet until tender.
Spread in pie shell.
Combine eggs, milk, salt and pepper in bowl; mix well.
Spoon over onions; top with cheese.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: creamy parmesan pizza
directions: In a small saucepan, cook onion and garlic in hot margarine until onion is tender.
Stir in the flour and pepper.

title: taco pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Brown meat and drain.
Cook onion until tender.
Combine meat, onion, taco mix, salsa and tomato sauce.
Add water.
Add garlic, salt and oregano to taste.
Mix well.
Place ingredients in 1 pie shell and top with half of the cheese.
Place the second crust on top and seal.
Bake until pie shell is brown.
Remove from oven and place remaining cheese on top of pie while it is hot.

title: hominy and black-eyed pea salad
directions: Combine all ingredients. Chill. Serve cold.

title: rohm soup(potato)
directions: Chop potatoes and celery; cut sausage in bite-sized pieces. Cover with water.
Add salt and pepper and cook until potatoes are tender.
Add milk and butter.
Heat until milk is hot and butter is melted.
Do not boil.
Maybe blended in blender for creamy soup.

title: romaine and almond salad
directions: Wash lettuce and tear into bite size pieces.
Slice onions thin, including green tops.
Toast almonds and sesame seed in toaster oven at low temperature until brown (watch carefully, they burn quickly).
Prepare dressing according to directions on the package.

title: bible cake
directions: Mix in order given.
Bake at 325° for about 1 1/2 hours.
This is something different to serve, then let everyone look up in the Bible to find what they have eaten.
Good to use for a church group or meeting.

title: freezer pickles
directions: Mix salt, celery seed and vinegar.
Pour over cucumbers, onions, green peppers and cauliflower.
Let stand overnight. Makes 4 pints. Freeze the next day.

title: potatoes au gratin
directions: In a small pan, melt butter slowly. Add onions and cook until soft. Add milk, soup and salt. Add to potatoes and pimento in a greased casserole pan. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: lo-cal veggie dip
directions: In blender, cream cottage cheese until smooth.
Add the other ingredients until mixed thoroughly.
Chill and serve with favorite raw veggies.

title: rice pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 300 degrees.

title: crawfish corn bisque
directions: Cook crawfish in water for 15 minutes over very low heat. Drain and reserve liquid.
Chop tails into coarse pieces.
Saute onions in margarine.
Process corn in blender to break kernels.

title: stuffed dates
directions: Split
dates
down
the
middle,
but
not
all
the way through.
Insert 1/2 of a pecan.
Roll pie crust dough out very thin; cut in triangles.
Roll dough around date and seal edges. Brush with	butter;
bake
in
a 350° oven until dough is light brown.
Remove
from
oven and roll in 10x sugar.
Very simple, delicious and easy to fix for any party.

title: famous christmas ham(great anytime)
directions: For slow even cooking, prepare grill by placing charcoals along 2 sides, leaving the center open.

Trim all excess fat from ham; place ham on grill and cook covered for 1 hour. Mix equal portions of prepared mustard, currant jelly and brown sugar in a saucepan over medium heat; stir until becomes a clear liquid. Baste ham every 15 minutes for the last 1 to 1 1/2 hours, depending on size of the ham.

title: pretzel salad
directions: In bottom of 9 x 13-inch dish, put the broken pretzels, then pour margarine over pretzels.
Heat 10 minutes in 350° oven. Remove and let set.
Chill.
Mix cream cheese softened with sugar and Cool Whip; spread over pretzels.
Set aside to chill.

title: diablos con queso
directions: Slice jalapenos in half lengthwise.
Remove seeds and membrane.
Fill jalapeno halves with softened cream cheese.

title: ham and potato scallop
directions: Combine ham, onions and green pepper to soup and milk mixture. Place potatoes into greased 2-quart casserole dish and dot top with butter.
Top with soup mixture and bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
Cover and bake for 45 minutes longer, until potatoes are done.

title: pecan logs
directions: Combine marshmallow cream, sugar and flavoring.
Shape into finger sized rolls.
Place on a wax paper lined cookie sheet and freeze until very hard.
Add caramel to unwhipped whipping cream in a double boiler.
Dip the rolls in the melted caramel and roll them in chopped pecans.
Store covered in a dry place.
Yield:
30 logs.

title: sweet potato biscuits
directions: Cook sweet potatoes and mash.
Mix yeast and warm water.
Stand for 5 minutes. Mix flour, baking powder and salt in large bowl. Add yeast mixture and stir.
On ungreased pan, turn dough out and knead for 5 minutes.
Place dough on greased sheet.
Let stand for 8 hours or overnight.
Roll dough 1/2 inch.
Cut dough with 2-inch biscuit cutter.
Place dough on ungreased sheet and allow to rise for 25 minutes.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Yields about 7 dozen.

title: chicken divan
directions: Melt margarine.
Blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Add chicken broth and bring to a boil over medium heat.
Stir in half and half and wine.
Remove from heat.

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Cream together first 3 ingredients and add lemon and vanilla flavoring.
Add oil for moisture.
Add eggs 1 at a time, beating well after each one.
Add flour alternately with whipping cream. Use milk.
Grease and flour pan, then line bottom of tube pan with waxed paper.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: black walnut ice cream
directions: Scald the milk; mix eggs, sugar, salt and flour.
Beat well and cook over medium heat until mixture thickens.
(I cook in the microwave, cooking on Medium, setting the timer at 3 minute intervals, stirring well after each 3 minutes.
It takes about 9 to 12 minutes this way.)
Chill the custard as well as the canned milk.
When ready to freeze, add the chilled canned milk and the flavoring to the custard.
Freeze until almost firm and add the cooled black walnuts.
Continue to freeze until firm.

title: crayfish etouffee
directions: Add crayfish tails to mixture and saute 1 minute.
Then add flour.
Mix well and add chicken broth and cayenne pepper.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Serve over hot rice.

title: depression cookies
directions: Mix all together and roll into little balls.
Press down with a fork and put a nut on each one.
Bake at 350° until lightly brown.

title: crustless asparagus quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In small skillet heat 1 teaspoon margarine until bubbly and hot.
Add scallions and saute until softened.
In medium bowl combine sauteed scallions with asparagus, milk, eggs, 1 ounce cheese and seasonings.
Grease 7-inch pie plate with remaining 1 teaspoon margarine and pour in egg mixture.
Sprinkle with remaining 1 ounce of cheese and bake for 35 minutes.
Test for doneness; insert knife in center, comes out clean.
Makes 2 servings.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix flour and sugar; add margarine, beaten eggs, buttermilk and vanilla.
Beat well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake in moderate oven at 375° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into greased casserole.
Top with crushed corn flake crumbs; pour 3 tablespoons melted butter over them.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: rice and broccoli
directions: Melt Cheez Whiz in margarine; add milk and soup.
Stir until smooth.
Pour over rice and broccoli.
Mix and place in ovenproof casserole.
Top with bread crumbs and bake for 45 minutes at 350° in oven.

title: lobster cheesy macaroni
directions: Cook macaroni in boiling salted water 8 to 10 minutes. Combine Cheddar, 1/2 pound Parmesan, Gruyre and cream cheeses in double boiler; heat until creamy and blended. Slowly add cream and stir until smooth. In large saut pan, heat olive oil; add shallots and garlic and saut. Add lobster meat and cook until opaque; set aside. Drain pasta and add to lobster; add cheese sauce, peppers, cilantro and salt and pepper and mix well. Divide mixture among 12 (12-ounce) ramekins or turn into large casserole. Sprinkle with remaining Parmesan and breadcrumbs. Bake at 350° for 7 minutes or until crumbs are golden brown.
Yield: 12 servings.

title: jackie's easy coffeecake
directions: Grease Bundt or angel food pan; put pecans in pan.
Add roll pieces.

title: swiss cheese salad(meatless)
directions: Chop eggs.
Mix cheese and eggs in a bowl.
Combine sour cream, mustard, horseradish, salt, pepper and cumin.
Fold in cheese and egg mixture.
Refrigerate 1 hour.
Serve on a bed of lettuce.
Serves 4.

title: deviled steak strips
directions: Cut meat into 2 inch thin strips.
Coat with flour.
Brown meat, onion and garlic in shortening.
Stir in 1 cup water, tomato sauce, vinegar, horseradish, mustard, salt and pepper.
Simmer 1 hour.
Stir in 1/2 cup water; heat through.
Serve with rice or noodles.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute celery and onion, then add frozen broccoli and steam for 10 minutes.
Then add Cheez Whiz, rice, milk, chicken soup and water.
Bring ingredients to a boil.
Pour into a casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: chili
directions: Melt fat.
Add onions, pepper, celery and garlic.
Cook until partly tender.
Add beef and cook until light brown.
Add tomatoes, chili powder and 2 tablespoons water.
Add salt and sugar.
Bring to boil, then reduce to low heat and simmer for 1 hour.
Add beans and heat well.

title: professor's squash casserole
directions: Cut squash and cook until tender.
Drain thoroughly.
Add remaining ingredients.
Sprinkle a few seasoned crumbs over the top and bake in a 350° oven until bubbly.
Serves 6.

title: baked apples!
directions: Core apples without cutting through bottom end.
Place in baking pan.
Mix sugar and cinnamon; fill centers of apples.
Put margarine on top of filling.
Makes 4 servings.
A healthy, light dessert.

title: jamie's marzetti
directions: Chop onions and brown with hamburg; drain.
Cook noodles for 5 minutes; drain.
Mix hamburg, noodles, soup and cheese in a large bowl.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour tomato juice over mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, then turn oven to 300° for 30 minutes more.
Stir and serve.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Mix 1/2 pound of cheese and butter with cracker crumbs.
Line casserole, reserving some for top.
Stir liquid from asparagus into mushroom soup.
Put a layer of asparagus, sprinkling of nuts and cheese and cover with soup mixture.
Repeat until casserole is filled.
Top with remaining cheese and cracker mixture.
Decorate with almonds and bake in a 350° oven for 20 minutes.
Serves 10. Can be made the day before.

title: italian spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown ground beef, onion, mushrooms, Italian sausage and green pepper.
Drain fat.
Add tomato paste and Italian seasoning; stir until mixed well.
In large pot or crock-pot, add tomato sauce, crushed tomatoes, meat mixture and seasoning to taste.
Cook slow for 3 to 6 hours.

title: peanut butter cornflakes
directions: Combine sugar and syrup.
Let it come to a fast boil; quickly add peanut butter, then take off and let peanut butter melt.
When melted, add cornflakes.
Mix well.
Drop onto a pan to cool.

title: cranberry-orange relish
directions: In a 6 to 8-quart kettle or Dutch oven, mix cranberries, sugar, water, orange peel and orange juice; bring to a boil. Cook, uncovered, until cranberry skins pop; about 5 minutes, stirring once or twice.
Stir in almonds if desired.
Remove from heat.
Ladle hot relish into hot sterilized half pint jars, leaving 1/2-inch head space.
Adjust lids; process in boiling bath 5 minutes (start timing when water returns to boiling).
Makes about 8 half pints.

title: pumpkin coconut muffins
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in large mixer bowl.
Beat at medium speed until well blended.
Combine flour and next ingredients in medium bowl.
Add to the sugar mixture alternately with pumpkin.
Mix after each addition.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into greased muffin pans.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes.
Makes 15 to 18 muffins.

title: cooked icing
directions: Mix thoroughly the milk and flour.
Cook over medium heat until thick; let cool.
Combine the rest of the ingredients together with the cooled mixture and beat well.

title: chocolate nut squares
directions: Melt oleo.
Add cocoa and sugar.
Add other ingredients.
Bake in square oiled pan in moderate oven for 30 minutes.
Cut into squares when cool.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown and drain sausage.
Add sausage and all remaining ingredients to a baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Reduce heat to 325° if using a glass dish.
This casserole is delicious without the bell pepper and onion.

title: mini pizza
directions: Fry meat and drain grease.
Chop cheese into meat mixture and melt.
Add other ingredients; mix well.
Spread on thin bread cut into 1/4-inch pieces.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and broil 4 or 5 minutes or until cheese is melted just before serving.
Can freeze after spreading on bread.

title: never fail dumplings
directions: Mix all ingredients and roll out thin.
Let dry about 20 minutes.
Cut into strips and drop into chicken broth and cook. When done, cut up one hard-boiled egg into dumplings.

title: noodle casserole(good side dish with a roast or ham)
directions: Spinach, chicken or mushrooms can be substituted for some or all of the vegetables and meat in this recipe.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Rinse mushrooms, remove stems and chop stems into fine pieces. Leave mushrooms caps full; saute lightly in butter.
Remove from pan.
Saute chopped stems for about 10 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cool.
Fill mushroom caps with mixture; press lightly into the hollows.
Broil until hot and lightly browned (3 to 5 minutes).

title: shrimp moqueca
directions: Cook onion and garlic in oil until translucent.
Add tomatoes, coriander, hot pepper sauce and shrimp.
Simmer ingredients until shrimp turns pink.
Pour in coconut milk.
Serve with rice.

title: hopping john
directions: Fry sausage and drain.
Add remaining ingredients and cook until rice is tender.

title: banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour loaf pan.
Beat eggs, sugar and oil.
Stir in bananas.
Sift dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture.
Fold in nuts and vanilla.
Bake for 1 hour or until golden brown at 350°.

title: veggie-meat cups
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine first 7 ingredients in medium bowl and mix well.
Divide meat mixture into 6 equal pieces and place each into a greased 6 ounce glass custard cup.
Pat meat mixture against bottom and sides of cup.
Place custard cups on a pan.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes.
Pour off drippings.

title: hello dollies
directions: Pour 1 can of Eagle milk over mixture.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: caramel dumplings
directions: Burn 1 cup sugar.
Add hot water, 1/2 cup sugar, vanilla and butter.
Boil ingredients until all sugar has melted.

title: no nothing pie
directions: Take biscuits and cut in half.
Put them in a large pan and add cup of sugar, then a cup of milk and cut butter into small quarters and arrange over the top.
Dash nutmeg over the top. Bake in moderate oven (325°) for 15 minutes.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Put crackers in plastic bag.
Close bag; crush crackers with rolling pin.
In casserole dish, beat egg with fork.
Stir in milk, onion, salt and pepper.
Measure 2/3 cup cracker crumbs; add to milk mixture.
Add corn and stir.
Put rest of crumbs into small bowl.
Put butter into skillet on low heat.
Heat until butter melts.
Pour over crumbs in bowl.
Stir to mix.
Sprinkle crumbs over corn mixture.
Put in 350° oven for 1 hour or until knife inserted comes out clean.
Makes 6 servings.

title: homemade potato soup
directions: Dice potatoes.
Put first 6 ingredients in large pot and cook on low until potatoes are tender.
Remove from heat and mash part of the potatoes until soup starts to get thick.
Combine celery soup and milk; mix well.
Add slowly to potato mixture. Return to heat and cook on low until bubbly.
Remove and serve with cheese on top.

title: "brunch" sausage casserole
directions: Brown and drain sausage.
Cube bread and Velveeta and arrange in 8 x 12-inch pan.
Add drained sausage.
Beat eggs; add milk and mustard and mix well.
Pour over bread mixture.
Cover with foil and refrigerate overnight.

title: beer bread
directions: Mix altogether.
Bake for 55 minutes in a 300° oven.

title: coffee for 50 persons(ladies aid cookbook methodist church, 1926)
directions: Beat egg and add enough water to moisten coffee; mix well. Place in 4 cloth bags and tie at top.
Let soak in water 3 or 4 hours, then bring to a boil. Remove bags.

title: black forrest cake
directions: Cream oleo and flour; add nuts.
Pat into 9 x 12-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Let cool.
Mix cream cheese, 1 cup Cool Whip and powdered sugar; spread over crust.
Mix puddings and milk; spread over cream cheese.
Top with remaining Cool Whip. Refrigerate.

title: caramel icing
directions: Cook first 2 ingredients for 3 minutes; add milk and cook 5 minutes more.
Add powdered sugar until it gets as thick as you want it.

title: chicken breasts and wild rice
directions: Cook wild rice in boiling water until kernels open (30 to 40 minutes).
Drain.
Spread rice in buttered 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Combine soup, sour cream, undrained mushrooms and sherry. Pour 1/2 of this mixture over rice.
Skin chicken breasts; arrange over soup.
Spread remaining soup mixture on top of chicken. Sprinkle cheese over all.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes, covered. Then uncover and bake 30 minutes longer.

title: blueberry disaster(boy scout recipe)
directions: Put the can of pie filling in bottom of casserole dish. Cut oleo into dry yellow
cake	mix.
Put
the	cake
and oleo mixture on top of the
blueberry
pie
mix.
Cook in 450° oven for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: crab puffs
directions: This delicious cheese roll goes well with a bean salad or thick soup.
Any leftover slices can be included in a lunch box.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine sugar and milk in saucepan.
Boil until mixture forms a soft ball.
Remove from heat and stir in marshmallow cream, peanut butter and vanilla.
Beat until blended.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: karo pie
directions: Beat eggs until fluffy.
Add sugar and syrup.
Mix well with mixer.
Add melted butter and vanilla.
Mix well and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 or 40 minutes or until filling sets and top is crisp.

title: pecan cheese dip
directions: Melt Velveeta in double boiler. Add cream cheese, pecans and garlic. Chill. Serve with crackers.

title: no peek stew
directions: Put beef in large bowl.
Add soups as is (do not dilute). Season.
Mix well with hands.
Add water (or wine) and mix again. Put in closely covered casserole.
Bake for 3 hours at 300°.

title: chess pie
directions: Mix together the egg yolks (save the whites), sugar and butter or margarine.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then bake at 300° to 350° until done.

title: herbed chicken soup
directions: In a 4-quart pan, place all ingredients except noodles. Cover and bring to boil; skim fat off. Reduce heat, cover and simmer 1 1/2 hours. Remove chicken and cool, then debone. Skim fat again then return chopped chicken to boiling broth. Add noodles and heat. Remove bay leaf. Serves 16.

title: glazed fresh apple cake
directions: Combine sugar and oil.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add to egg mixture.
Add vanilla.
Sprinkle apples with lemon juice and fold into batter with nuts.
Pour into greased and floured tube or Bundt pan.
Bake at 325° for 75 minutes.
Cool 15 minutes and top with Caramel Glaze.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Combine sugar, flour and salt in saucepan; blend in water. Add chocolate.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture boils.
Remove from heat.
Blend in butter and vanilla extract.
Serve hot.

title: pie crust
directions: Blend and refrigerate.
One cup for 1 crust.
Moisten enough to hold together and roll.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Melt margarine and blend in flour and salt.
Add wine.
Drain mushroom liquid and add enough milk to make 2 cups.
Gradually stir into margarine mixture.
Place over medium heat, stir and cook until sauce thickens.
If using fresh mushrooms, slice and saute in a little margarine.

title: mexican dip
directions: On a regular plate spread dip.
Mix taco seasoning with sour cream and spread over top.
Sprinkle with grated cheese, green onions and tomatoes.
Serve with taco chips.

title: ravioli salad
directions: Fry bacon, blot on paper toweling; crumble.
Pour off all but two tablespoons of bacon fat.
Saute onions, celery and green pepper lightly in fat.
Add vinegar and sugar; stir.
Add mini ravioli and bacon.
Cover; heat gently for 10 minutes.
Garnish with sliced green pepper, if desired.
Serves four to six.

title: don pablo-like queso dip
directions: Saute onion in butter. Add tomatoes with chilies and stewed tomatoes. Cook until thick. Add cheese. Cook until thick and smooth, stirring often to keep from sticking. Refrigerate overnight. Heat to eat. Serve with chips of your choice.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Mix pudding and pie mix with milk in a bowl with a wire whisk for 2 minutes. Whisk in coconut extract for 1 minute, then stir in flaked coconut and mix well. Pour mixture into cooled pie crust and refrigerate for 5 minutes. Toast 1 tablespoon of coconut for garnish. Stir whipped topping and then spread on top of pie and garnish with toasted coconut. Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Cook all
(on
burner on top of stove), except oatmeal, which should
be
added last half hour.
Amounts of vegetables and water
are
approximate.
Use
your imagination.
Use any leftover vegetables, water from cooking vegetables and seasoning you prefer.
Soup
may
be
prepared in quantity and used several days.
It is actually better when it has blended.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Add syrup, sugar, juice and rind.
Stir in butter.
Spread pecans over unbaked pie crust and pour filling over.
Bake approximately 45 minutes at 350°.
Serve topped with whipped cream, if desired.
Yields one 8 or 9-inch pie.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Grate cheese and mix with cracker crumbs.
Add liquid of asparagus to mushroom soup and set aside.
Put layer of cheese and crackers in bottom of buttered casserole, layer of asparagus, layer of sliced, hard-boiled eggs and a layer of water chestnuts. Repeat until all ingredients have been used.
Sprinkle over top English peas.
Use melted oleo on each layer and on top.
Put rest of cheese and crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Grease a large casserole dish and set aside.
Brown and drain sausage; refrigerate.
Line casserole with bread cubes, cover with cheese.
In a separate bowl, beat eggs, add 2 cups milk and the dry mustard.
Mix well, then pour over the cheese and bread. Refrigerate overnight.

title: ines' peanut butter blossoms
directions: Mix first 9 ingredients together.
Roll into balls and then roll into granulated sugar to coat.
Bake in a 375° oven for 8 minutes.
Take out of oven, put "kiss" on top and press.
Okay if it cracks.

title: blackberry cobbler
directions: Cook the berries and 1 cup sugar until juicy. Set aside.

title: blueberry feather muffins
directions: Cream 1/3 cup sugar and 1/4 cup butter in bowl.
Add egg; beat well.
Combine 2 1/3 cups flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with milk, mixing well after each addition.
Stir in vanilla; beat well.
Fold in blueberries.
Fill greased muffin cups 2/3 full.

title: chicken and yellow rice
directions: Brown onion in olive oil, then add garlic.
Add chicken; brown slightly.
Add the chicken broth to cover chicken.
Add chopped tomato, chopped green pepper, chopped red pepper, oregano, salt and pepper.
Cover; let simmer until chicken falls off the bone.

title: squirrel mulligan
directions: Cook squirrels, salt, pepper and bouillon cubes in pressure cooker until tender, about 30 minutes.
Cool and remove meat from bones.
Add onion, celery and green peppers to squirrel broth. Cook until tender.
Add rice, potatoes, tomatoes, corn, red pepper and sugar.
Simmer on low heat until thickened.
Add squirrel and stir.
Serve warm.

title: aunt garnett's pear honey
directions: Put
pears and oranges through food chopper.
Add sugar and cook until tender, stirring constantly.
Add pineapple and cook until
it looks like marmalade.
Add coconut; boil again. Stir very
often to prevent scorching.
Seal while hot.	Makes 12 pints.

title: apple bread(makes 1 large loaf)
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, milk, vinegar, vanilla and apple slices.
Add flour, soda and salt; mix well.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Sprinkle top with 1/4 teaspoon cinnamon and 1 tablespoon sugar mixed.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: mum's bumstead sandwiches
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Stuff 4 halves of the pita bread with the mixture and cover each one with foil.
Put in 225° oven for about 1/2 hour.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: On top of stove, melt margarine and broccoli. Break up broccoli and add remaining ingredients, stirring. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, uncovered.

title: baked beans with meat
directions: Brown ground beef with chopped onion, garlic, celery seed and chili powder. Simmer until ground beef is lightly brown. Add beans, vinegar, brown sugar and mustard to meat mixture. Bake at 325° until it starts to bubble around edges.

title: barbecue beef sandwich
directions: In blender, combine all ingredients.
Pour into electric skillet and simmer for 1 hour.
Add corned beef; warm through and serve on buns.

title: mounds candy
directions: Combine milk and butter.
Add sugar and coconut.
Mix well. Let chill for 2 hours.
Roll into balls and flatten.
Place on wax paper; chill for 2 hours.
In double boiler, melt chocolate morsels and chopped paraffin wax on low heat.
Dip balls and dry on wax paper.
After dry, keep candy chilled.

title: cooked play dough
directions: Combine all ingredients in a saucepan.
Cook over medium heat. Stir constantly until mixture forms a ball.
Knead until smooth. Store in covered container.

title: cheesecake
directions: Soften cream cheese to room temperature.
Mix cream cheese and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla and lemon juice. Mix well with mixer.
Pour into graham cracker crust on spring-form pan.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: fresh apple pie
directions: Peel and slice apples thin.
Arrange in bottom of deep-dish pie crust.
Mix dry ingredients and spread dry mixture over top of apples.
Cut butter in small pieces and place over pie filling. Put top crust on pie and pierce with fork so steam can escape. Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Then reduce heat to 350° and bake until golden brown and apples are tender.

title: quick italian bread
directions: Heat broiler.
Mix margarine, seasonings and garlic until well blended.
Place each bread half, cut side facing up, on cookie sheet.
Spread with margarine mixture.
Top with cheese, tomatoes and pepperoni.

title: chocolate mousse
directions: Separate eggs.
Beat egg whites and heavy cream separately. Melt chocolate in microwave.
Beat egg yolks with 2 tablespoons of water.
Slowly add sugar and beat until creamy.
Add melted chocolate and immediately fold in cream, then the stiff egg whites.
Place in refrigerator.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: biscuits
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt together in a mixing bowl. In a measuring cup, pour oil or melted shortening and milk without stirring.
Add all at once to the flour mixture and stir quickly with fork until dough clings together.
Knead dough lightly 10 times.
Place on waxed paper and pat out until 1/2 inch thick. Cut with biscuit cutter and place on an ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 475° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: banana pudding pie(for dieters)
directions: Slice bananas and completely line 'Nilla crust.
Make pudding as directed and pour on top of bananas.
Top with Cool Whip. Chill for approximately 30 minutes.

title: cabbage stew
directions: Brown chuck and then add other ingredients listed.
Can mix and store in refrigerator or let simmer one hour and serve.

title: simple banana ice cream
directions: Blend
together
to desired consistency.
Serve soft or freeze for firmer ice cream.

title: fruit tart with citrus glaze(serves 8)
directions: Stir together flour, cornstarch and sugar in medium size bowl. With pastry blender or 2 knives, cut in margarine until mixture is well blended and coarse crumbs form.
With fork, stir in egg. Press dough firmly into ball with hands.
(If mixture seems crumbly, work with hands until it holds together.)
Flatten dough slightly; roll out on large cookie sheet to 10 1/2-inch circle.

title: german potato salad(serves  8 to 10)
directions: Boil potatoes (skins on) in a 4-quart pan or Dutch oven. Drain, cube and season with salt and pepper (to taste) while still hot.
Set aside in colander.
Dice and cook bacon in the pan. Remove bacon.
Reserve 1/2 cup bacon fat and drain rest from the pan.
Dice and saute onion in the bacon fat.
Blend in cornstarch. Add vinegar, water and sugar.
Cover and cook until thick and glossy.
Stir in bacon, paprika and potatoes.
Garnish with sliced eggs.
Sprinkle generously with celery salt.
Serve warm.
Great potluck dish or complement to baked ham or sausage.

title: honey oatmeal bread(low in fat)
directions: I sometimes add 2 to 3 tablespoons wheat germ.

title: sweet pickles
directions: Put lime over cucumbers and cover with water (do not use an aluminum pan).
Soak overnight.
Next day, rinse and soak in clear water.
Change water 4 times.
Boil vinegar, sugar and spices (in cheesecloth or tea ball) until sugar is dissolved, then cut off. Drain cucumbers and add to vinegar mixture.
Soak overnight.
Next day, bring to a boil and pack in sterilized jars.

title: easy chicken wings
directions: Marinate chicken wings with ingredients for at least 1 hour. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Blend dry ingredients in bowl until well mixed.
Combine oil, eggs, water and pumpkin and beat until well blended.
Add dry ingredients slowly and beat well.
Stir in pecans that have been dusted with flour and pour batter into greased loaf pans.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes for large loaves or 60 to 65 minutes for small loaves.
Cool 10 minutes before removing from pans and continue cooling on wire racks.
Wrap in foil and keep in refrigerator or freeze.
Yield:
2 large loaves (9 x 5 x 3-inch) or 3 small loaves (8 x 4 x 2-inch).

title: squash casserole
directions: Slice squash into 3/8-inch thick slices.
In a large pan, cook squash and onion in salted boiling water for 5 to 10 minutes or until crisp-tender.
In a large bowl, mix soup, sour cream and carrots.
Fold in squash (drained).
Toss stuffing mix with melted butter and spread 1/2 on bottom of a 12 x 7 x 2-inch baking dish. Spoon squash mixture on top of this and sprinkle rest of stuffing mix on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: fried pie crust
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Add egg and flavoring to ice water, then mix all ingredients together and roll out.

title: nine bean soup
directions: Soak 2 cups washed bean mix overnight.
Drain; combine beans and next 5 ingredients.
Bring to boil.
Simmer 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until tender.
Add remaining ingredients; simmer 30 minutes.

title: heavenly delight salad
directions: Dissolve jello in cottage cheese.
Combine all other ingredients.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: layered spinach salad
directions: Layer vegetables in a colorful way, using a clear bowl.
Start with spinach, then sprinkle salt, pepper and sugar.
Add layers as you like.
Layer 1/2 cup of bacon bits somewhere between layers. End with shredded cheese.
Cover with Miracle Whip; spread to edges of salad.
Sprinkle the other bacon bits over top.
Cover with clear wrap tightly.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight.

title: apple kuchen
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cut butter into dry cake mix until crumbly.
Mix in coconut.
Pat mixture into greased 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake 10 minutes.
Mix pie filling and cinnamon.
Pour over crust.
Blend sour cream and egg.
Pour over apples.
Bake 25 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Delicious!

title: cold oven pound cake
directions: Cream sugar, Crisco and margarine together.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add flour and milk alternately, beginning and ending with flour.
Add flavorings. Place in a cold oven and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes. Use a 10-inch tube pan.

title: banana salad
directions: Mix bananas, pears and marshmallows and grapes.
Add enough mayonnaise to milk to thoroughly moisten.

title: ham rolls
directions: Mix cheese, onion, horseradish and Worcestershire sauce. Spread on ham slices.
Lay a stem of asparagus across ham and roll.
Chill.
Cut into 4 lengths.

title: crab quiche
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Prepare pastry for 9-inch one-crust pie as directed on package*.
Beat eggs until blended.
Stir in cream, onion, salt and cayenne red pepper.

title: spaghetti pizza(from a family friend, anna)
directions: Cook spaghetti in
salted
water
according
to package directions.
Drain and rinse
lightly
in
cool
water;
drain again.
In large bowl place
spaghetti
and
the
rest
of the ingredients except oil and
toss
gently.
Heat oil in 10-inch non-stick frying pan.
When oil
is hot, place mixture in pan. Shake pan occasionally so
pizza
does
not stick.
Lower heat and cover for 7 to 8 minutes.
Slide pizza onto flat plate and flip pan over top of pizza, so the other side will cook.
Cook an additional 10
minutes
until nicely firm and set.
Makes 4 servings.
This is also great as a side dish.

title: brown sugar surprises
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add flour to which baking powder and salt has been added.
Add vanilla and nuts; mix well.
Pour into a greased 8 x 2-inch pan and bake for about 30 minutes.
Cut into squares while warm.
You can sprinkle lightly with powdered sugar.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers and slice as thin as possible.
Chop onions and peppers.
Combine with cucumbers and salt.
Add cracked ice.
Let stand 3 to 4 hours; drain.
Combine vinegar, sugar and spices in a large preserving kettle.
Bring to a boil.
Add drained cucumbers; heat thoroughly, but do not boil.
Pack while hot into sterilized jars and seal.

title: oyster dressing
directions: Break bread into pieces.
Use essence from giblets to mix. Grind giblets, oysters and onion together.
Cut celery in small pieces.
Place on baking dish.
Moisten top with essence and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until browned.

title: walnut balls
directions: Cream butter in large bowl with mixer.
Add sugar and beat until light and fluffy.
Sift in flour.
Add vanilla and beat until smooth.
Stir in walnuts.
Form into balls the size of a quarter.
Place on greased baking sheet.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes. When done, roll in confectioners sugar.
Store in airtight container.
Yield: 60 to 65 pieces.

title: italian sausage soup
directions: In a 5 to 6 quart pan (non-stick if possible), combine onions, garlic and one cup broth.
Boil on high heat, stirring occasionally, until liquid evaporates and vegetables begin to brown, 10 to 15 minutes.
To deglaze, stir in 3 tablespoons water to release browned bits.
Cook, uncovered, until liquid evaporates and moisture begins to brown again, about 1 minute.
Repeat deglazing step 3 more times until mixture is richly browned. Lightly brown the sausage, pour off and discard the grease.
Add sausage and 1/2 cup more water to mixture.
Stir gently until liquid evaporates and meat begins to brown, 8 to 10 minutes.
Add remaining 4 cups broth.
Stir to loosen browned bits.
Then add wine, tomatoes (and their liquid), basil, sugar, bell pepper, zucchini and pasta.
Cover and bring to a boil over high heat. Simmer until pasta is just tender to bite, about 15 minutes. Serve hot, with parsley, salt and pepper to taste.
If made ahead, let cool, cover and chill until next day.
Reheat to simmering. Serves 6.

title: hamburger meat casserolegroves, texas
directions: Brown ground meat.
Layer meat, greenbeans, corn, meat, greenbeans, corn until gone.

title: beef burgundy
directions: Brown beef in butter; mix all ingredients except mushrooms in Dutch oven.
Bake, covered, at 325° for 2 hours.
Add mushrooms last 15 minutes.
Serve over noodles.

title: cocktail wieners(appetizer)
directions: Mix mustard and currant jelly over low heat.
Slice smoky links into bite-size pieces.
Add to mustard/jelly mixture and heat thoroughly.
If desired, transfer mixture to chafing dish (or for larger quantities, use crock-pot).

title: apple crisp
directions: Place apples in baking dish.
Mix all other ingredients together and pour
over
apples.
Bake
at
for 45 to 60 minutes, until
apples
are done and crust browned.
Serve for breakfast topped with CASHEW-RICE MILK.

title: cottage potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes, peel and cube.
Mix potatoes, green pepper, onion, pimentos, parsley, salt, pepper, bread and cheese in a greased casserole dish.
Cover with enough milk to moisten.
Melt butter and mix with cornflake crumbs and sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: eggplant parmesan
directions: Saute garlic and onion in oil until golden brown; stir in drained tomatoes, tomato sauce, salt, basil and oregano.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer for 10 minutes.
Break up tomatoes if still whole.

title: bac*o salad
directions: Layer ingredients as listed in 8 x 8-inch pan.

title: potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes well done.
Dice potatoes.
Add celery and onions.
Cook sugar, vinegar, eggs and mustard slowly until thick and creamy.
Mix with potatoes.

title: apple breakfast lasagna
