directions: Blend sour cream and brown sugar in small bowl; refrigerate. Place 6 French toast slices in the bottom of a greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Layer ham, 1 1/2 cups of cheese and the rest of the French toast.
Spread apple filling over top and sprinkle with granola and raisins.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese and bake another 5 minutes until cheese melts. Serve with sour cream mixture.

title: mixed vegetable pickles
directions: Clean and slice vegetables. Mix in desired amounts.
Pack in jars (may put hot peppers in bottom of jar if desired).
Dissolve vinegar, sugar and water.
Pour solution over vegetables, leaving 1/4-inch clear at top.
Seal.
Water bath 25 minutes.
Remove right away.

title: oreo ice cream cake
directions: Use a container with a top.
Crunch Oreo cookies in the bottom of container.
Spread enough melted butter to cover the cookies. Spread thawed ice cream over cookie crumbs.
Put hot fudge in microwave until melted, then cover the ice cream.
Crunch more Oreo cookies over the fudge and cover with Cool Whip.
Cover the ice cream cake with lid and put in freezer.
Leave in freezer 2 to 3 hours, then serve!

title: strawberry rhubarb coffee cake
directions: Combine fruits in saucepan and cook over medium heat for 5 minutes, stirring.
Add lemon juice, 1 1/2 cups sugar and cornstarch and cook, stirring for another 5 minutes.
Cool. Combine flour, 1 cup sugar, baking powder and salt in bowl.
Cut in 1 cup butter until mixture is crumbly.
Beat together the buttermilk, eggs and vanilla.
Add to flour mixture.
Spread 1/2 of batter in a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Spread fruit mixture over batter.
Spoon rest of batter in small mounds on top of fruit.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Prepare rice according to directions.
Brown hamburger meat with chopped onion; drain.
Add Ragu sauce and stir in rice.
Add Cheddar cheese.
Prepare green peppers by cutting off top and seeding.
Parboil in lightly salted water for 2 minutes.
Drain. Fill peppers with ground meat mixture; sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Put 1/2 teaspoon catsup on each stuffed pepper.
Bake for 30 minutes at 325°.

title: pork chops and rice
directions: * Chicken can be substituted for pork chops.

title: strawberry glaze pie
directions: Cook first four ingredients until thick.
Add Jell-O and cool. Pour over strawberries that have been placed in a baked pie shell.

title: black walnut pound cake
directions: Mix all together and bake.

title: squash souffle
directions: Mash and measure squash; melt butter in hot milk and pour over crumbs. Mix well and add to squash. Add seasoning; beat eggs together and add to mixture. Pour into baking dish. The top may be covered with extra buttered crumbs. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: rice casserole
directions: Put butter in baking dish and melt.
Mix 3 cans of soup over stove and add rice.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Do not use French onion soup.

title: zucchini soup
directions: Saute onion. Add zucchini, broth and seasoning. Bring to a boil. Add Cream of Wheat. Simmer 5 minutes. Puree entire soup and return to heat. Add 1/2 cup sour cream when ready to serve. Garnish with fresh dill. Enjoy!

title: amelia island crab
directions: Beat eggs.
Add milk and 1 1/2 cups bread crumbs.
Flake crab meat and add other ingredients.
Put in buttered baking dish, 8 x 8 x 2-inch.
Cover with remaining crumbs.
Drizzle with melted butter.
Bake at 350° until brown, 30 to 35 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: homemade waffles
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff; set aside.
Mix dry ingredients. Add milk and butter.
Beat until smooth.
Fold in egg whites. Pour 2/3 cup of batter per waffle.
Makes delicious pancakes, too!

title: banana nut snack cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat eggs, oil, sugar and vanilla together.
Add flour; stir until just mixed.
Pour into greased baking pan.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes, or until brown.

title: holiday relish
directions: Stir cranberries with sugar in shallow pan.
Cover tightly with foil and bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.
Toast walnuts on cookie sheet about 12 minutes; watch very closely.
Stir baked cranberries, marmalade, walnuts and lemon juice until well mixed. Chill.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add unbeaten egg and molasses; beat until smooth.
Add flour, spices and baking soda to the creamed mixture; mix well.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheets.
Lightly press each cookie with the bottom of a glass that has been dipped in sugar.
Bake at 375° for approximately 10 minutes.
Watch closely.

title: pineapple mold for 14 to 16
directions: Combine jellos with boiling water and let cool slightly.
Use a spray (like Pam or Wesson) to wet a 1 1/2-quart ring mold.

title: caramel corn
directions: Bring to boil; stir to hard ball (260° or about 5 minutes). Remove and stir in soda quickly.
Pour over popped corn.
Stir well.
Bake at 200° for one hour.
Stir 2 or 3 times while baking. Turn out of pan or will stick.

title: round steak casserole
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Cut meat into 1-inch pieces.
Put meat, carrots and thinly sliced potatoes (cut in quarters) into casserole dish.
Mix soups together; mix with meat and vegetables. Cover with lid or foil and bake 50 minutes or until meat and vegetables are tender.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: In bowl, combine soup, milk, dill and pepper.
Add potatoes and cheese; toss to coat.
Spoon into 3-quart oblong baking dish. Bake at 375° for 1 hour or until potatoes are fork-tender.
Makes 10 servings.
tags: Campbell's condensed cream of chicken soup

title: cheese fudge
directions: Melt the Velveeta cheese and butter together. Add the powdered sugar, cocoa and nuts to the melted cheese and butter. Butter a large pan and pour in using buttered hands to spread. Let cool. Cut into squares. Very rich!

title: frosty
directions: Combine all of the ingredients in a blender.
Blend on medium speed until creamy.
Stir if necessary.
If too thin, freeze the mixture in the blender or in cups until thicker.
Makes 2 drinks.

title: easy minestrone soup
directions: Saute onions, garlic and celery in oil in large kettle.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bring to boil, lower heat and simmer for 1 hour or more.

title: barbecued grilled shrimp
directions: Shell shrimp.
Put one shrimp in each slice of bacon; fasten with a toothpick.
Cover each with barbecue sauce.
Cook on grill until brown and shrimp are cooked.

title: cherry chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Blend in egg and vanilla.
Blend in dry ingredients.
Add cherries, coconut and chocolate chips.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen cookies.

title: biscuits
directions: Combine sugar, shortening and flour.
Add yeast and water together.
Add baking soda to buttermilk.
Add all liquids to flour mixture.
Bake at 425° until brown.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook for 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: no bake pineapple pie
directions: Stir together in a large bowl and pour into 2 baked pie shells.
Sprinkle with coconut or nuts, if desired.
Put in refrigerator and cool.

title: quick cake
directions: Cream sugar and oleo.
Add egg.
Sift dry ingredients and add alternately with milk.
Grease and flour square pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Saute ground beef, onion, cumin and green chiles in heavy skillet; drain.
Mix remaining ingredients together.
Spoon half batter in greased casserole.
Place beef mixture over batter; top with remaining batter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until brown.

title: pimento cheese
directions: Mix mayonnaise, pimento, sugar and vinegar.
Use hand mixer or use potato masher and mix the cheese until smooth.
Add mayonnaise mixture and juice of 1 jar of pimento and cream together to desired texture.
May be creamy or chunky.
Keep refrigerated.
Serves 12.

title: potatoes deluxe
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Mix ingredients together in a large bowl. Place in a greased 9 x 13 pan. Sprinkle with onion rings on top. Bake for 1 hour.

title: crab-lobster casserole
directions: Cut crab and lobster into pieces.
Combine seafood with next 6 ingredients, 1/2 teaspoon salt, and dash pepper.
Spoon into 1-quart casserole or 4 individual baking shells.
Combine 1 cup crumbs and melted butter; sprinkle around edge of casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° till heated through, 30 to 35 minutes for casserole and 20 to 25 minutes for shells.

title: chocolate glop
directions: Melt butter and baking chocolate and add dash of salt and vanilla.
Combine flour, sugar, baking powder and milk.
Add melted butter and chocolate mixture to flour and sugar mixture. Spread in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine cocoa, brown sugar and sugar and spread evenly over batter in pan.
Carefully pour 2 cups of boiling water over all.
Cook at 350° for 45 minutes. Serve with vanilla ice cream.

title: bette's recipe for an english tart
directions: Roll out the pastry and line an 8-inch sandwich tin.
Spread the jam over the bottom.
Melt butter.
Stir in egg, sugar, coconut and baking powder.

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl; mix well.
Pour into casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hungry man's potato
directions: Bake potatoes.
Fry sausage and melt cheese.
Split the potatoes; top with sausage and cheese.
This is an easy filling lunch.

title: mushroom rice
directions: In Pyrex dish, melt butter and then add all other ingredients. Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour.

title: homemade mayonnaise
directions: Beat egg with mixer.
Add next 4 ingredients, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Gradually add oil, beating constantly.

title: "edible" terrariums
directions: Cream together butter and cream cheese.
Add powdered sugar. Mix in pudding and milk until blended.
Add Cool Whip.
In blender, grind Oreo cookies (dirt).

Layer in plastic flowerpot (or clear plastic cups) or large bowl, starting with peanuts (rocks), M&M's chocolate candies (charcoal), then add pudding mixture. Repeat once more, ending with dirt on top.
Refrigerate.

title: tia maria fluffs
directions: Mix well in blender.
Strain into cocktail glasses.

title: vegetable lasagna
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Heat oil in large saucepan (medium-high).
Add eggplant, onion and garlic.
Cook, stirring 5 minutes.
Stir in tomatoes, salt, sugar and basil.
Bring to boil; reduce heat to low.
Cover and simmer until eggplant is tender, about 20 minutes.
Makes 4 3/4 cups.
Combine spinach, Ricotta, Mozzarella, egg and nutmeg in a large bowl.
Spoon 1/4 cup eggplant sauce in 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Layer with 3 lasagna noodles and 1/2 spinach mixture, 3 noodles and 1 3/4 cups sauce, remaining spinach mixture and noodles.
Top with remaining Parmesan cheese. Bake uncovered 30 to 40 minutes until hot.
Total fat 12 g. Contains 380 calories per serving (6 servings).

title: blueberry crunch
directions: Pour the pie filling into a 9 x 13-inch glass pan.
Stir in the lemon juice; mix well.
Mix the cake mix with melted butter.
(Use more or less butter to make mixture easy to handle like dough, but not sticky.)
Use hands, if necessary; make patties and lay on top of blueberry mixture.
Make mixture of pecans and walnuts, chopped (use as much as desired).
Cover top of cake mixture with nuts and push them gently into cake mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Sift together the flour and baking soda.
Blend vanilla, oil, white sugar and brown sugar.
Add 2 eggs.
Stir in flour mixture, oatmeal, walnuts and chocolate chips.
Drop onto greased cookie trays by the spoonful.
Bake for 8 minutes at 375°.

title: fried cheerios
directions: Melt Butter in a frying pan over low heat.
Add Cheerios, stirring constantly until warm and lightly browned.
One of the first things I learned to make as a child.
Better than popcorn.

title: spanish bean soup
directions: Brown sausage.
Place all ingredients in a large pot.
Bring to a boil then turn heat down and simmer 1-2 hours.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; add mushroom soup, Ro-Tel tomatoes and Ranch Style beans.
Pour crushed chips in bottom of casserole dish.
Pour meat mixture over chips.
Top with cheese. Bake in a 350° oven.

title: fried squash
directions: Cut squash into circular pieces.
Salt and pepper squash.
Dip in eggwash and flour, and place in hot vegetable oil.
Fry on both sides until golden and crunchy.

title: christmas breakfast
directions: Trim crust and cut into cubes, then put 1/2 of the cubes into the bottom of a greased casserole pan.
Add sausage, browned and drained.
Sprinkle top with 1/2 of the cheese.
Add the remainder of bread cubes and rest of cheese.
Whip eggs and rest of ingredients.
Pour over the layered bread.
Cover and store in refrigerator overnight.
The next morning, bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours, uncovered.
Serve in casserole dish with fruit and hot biscuits.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Preheat the broiler or grill. Combine all ingredients except the shrimp in a bowl. Add shrimp to coat. Broil or grill (approximately) 2 minutes per side.

title: oatmeal bars
directions: Cream butter and sugars; blend in eggs and vanilla. Stir in the rest. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes in 8 x 8 pan.

title: easy hot sauce
directions: Quarter the onion and place all ingredients in blender. Season to taste.

title: lemonade torte
directions: Combine first 2 ingredients together.
Fold in whipped topping.
Spoon into graham cracker crust.
Top with a few extra crumbs.

title: snack
directions: Mix ingredients and drizzle over crackers.
Stir and mix well. Let sit.
No baking.

title: slush
directions: Boil 7 cups water and 2 cups sugar for 10 minutes.
Let cool. Boil 2 cups water and tea bags for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool.
Mix together and add the frozen orange juice and lemon juice. Add either 2 cups of vodka or gin.
Mix well and put in freezer.
Use half mix to half 7-Up.

title: pecan kisses
directions: Mix beaten egg white, vanilla and brown sugar together.
Cover pecans one at a time and place on cookie sheet.
Bake 30 minutes at 250° or until light brown.

title: healthful chicken casserole
directions: Cook spinach according to package directions; drain.
Mix onion with spinach.
Arrange spinach in bottom of 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle with 1/4 teaspoon of garlic powder. Arrange mushrooms on spinach and drizzle with melted butter. Place chicken on mushrooms and sprinkle with remaining 1/4 teaspoon garlic powder.
Top with Mozzarella cheese.
Place in 350° oven and bake for 30 minutes.

title: baked vegetable and seafood won tons
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium bowl, combine soup mix, cheese, crab, garlic powder and pepper.
Place 1 tablespoon mixture on center of each won ton.
Brush edges with water.
Fold each corner into center and press to seal.

title: strawberry angel food cake
directions: Tear angel food cake into pieces and put in bottom of dish. Mix sugar, milk, Cool Whip and sour cream.
Pour over cake.
Cut up strawberries and put on top.
Cover with glaze.

title: brownie sheet cake
directions: Combine flour, sugar, cinnamon, baking soda and salt in a large mixing bowl.
In saucepan, over low heat, melt margarine, water and cocoa.
Pour this mixture into dry ingredients; blend well.
Add eggs, milk and vanilla.
Blend well.
Pour into a greased and floured sheet cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: spanish rice with beef(first place recipe)
directions: Cook ground beef, onion and green pepper in small Dutch oven until browned.
Drain meat; pat dry with a paper towel.
Wipe drippings from pan with a paper towel.
Return meat mixture to Dutch oven.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil. Cover, reduce heat and simmer for 30 minutes, or until rice is tender, stirring occasionally.
Serves 6.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix together.
Put in shallow dish (1 to 2 inches deep).
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done, light brown.

title: gardening salad
directions: Combine macaroni, beans, meat, celery and peas.
Combine mayonnaise and mustard.
Stir in sour cream.
Toss with salad mixture.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Chill.
Makes 6 servings.

title: leonard blush fruit slush
directions: In a large container, combine water and sugar, stirring until all is dissolved.
Add mashed bananas and juices.
Freeze mixture. Remove from freezer, about 30 minutes before serving.
Scoop into glasses and pour 7-Up or ginger ale over mixture.
Makes about 26 servings.

title: corn stacks
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients and spoon into greased muffin cups.
Set in pan of water and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until set.
Loosen edges and turn out onto serving platter.

title: transparent pie
directions: Make
your
favorite pastry recipe for a one-crust pie. Line pie
shell
and
crimp
the
edges.
Have
the butter or margarine at room temperature and work it into the sugar.
Add the
egg yolks and cream.
Then add the flavoring.
Pour into the unbaked pie crust and bake in a 375° oven for approximately 30 minutes or until the filling is firm and light brown.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350° while mixing the cookie batter.
Beat egg whites until foamy.
Add salt, cream of tartar and sugar. Continue beating until stiff.
Add almond and vanilla extracts. Fold in nuts and chocolate morsels.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Place in oven and turn off oven; leave overnight.
Yields approximately 4 dozen.

title: thousand dollar orange salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add 7-Up.
Refrigerate about 45 minutes or until slightly jelled.
Whip the cream until stiff. Fold whipped cream and remaining ingredients into jello mixture (2-quart dish).
Refrigerate until firm.

title: water crackers(wind river reservation)
directions: Make up with some powdered milk to form a dough and beat it up.
Roll thin and bake quickly.

title: all-purpose ground beef mix
directions: Brown beef; drain and stir in salt, celery, onions and green peppers.
Cover; simmer over low heat until veggies are crisp-tender, about 10 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Cool on rack. Pour into six 2-cup freezer containers with tight fitting lids. Cut through mixture with knife to remove air pockets.
Attach lids. Label containers with date and contents.
Store in freezer.
Use within 3 months.
Makes Sloppy Joes, Beef Stroganoff, Hearty Beef Chowder, Chili, Rice Creole and Company Casserole.

title: taco rice
directions: Brown meat and onion in skillet.
Add salsa and tomato sauce; bring to a boil.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer for 5 minutes. Serve with rice.

title: lint modeling
directions: Stir lint and water in a saucepan. Add flour and stir to prevent lumps.
Add oil of cloves.
Cook over low and stir until mixture forms peaks.
Pour out and cool on newspapers.
Shape over boxes, bottled, balloons or press into a mold or use like papier mache.

title: oriental rice medley
directions: Combine rice and broth in 3-quart micro-proof casserole. Cover with casserole lid and cook on High 10 minutes.
Stir in Oriental vegetables, mushrooms, onions, butter and soy sauce; cover and cook on High 4 to 5 minutes or until hot, stirring once. Yield:
4 servings.

title: nannie's pepper relish(cir. 1865)
directions: Run the peppers and onions through food chopper.
Cover the mixture with boiling water and let stand 5 minutes.
Drain well. Add salt and sugar and barely cover with good vinegar.
Cook 5 minutes.
Seal in fruit jars.

title: creamy cheesy chicken
directions: Place cooked chicken breasts in a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish. Place cheese on top of each.
Spread soup over chicken and cheese. Sprinkle dressing over chicken and drizzle melted margarine on top.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: cheese cake
directions: Make graham cracker pie crust in long dish and chill.
Whip cream and set aside.
Whip egg whites and set aside.
Cream cheese and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time and beat.
Add salt and vanilla.
Add cream and beaten egg whites.
Pour into crust and freeze, overnight is best.

title: apple yams
directions: Bake 6 yams.
Peel and slice.
Peel and slice apples.
Mix pecans, cinnamon, brown sugar and melted butter.
Alternate layers of apples and yams in 1 1/2-quart greased casserole.
Sprinkle each layer with pecan mixture.
End with decorative layer of apples.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Uncover and bake for 45 more minutes.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Heat first four ingredients on low heat until dissolved completely.
Cool, then add last 5 ingredients.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: north carolina yam casserole
directions: Boil potatoes until tender.
Peel potatoes; mash and add the sugar, beaten eggs, butter, milk, salt and vanilla.
Top with topping mixture.
Bake 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: sugar-free fruit cake
directions: Bring to a boil the dates, prunes, raisins, margarine and water.
(You may use 1 cup apple juice plus 1 cup water instead of the 2 cups water.)
Simmer 2 minutes; let cool.
In a separate bowl, mix the flour, soda, salt, cinnamon, beaten eggs, vanilla and nuts.
Add this to the cooled fruit mixture.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 12-inch pan or a tube pan.
Bake in a preheated 325° oven for 40 minutes.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit; measure 1 1/2 cups juice and 1 1/2 pounds marshmallows into large pan.
Heat and stir until melted.
Cool. Pour over fruit.
Whip 1 pint cream, no sugar, and pour over fruit mixture.
Freeze.
Serve frozen.

title: spiced tea mix
directions: Combine the sugar, beverage crystals, lemonade mix, tea mix and cloves in a large bowl and mix well. Store in an airtight container. To serve, place 2 heaping tablespoons of the mix in a cup or mug. Add 3/4 c boiling water and stir until mixed.

title: easy carrot cake
directions: Combine cake mix, salad dressing, eggs, water and cinnamon, mixing at medium speed on electric mixer until well-blended.
Stir in carrots and walnuts.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.

title: dumplings
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Roll thin and cut in small squares. Sprinkle with pepper. Drop in boiling chicken broth.
Cover and simmer for 20 minutes.

title: potatoes
directions: Quarter potatoes.
Empty package and 1/3 cup oil in plastic bag.
Add potatoes and shake.
Coat, then add salt and pepper, and put in pan.
Cook at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Melt oleo.
Mix with graham crackers.
Press in 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: jello salad
directions: Mix jello and water; cool.
Mix fruit with jello.
Layer jello and sour cream.
Serves 12.

title: swedish apple pie
directions: Fill 9 x 13-inch pan 2/3 full of peeled and sliced apples. Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
In small bowl, combine melted butter, 1 cup sugar, flour, egg, pinch of salt and nuts.
Pour mixture over apples.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: lt.  governor's chocolate chip cookies
directions: Sift flour, baking soda and salt together. In a separate bowl, cream shortening and sugars together. Add egg and vanilla. Blend thoroughly. Then add sifted ingredients. Fold in chocolate chips and nuts. Drop from teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Makes about 4 dozen.

title: sauteed squash
directions: Peel raw sweet potatoes and slice into rounds about 1/4-inch thick.
Fry in shortening 2 to 3 minutes on each side until they are done and golden brown.
Drain on paper towels and sprinkle with sugar.
One potato serves 2.

title: orange nuts
directions: Boil together orange juice, sugar and cream of tartar to soft ball stage (234°).
Add nuts and beat immediately.
Spread on waxed paper or foil and break apart as desired.
These are a lovely Christmas treat.

title: cheese soup
directions: Cook the celery, carrots, onion, cauliflower, broccoli and garlic in butter over medium heat for 6 minutes, stirring constantly.
Stir in flour.
Cook, stirring constantly, for 3 minutes.
Slowly add the broth, salt and pepper.
Simmer, covered, over very low heat for 20 minutes.
Add the milk, cheese and Worcestershire sauce.
Cook over low heat for 10 minutes.
Garnish with almonds.
Can be made ahead, refrigerate and reheated in a double boiler.
Serves 6.

title: stuffed chayote pears
directions: Halve the chayote pears horizontally.
Remove seed and place in a large Ziploc bag.
Cook on high 20 minutes.
Saute ham, onions and garlic with a tablespoon butter until vegetables are transparent.
Add celery and cook until tender.
Scoop out cooled chayote pear meat from outside shells.
Mash chayote pear meat and mix with shrimp and cheese.
Add to mixture in skillet.
Add bread crumbs.
Place in greased 8 x 12-inch casserole dish.
Cover with additional seasoned bread crumbs and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8. Can be used as a main dish or side dish.

title: easy chicken divan
directions: Steam broccoli until just tender.
Melt butter in large frypan. Saute chicken breasts until lightly browned.
In mixing bowl, mix cream of mushroom soup and mayonnaise.
In casserole dish, drain butter from frypan.
Layer broccoli spears.
Spread half of soup and mayonnaise mixture over spears.
Top with 1/2 cup shredded cheese.
Layer chicken then top with remaining soup and mayonnaise mixture.
Sprinkle remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, uncovered.
Serve with rice.

title: cornbread
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add milk, egg and butter (melted). Stir just to blend.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.

title: tangy cranberry sauce
directions: Roast is to be left at room temperature.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Season as desired; add oil to pan and some onions (optional).
Bake at 375° for 1 hour!
Turn off oven and do not open door.
Leave in oven all day if you like, but don't open oven door.
One hour before you sit down to eat, turn oven back on at 375° and bake for 1/2 hour.
After 1/2 hour, open door and add 1 full glass of white wine.
Close door and cook for 1/2 hour.
Let rest short time and slice to your perfection.

title: quick chocolate cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients in a large bowl with electric mixer on medium speed until blended.
Note: Batter will be very thick.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes, until edges are lightly browned. Makes 4 dozen.

title: scallops in garlic butter sauce
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Place scallops in a flat baking pan. Sprinkle with garlic and seasoning, lightly dusting with crumbs and dot with butter and paprika.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes, then add wine and stir in.
Bake for 2 more minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: squash casserole
directions: Boil squash in water and salt for 8 minutes; drain.
Cook beef and onion in oil and drain.
Add crumbs, salt and pepper. Stir in butter and flour.
Add milk; cook until bubbly.
Add cheese.
Stir until mixed.
Put squash in bottom of buttered casserole.
Top with meat mixture.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: ha' pennies
directions: Knead all together in smooth ball.
Divide in half. Shape into 1-inch roll. Wrap in wax paper and refrigerate or freeze.

title: brunch casserole #2
directions: Cut bread into 1-inch pieces (no crust).
Cover bottom of pan with bread.
Cook sausage and crumble over bread.
Grate cheese and place on top of sausage.
Beat eggs and milk and pour over cheese.
Beat soup with some of milk and pour on top.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Reheat at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: homemade rolls
directions: Mix egg, oil and sugar.
Add water and yeast.
Beat with mixer until yeast is dissolved.
Add flour.
Let rise.
Punch down twice.
Roll out and cook in greased skillet at 350°.

title: scalloped mushrooms
directions: Place 1/3 mushrooms in a buttered 1 1/2-quart baking dish. Cover with 1/3 of the bread crumbs; drizzle 1/3 of melted butter over top.
Repeat with 1/3 of the same ingredients; add salt and pepper and end with a layer of mushrooms.
Sprinkle salt and pepper and pour wine all over.
Cover and bake 25 minutes at 325°. Just before serving, mix remaining butter and crumbs; spoon over mushrooms.
Bake an additional 10 minutes, uncovered.

title: orange cottage cheese jello salad
directions: Drain oranges and pineapple.
Mix cottage cheese and Jell-O together.
Add in remaining ingredients.
Chill.

title: fruited cheese balls
directions: If dried apricots are used, chop and soak in 1 cup water for 2 hours; drain.
(I prefer to use canned apricots.)

title: blueberry cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg yolks.
Sift together flour and baking powder. Add alternately to batter with 1 cup milk. Fold in beaten egg whites. Fold in blueberries.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan at 375° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: easy beef burgundy
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large casserole.
Bake uncovered at 300° for 3 hours.
Serve over noodles or rice.

title: sausage cheese balls
directions: Grate cheese and let stand until room temperature.
Mix Bisquick, sausage and cheese until well blended.
Make into small balls and bake until lightly brown at 350°.

title: hurricane
directions: Fill a tall glass with ice.
Add rum and coffee liqueur.
Fill glass 2/3 with pineapple juice.
Fill almost to top with orange juice.
Top with grenadine.
Stir and serve.

title: barbecue chicken
directions: Put on and simmer 30 minutes.
Cut chicken into serving pieces and
brown	in
hot
fat.
Pour
sauce over chicken and bake, uncovered, for 1 hour at 325° to 350°.

title: english pea salad
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together.
Add Miracle Whip until you get the desired consistency.
Refrigerate for 1 hour.

title: hot peppers and hot sausage bake
directions: Put juice from sausage in a
9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer peppers and then hot sausage.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Top with hot pepper cheese and Mozzarella slices; let melt and serve with fresh Italian bread slices or wedges.

title: foiled potatoes
directions: Slice peeled potatoes into a large piece of foil or a baking dish with a lid.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Add bacon, cheese, onion slices and dabs of oleo over all.
Seal with double fold.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: salad dressing chocolate cake
directions: Sift together sugar, flour, soda, baking powder and cocoa. Add cold water, salad dressing and vanilla.
Bake in 350° oven in a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan for 20 to 30 minutes or until middle springs back.

title: whiskey slush
directions: Boil 7 cups water and sugar.
Boil 2 cups water and tea bags. Let cool.
Mix pineapple juice with sugar water and tea water in large container.
Add whiskey and freeze overnight.
Fill glasses with slush and add 7-Up over the top.

title: north carolina pound cake
directions: Cream margarine and Crisco together.
Add sugar gradually and cream thoroughly.
Add flour and milk alternately.
Add vanilla and flavoring.
Place in tube pan in cold oven.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Increase heat to 350° and bake for 30 minutes.

title: pina colada fruit dip
directions: Blend all ingredients.
Blend 30 seconds.
Refrigerate overnight.
Serve with cut up fruit.

title: cheese pennies
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Using a food processor, shred the cheese.
Remove the cheese and position the knife blade.
Add the shredded cheese, flour, butter and dry mustard.
Process until a ball forms in bowl.
Roll dough into 1-inch balls and place 2 inches apart on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Serve hot.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: apricot nectar
directions: Make syrup of sugar and water.
Boil.
Let set overnight.
Add all other ingredients.

title: brown rice casserole
directions: Melt butter in baking dish.
Add rice and beef bouillon soup, onion soup mix and mushrooms.
Mix together.
Cook on 350° for 1 hour.

title: oh henry bars
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add oats, Karo and vanilla.
Pat dough in lightly greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.
While baking, melt chocolate chips with crunchy peanut butter.
Spread on dough after cooling slightly.
Cut into bars.

title: greek salad
directions: Tear lettuce and chicory leaves into
bite size pieces. Place in large bowl.
Add tomatoes, cucumber, Feta cheese and scallions. Pour
oil	and
vinegar over salad.
Sprinkle with oregano.
Toss and serve immediately.

title: homemade spaghetti sauce
directions: Fry hamburger until brown.
In another pan, mix tomato sauce, stewed tomatoes, oregano, basil, parsley, sugar, salt, pepper, onion and garlic powder.
Let simmer 2 hours.
Mix hamburger into sauce when done.

title: carrot cookies
directions: Cream together sugar and oleo or shortening.
Add egg and vanilla.
Sift together flour, salt and baking powder.
Add carrots.
Drop by teaspoonful and bake at 350°.

title: creamy chocolate frosting
directions: Combine melted butter and cocoa, then add milk and vanilla. Stir in the sugar (sifting if lumpy) and salt in three parts; beat until smooth.
If frosting is too thick to spread easily, beat in 1/2 teaspoon milk at a time.

title: danny's lasagne
directions: Brown sausage slowly with garlic, salt and pepper.
Drain fat. Add basil, oregano and tomato paste along with enough water to make a medium-thick sauce.
Simmer for 15 minutes, stirring often.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Boil chicken and cut into chunks.
Mix Veg-All, cream of chicken soup and chicken.
Use about 1 cup of chicken broth.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Portia said to put the chocolate in the bowl.
Stir it up. Put the cinnamon in it.
Add Crisco and sugar.
Mix it together. (Krystal, Samantha, Josh and Megan said to leave the graham crackers out, but everyone else said to leave them in.)
Sammy said to crack the eggs first and then stir them.
Tiffany said to add the flour last.
(Rebecca said we should just ask her mom to do them for us.)
Put 17 balls of dough on the cookie sheet.
Put it in the oven.
Josh said to put the oven at 100°.
Krystal said she thought they still might burn.
Brian said to cook them for 3 minutes.
Shad said to get a towel and take them out.
Scotty said to pour a big glass of cold milk and Sunny said to eat them up!

title: garden vegetable burrito
directions: In a large skillet, add zucchini, mushrooms, broccoli, bell pepper and jalapeno or red Fresno peppers.
Saute over medium heat for about 5 minutes, until vegetables are tender.
Reduce heat; stir in corn and cumin.
Heat for 2 to 3 minutes more.
Remove from heat; quickly blend in cheese.
Place vegetable and cheese mixture into center of tortillas, forming a log shape.
Wrap tortillas around vegetable mixture; roll into burrito.
Serve with red tomato salsa.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Grease casserole.
Cover bottom of casserole with rice.
Place chicken on top of rice.
Pour over the can of soup and water. Sprinkle onion soup on top.
Cover tight and bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: salmon croquettes
directions: Brown onion in butter until clear.
Add enough flour to thicken.
Stir in all of the salmon juice and milk.
When this thickens, add mashed salmon and lemon juice.
Mix well.
Chill for 3 to 5 hours.
When thoroughly chilled, shape into croquettes. Dip in beaten egg and roll in crumbs.
Fry in hot oil until tender.
Serves 4.

title: sweet potato yeast rolls
directions: Scald milk.
Add sugar, salt, mace and margarine.
Stir to melt margarine.
Pour over potatoes; add lemon juice.
Beat until smooth.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add beaten egg and yeast; blend.
Add 2 cups flour.
Beat 3 minutes at medium speed of hand mixer.
Add rest of flour.
Stir in with spoon.
Turn out on floured board. Knead until smooth.
Put back in bowl; grease top.
Let rise until doubled.

title: vegetarian patties
directions: (Millet is cooked in 1 part millet to 4 parts water.)

title: peppered pork roast
directions: Coat roast all over with garlic pepper.
Put in shallow pan in preheated 350° oven for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Remove and let stand for 10 minutes.
Slice.

title: three bean salad
directions: Combine wax beans, green beans, pinto beans, onion and green pepper in large bowl; mix well.
Add dressing; mix well.
Marinate in refrigerator for 1 hour.
Yield:
12 servings.

title: my broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Melt butter.
Add rice and hot water.
Stir until mixed well. Add other ingredients. Mix and spread in pan and bake 1 hour at 350° until done.
Can double recipe.

title: holiday cream pie
directions: Blend eggnog and cornstarch in saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture thickens and boils.
Boil and stir for 1 minute.
Remove from heat, blend in butter. Immediately pour into baked pie shell.
Cover with plastic wrap and chill for at least 2 hours.
Serve with whipped cream and sprinkle with shaved chocolate.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Heat potatoes, drain and mash well.
Add other ingredients. Place in buttered casserole and cover with the topping.

title: bubble solution
directions: Mix solution well and allow it to sit for 1 hour before using it.
Cover and label any leftover solution; store in refrigerator.

title: rocky road cake
directions: In medium saucepan, sprinkle gelatine over 1 cup milk.
Let stand 1 minute.
Stir over low heat until completely dissolved, about 5 minutes.
Add chocolate and continue cooking, stirring constantly until chocolate is melted.
With wire whip or rotary beater, beat mixture until chocolate is blended.
Stir in remaining milk.
Pour into large bowl and chill, stirring occasionally, until mixture mounds slightly when dropped from spoon.
Fold in nuts, Cool Whip and cake.
Turn into a 9-inch spring-form pan or 8 cup bowl.
Makes about 12 servings.

title: mac's masher biscuits
directions: Mix together with spoon.
Roll into 1/4 to 1/2 inch thickness. Cut out biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: marinated chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients except chicken.
Marinate chicken overnight in mixture.
Grill or broil.
Amounts may be increased according to number of pieces of chicken.

title: chicken dressing
directions: Saute onions and celery in margarine until tender.
Combine soup, broth, corn bread, croutons and onions and celery.
Mix in eggs and pepper.
Bake at 350° until done, about 35 to 40 minutes.

title: mole
directions: Cook sauce to a gravy consistency, stirring constantly.
Add chicken to sauce and simmer for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve with beans or rice.

title: quick cookies
directions: Mix melted margarine, sugar, milk and cocoa together over medium heat.
When mixture comes to a rolling boil, boil for 2 minutes.
Take off heat and add vanilla, oats and peanut butter. Stir until peanut butter has melted.
Drop by tablespoons onto wax paper.
Let set for 30 minutes.

title: dudley dunker doughnuts
directions: *May substitute 2 3/4 tablespoons vinegar and milk to make 2 cups.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Bake pie shells and let cool. Mix sugar, cornstarch and water. Bring to a boil and cook until thickens. Take off heat and add Jell-O; stir well and let cool. After pie shell has cooled, put whole or cut up strawberries in the shell. When the filling is cooled, pour over strawberries in shell. Refrigerate until set. Top with Cool Whip. This recipe makes 2 pies. To make 1, use 1/2 of the ingredients.

title: pork adobo(or make it with chicken, fish, or beef)
directions: Clean and slice pork into individual pieces for serving. Combine all the ingredients and let stand for 10 minutes in the frying pan.
Add enough boiling water to cover the meat, cover the pan and simmer until the water is evaporated.
Fry the meat, adding more fat if necessary.
Turn the meat to brown on both sides evenly.
Serve hot.
Serves 6.

title: chili con queso
directions: Optional: If you like it hotter, add several tablespoons picante sauce to mixture. Serve warm with chips. A crock-pot is handy.

title: mom's chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream the butter and sugars until light and fluffy.
Add beaten egg and mix.
Sift flour with salt and soda.
Add flour in 2 parts to egg mixture and mix well.
Stir in chocolate chips, coconut and vanilla.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Yields 36 to 40 cookies.

title: chicken soup
directions: Boil fryer and debone.
Cook diced potatoes in chicken broth. Cook until tender and add vegetables, onion, stewed tomatoes, soup and cheese.
Cook until cheese and soup have melted and soup is hot throughout.

title: green tomato conserve
directions: Cut lemons in thin slices.
Simmer in the salt and water for 5 minutes.
Add tomatoes, cut in chunks, and sugar.
Cook over low heat, stirring frequently, until sugar dissolves.
Simmer 1 hour or until thickened.
Pour into sterilized jelly glasses and seal with a layer of paraffin.
Yields approximately 1 1/2 quarts.

title: apple pandowdy
directions: Set oven at 350°.
Put apples in buttered dish about 9-inches square.
Sprinkle with molasses or brown sugar, spices and salt. Bake until apples are tender.
Pour cake batter over apples. Continue baking until done, about 25 minutes.

title: k-cereal cookies
directions: Boil first 3 ingredients together 1 minute.
Add peanut butter and cereal.
Drop at once by teaspoon onto oiled paper.
Makes about 50 non-baked cookies.

title: fettucine alfredo
directions: Cook fettucine, drain and set aside. Melt butter; add parsley and garlic. Saute for a few minutes. Add cream and 1 beaten egg. Stir together. Add fettucine and grated cheese. Stir until well blended.

title: huge cookie recipe
directions: *Add just before baking, since they tend to lose their color.

title: basic cake recipe
directions: Cream sugar and butter; add milk and salt.
Sift baking powder into flour and add to mixture.
Fold stiffly beaten egg whites. Bake in 3 layers.
Never fails.
Use any frosting.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Spray a 10 x 13-inch casserole and place 6
slices bacon on bottom to cover.
Pour rice evenly over bacon.
Place chicken over rice and sprinkle with spices.
Mix soup and water and spread over chicken to cover.
Top with heavy foil and place in 350° oven. Bake 2 hours.

title: easy meal
directions: Prepare macaroni and cheese according to package directions. Brown ground beef and add to macaroni and cheese.
Stir in corn (drained).
Heat thoroughly, stirring constantly.

title: beef beer balls
directions: Mix beef, cloves, salt, pepper and Accent.
Form into small balls; brown well.
Mix catsup, Worcestershire sauce and beer in separate pan; simmer for 10 minutes.
Drain fat from meat balls. Add beer sauce.
Cover; simmer for 2 hours.
Serve with toothpicks.

title: drew's pork chops(yield: 4 servings)
directions: 1. Preheat oven to 350°.

title: steamed salmon loaf
directions: Beat egg whites until foamy and fold in.
Steam 1 1/4 hours in double boiler.
Make egg gravy to serve over it.

title: baked chicken breasts
directions: Arrange breast halves in a 9 x 12 x 1 1/2-inch baking pan. Place 1 slice Swiss cheese over each.
Mix chicken soup (undiluted) with wine.
Pour over chicken.
Roll out dressing between waxed paper.
Spread over chicken and sprinkle with melted margarine.
Bake at 350° for about 45 to 50 minutes.

title: hidden valley ranch buffalo wings
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Dip chicken in mixture of melted margarine, sauce and vinegar. Put in baking pan.
Sprinkle with 1 pack dry dressing mix.
Bake 30 minutes or until browned. Sprinkle with paprika. Mix other package of dressing and use as a dip.
Good with celery sticks also.

title: paradise pumpkin pie
directions: Mix first four ingredients.
Place in a 9-inch pie shell. Refrigerate until set.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over cheese mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: scandinavian cabbage salad
directions: Place oranges, apples, cabbage and grapes in bowl.
Fold whipped cream (or topping), sugar, lemon juice and salt into mayonnaise.
Stir into fruit mixture.
Chill.
Serves 6.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
Set aside to cool.
Whip until thick Dream Whip and milk.
Add cream cheese and continue to whip. Fold into Jell-O.
Add crushed pineapple and chopped pecans. Refrigerate until set.

title: mom's scalloped oysters
directions: Mix bread crumbs and melted butter.
Put a thin layer of mixture in bottom of flat casserole.
Cover layer with half the oysters (oysters may be cut in half or quarters).
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Mix the oyster liquor and cream, pouring half over oysters.
Cover with thin layer of bread crumbs.
Repeat steps 3, 4 and 5 (layer of oysters, layer of salt and pepper and layer of oyster liquor), topping with the remaining crumb mix. Bake 30 minutes in hot oven (450°).
Serve hot.

title: cream of potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes and carrots in boiling water until tender. Drain.
Cook bacon until crisp.
Drain and crumble.
Saute and celery in 2 tablespoons bacon fat.
Combine cooked vegetables, bacon, salt, pepper, milk and cream.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
(Do not boil.)
Garnish with shredded Cheddar cheese and parsley. Yields 2 quarts.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine potatoes, sugar, 1/2 cup melted butter, eggs, vanilla and milk.
Mix well.
Spread in buttered 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Combine 1/3 cup melted butter with brown sugar, flour and pecans. Sprinkle over potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: blender cheesecake
directions: Make a graham cracker crust in
a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour on the pie filling.
In blender, mix remaining ingredients until smooth.
Pour over pie filling, then sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake at 325°
for 45 to 50 minutes.
Chill.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: chess cake
directions: Beat egg
whites
and
set aside.
Cream butter, sugars and egg
yolks.
Sift
flour, baking powder and salt together. Add to the creamed mixture.
Add vanilla.	Fold in beaten egg whites.

title: * five-can casserole *
directions: Mix all together.
Bake in greased casserole at 350° for 1 hour.
May add nuts, onion, celery, etc.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix together the dry ingredients.
Stor in an airtight container.

title: baptist pot roast
directions: Quickly brown roast in a skillet.
Place roast in a large roaster pan with potatoes and carrots.
Cover meat with soup
mix. Season meat, potatoes and carrots with salt, pepper and a dash of Worcestershire sauce.
Cover with 1 1/2 cups of water.
Cover pan tightly and bake at 275° to 300° for 3 hours.
Roast should be cooked about 1/2 hour for each pound, but the dinner won't be ruined if the pastor's sermon gets a little long.
So forget about your dinner and concentrate on what he says.

title: peppy lasagna
directions: In skillet, cook the Italian sausage, onion, celery and carrot until meat is lightly browned. Drain off excess fat.
Stir in undrained tomatoes, tomato paste, salt, oregano and pepper. Simmer, uncovered, for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.

Cook lasagna noodles according to package directions. Drain well. Combine Ricotta, Parmesan, eggs, parsley and 1/4 teaspoon pepper. Place half of the noodles in greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Spread with half of the cheese filling.
Top with half of the Mozzarella and then half of the meat mix. Repeat layers.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Let stand 10 to 15 minutes.

title: mrs. field's chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Blend butter, eggs, sugar and brown sugar. Add baking powder, baking soda, vanilla and salt to mixture. Blend gently. Add flour one cup at a time and gently blend before adding the next cup. Add chocolate chips. Use spoon to form dough balls and place onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake for 7 minutes and allow to cool. Makes about 48 cookies.

title: mary ball's egg nog
directions: Beat egg whites until fluffy and stiff.

title: handi-wipes(money saver)
directions: You will also need one large mixing bowl and one pair of scissors.

title: cherry angel dessert
directions: Cream softened cheese and sugar; blend in thawed topping. Crumble cake into a 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Pour cheese mixture evenly over cake.
Top with cherry filling.
Cover and chill for 2 hours or overnight.
Serves 12.

title: alta's cheese ball
directions: Mix together and form in a ball.
Add a little milk, then roll in parsley, paprika and nuts.
Wrap in foil and store in refrigerator.

title: instant pudding dessert
directions: Mix cracker crumbs, oleo and vanilla.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: church windows
directions: Melt chocolate and
mix
with margarine.
Add marshmallows. Take 2 pieces of waxed paper and sprinkle with coconut, then drop this mixture on
the
paper.
Roll	into logs.
This will make 4 logs.
Refrigerate overnight, then slice.

title: coconut-pinto bean pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mash pinto beans.
Add sugar, syrup and unbeaten eggs.
Beat together with a wooden spoon until sugar is dissolved.
Stir in coconut.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake for 10 minutes at 400°, then turn down oven heat to 375° and bake another 20 minutes.
Let cool before serving.

title: confetti party mix
directions: Combine all ingredients. Store in tightly covered container at room temperature.

title: old fashioned lemon chess pie
directions: Mix ingredients together and put into unbaked pie crust and cook at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: salsa
directions: Chop all ingredients and mix in herbs in a large bowl.

Add water, stewed tomatoes, tomato paste, lime juice, vinegar and jalapeno juice (if any) until desired consistency is achieved. Taste and adjust seasonings (salt, pepper and Tabasco) to taste. Let sit 24 hours in plastic or glass container with lid.
Keep refrigerated.

title: lasagna
directions: Simmer tomato paste, sauce, salt and Italian seasoning in uncovered pan.
Cook onion, garlic and ground beef in another pan until brown.
Add tomato sauce mixture and simmer until thickened (about 1 to 1 1/2 hours).
Add 1 bay leaf 1/2 hour before done.

title: fruit crunch
directions: Place pie filling in bottom of loaf cake pan.
Sprinkle cake mix on top.
Place pats of margarine all over top, making sure to cover completely.
Bake until brown on top.

title: tuna burgers
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Blend the next 3 ingredients. Stir
into	tuna
mixture.	 Form 4
patties.
Fry	in lightly oiled skillet for 5 minutes, or
until browned.
Serve on buns with lettuce and tomato.

title: seasoned salt
directions: Mix all ingredients and store in covered container.

title: bread pudding spiced cream
directions: Beat the cream with an electric mixer on high speed in a large cold mixing bowl for about 2 minutes.
The colder the bowl, the better and faster the cream will thicken.
Add the sugar, cinnamon, and nutmeg and beat again until the mixture thickens and forms stiff peaks.
Makes 4 cups.

title: grandma's cranberry salad
directions: Grind the cranberries.
Add sugar and mix.
Heat pineapple juice with flour.
Will thicken as it cools.
Set aside until cool.
Mix cranberry-sugar mixture with grapes, mini marshmallows, nuts and pineapple chunks.
Add cooled juice-flour mixture.
Mix. Blend in whipped cream.
Chill until serving time.
Doubles well.

title: coconut dessert
directions: Mix together margarine, flour and pecans and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Cool.

title: stuffed cabbage rolls
directions: Pour boiling water over cabbage leaves.
Let stand for 5 minutes.
Drain.
Season meat; add onion, rice and eggs.
Roll a portion of filling into each leaf.
Fasten ends with toothpick. Place cabbage rolls in frypan.
Brown lightly on each side.
Place cabbage rolls into casserole dish.
Pour tomato sauce over them. Add 1 can of water.
Bake in oven at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Cook chicken on medium heat for 1 hour.
Take meat from bone; save or reserve to pour into chicken dumpling broth.
Stir flour, butter and milk together until consistency stiff as pie crust dough.
Lay onto slightly floured cutting board; roll with rolling pin until thin.
Cut dough with knife into desired size pieces. Cook in boiling broth.
Don't forget to put chicken in.

title: chicken with lime butter
directions: Sprinkle chicken on both sides with salt and pepper.
In large frying pan, place oil and heat to medium temperature.
Add chicken; saute about 4 minutes, or until light brown.
Turn chicken; cover and reduce heat to low.
Cook for 10 minutes, or until fork can be inserted in chicken with ease.
Remove chicken; drain off oil and discard.
In same frying pan, add lime juice and cook over low heat until juice begins to bubble.
Add butter, stirring until butter becomes opaque.
Stir in chives and dill weed.
Spoon over chicken.
If chicken needs to be kept warm until meal is served, put back in pan with lime butter until ready to serve.

title: bedtime bars
directions: Mix crumbs and powdered sugar.
Add butter and mix well.
Add peanut butter and walnuts; mix well.
Spread in greased jelly roll pan.
Melt 1/2 cup butter and chocolate together.
Spread over graham mixture.
Chill for 2 hours.

title: pork chop skillet dinner
directions: Brown pork chops in butter; remove and saute onions.
Add remaining ingredients to the onions.
Lay chops on top.
Cover and simmer for 20 minutes.

title: baked cornbread
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Pour into an 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan. Bake at 450° for 20 minutes.
Yield: 9 servings.

title: english muffin loaf
directions: Set aside 2 cups flour. Combine dry ingredients. Heat liquid to 125° to 130°. Add dry mixture. Beat well. Stir in reserved flour. Grease 2 loaf pans. Dust with cornmeal. Dust top of bread with cornmeal. Cover and let rise 30 minutes.

title: apple date bread
directions: Prepare apples, dates and nuts.
Cream together butter and sugar and beat until light and fluffy.
Add the well beaten egg and blend until smooth.
Stir in the fruit and nuts.
Sift together the dry ingredients and add alternately with the sour milk. (Make sour milk by adding 1/2 teaspoon vinegar to 1/2 cup milk.)
Place in a greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan and let stand 10 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until bread tests done.

title: quick biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients; turn out on well floured board.
Knead until right consistency to handle without being sticky.
Roll to 1/2-inch thick.
Cut with floured cutter and place on greased biscuit pan.
Bake at 400° until golden brown.
Yields 12 to 14 biscuits.

title: spice dip
directions: Mix sugar and spices in small bowl.
Gently stir into whipped topping.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Sprinkle additional cinnamon on top, if desired.

title: pina colada slush
directions: Mix well and freeze.
Scoop a couple of spoonfuls into a glass and add pop (7-Up, Squirt).
Mix well and enjoy.

title: classic peanut butter pie
directions: In small bowl, cut peanut butter into powdered sugar until crumbly.
Sprinkle into prepared crust (reserve small amount for topping).
In medium saucepan, combine Eagle Brand milk, egg yolks, water and pudding mix.
Over medium heat, cook until thickened.
Cool 15 minutes.
Beat in sour cream.
Spoon into shell.
Top with Cool Whip and sprinkle with reserved crumb mixture.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Combine sugar, butter, milk and cocoa.
Cook until mixture boils.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter, oats and vanilla. Drop onto wax paper or put in a sheet cake pan.

title: brown sugar oatmeal pancakes
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine egg, oil and buttermilk.
Combine flour, baking soda, salt and sugar; add to egg mixture.
Stir in oats.
Pour by 1/3 cupfuls onto lightly greased hot griddle.
Turn when bubbles form on top of pancakes and start to pop.
Yields about 10 pancakes.

title: isabel's pineapple salad
directions: Arrange pineapple slices on large glass dish or tray, using crisp lettuce leaves under each.
Cover with sauce, spooned on.

title: spaghetti(spaghetti is jeremy's favorite food.)
directions: Boil spaghetti in a large saucepan, drain and place in a serving dish.
In a skillet, melt butter.
Add onion and cook until tender.
Blend in flour, mixing well.
Add remaining ingredients except the cheese.
Cook thoroughly.
Just before serving, add cheese and cook only long enough to melt cheese. Pour over cooked spaghetti.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: ortega chicken tacos
directions: In a large skillet, over medium heat, cook chicken in hot oil for 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add scallions and pepper; cook 5 minutes more or until chicken is no longer pink and vegetables are tender.
Drain mixture; set aside.

title: lemon loaves
directions: Cream butter, sugar, egg yolks, one at a time.
Add lemon extract and soda water.
In a separate bowl, mix raisins and nuts thoroughly in flour.
Add this to butter mix.
Beat egg whites and fold into mixture.

title: best ever potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake about 1 hour in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish at 350°.

title: play dough
directions: Mix all ingredients.
When mixture is smooth, put on burner. Cook all ingredients until the play dough is formed.

title: dad's calico beans
directions: Fry bacon and crumble. Set aside. Saute onion and celery in bacon drippings. Brown ground beef and drain off excess fat.
Add all the beans.
Mix all in a large casserole and bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Serve with cornbread!

title: peanutty squares
directions: Measure honey, peanut butter and brown sugar.
Cook over medium heat until melted and well blended.
Add nuts and dry milk.
Add raisins, peanuts and Special K. Stir until well coated.
Press into buttered pan.

title: oreo cookie supreme
directions: Crush Oreos; reserve 1 cup.
Mix remainder with melted margarine.
Press into 13 x 9-inch pan; chill 1/2 hour.
Blend softened cream cheese with powdered sugar.
Fold in 8 ounces Cool Whip.
Spread over Oreo crust and chill 1/2 hour.
Prepare instant pudding.
Spread over cream cheese layer.
Chill.
Top with 8 ounces Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with crushed cookies remaining and chopped nuts (optional).

title: honey squash pie(modern)
directions: Sift flour and salt into bowl; add shortening.
Cut in with pastry blender until combined.
Cut in a small amount of water to hold together from bowl.
Roll on floured board; fit into 10-inch pie pan, letting pastry hang over 1/2 inch.
Fold under extra 1/2 inch; flute edges.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Cook green beans and drain. Saute the mushrooms in margarine. Blend in soup, milk and seasonings. Pour into a deep pan. Sprinkle cheese over beans. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Remove from oven and combine crumbs, bread or saltine crackers, with margarine. Sprinkle cheese over bread. Bake for 5 to 10 minutes. Feeds 100 people.

title: baked gouda or brie cheese
directions: Place cheese on pastry sheet.
Roll out sheet a little.
Top with chopped pecans and bring each edge (4) up to center and twist to close (makes a little flower or bow).
Bake at 400° for about 15 minutes.
Serve while hot.

title: green bean salad
directions: Drain beans.
Mix chopped green pepper and onion together. Mix vinegar, oil, pepper, salt and sugar.
Heat to boiling.
Pour over beans.
Let cool overnight.
Keeps several days in refrigerator.

title: pumpkin ice cream pie
directions: Line pie shell with ice cream.
Make layer 1/2-inch thick. Place in freezer.
Blend together the pumpkin, sugar, nutmeg, ginger, cinnamon and salt.
Whip cream until stiff; fold into pumpkin mixture.
Spoon over ice cream in pie shell.
Return to freezer for at least 2 hours.
Let stand at room temperature 5 minutes before cutting.

title: chinese dish
directions: Rinse green beans under hot water to separate.
Brown meat and onion; drain.
Add soy sauce, 2 tablespoons water, garlic and pepper.
Remove and keep warm.
Add beans to skillet and cook 2 to 3 minutes.
Stir in rice and push mixture up sides of skillet. Melt oleo in center.
Add eggs and fry until set.
Stir rice and meat mixture carefully into egg mixture.
Stir in sprouts and cook 1 to 2 minutes.

title: white corn casserole
directions: Cut corn off of cobs and scrap cobs clean.
Preheat oven to 350°.
In a medium bowl, use mixer to cream egg yolks.
Beat until smooth.
Add milk and mix until well combined.
Stir in corn, salt and pepper.
In a small bowl, beat egg white until stiff enough to form peaks.
Fold egg whites into corn mixture.
Pour into lightly greased 1 1/2 quart casserole dish.
Bake 45 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Cover and let stand until set.

title: angels on horseback
directions: Drain oysters and lay each oyster across half a slice of bacon.
Sprinkle with seasonings and chopped parsley.
Roll bacon around oyster and fasten with a toothpick.
Place oysters on a rack in a shallow baking pan and bake in hot 450° oven for about 10 minutes or until bacon is crisp.
Remove toothpicks to serve.

title: shrimp fettucine
directions: In large skillet, heat 1 tablespoon butter over medium high heat.
Add garlic and cook for 1 minute.
Add parsley, shrimp and vermouth and cook for 2 minutes, stirring constantly until shrimp turn pink.
Do not overcook.
Transfer shrimp mixture to small bowl.

In same skillet, heat 3 tablespoons butter until melted. Reduce heat to low and add cream, Parmesan and red pepper flakes. Cook for 3 minutes, stirring constantly until cheese melts and sauce is smooth.
Stir in salt and pepper.
To serve, place warm fettucine in serving dish.
Add shrimp mixture and toss gently to coat thoroughly.
Makes 4 servings.

title: nutty shake
directions: Mix in blender or mixing bowl until foamy.

title: congo bars
directions: Cream together the margarine and brown sugar.
Add eggs and beat well.
Sift plain flour, baking powder and salt.
Cream this with eggs, chocolate bits and chopped nuts.

title: fresh blueberry pie
directions: Place 2 cups blueberries in pie shell.
Cook remaining berries with sugar, cornstarch, salt and water over medium heat until thickened.
Remove from heat.
Add butter and cool.
Pour over berries in pie shell and chill.
Top with whipped cream.
It seems easier to heat the sugar, cornstarch and water before you put the berries in to cook.

title: no cook fudge
directions: Let cream cheese set at room temperature.
Add sugar to cream cheese and cream together.
Add melted chocolate, vanilla, salt and nuts (if desired).
Press fudge into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan and chill.

title: savory potato skins
directions: Cut potatoes in half lengthwise.
Scoop out the insides and serve as mashed potatoes, leaving 1/4-inch of potato to the shell. Halve shells lengthwise.
On baking sheet, brush skins with butter and sprinkle lightly with salt, garlic powder, bacon bits and paprika.
Broil until golden brown, about 5 minutes.
Makes 16 potato snacks.

title: flying fish chowder
directions: Boil the fish in the water until it flakes.
Place bacon in a skillet and cook until fat is rendered.
Saute the onion, pepper, celery, carrots and potatoes in the fat for 10 minutes.
Flake the fish into a large stockpot.
Add the water, vegetables, bacon and tomatoes.
Heat to boiling.
Add all other ingredients except rum, cayenne pepper and thyme.
Cover.
Lower the heat and simmer for 1 hour.
Add the rum, cayenne and thyme.
Simmer for an additional 30 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: con queso dip
directions: Pour Rotel tomatoes into medium saucepan: add cheese. Cook over low heat; serve with favorite chips.

title: chocolate crinkles
directions: Mix oil, chocolate and sugar.
Blend in one egg at a time until well mixed.
Add vanilla.
Measure flour, baking powder and salt; stir into oil mixture.
Chill several hours or overnight.

title: chili meat balls
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients and 1/4 can tomato soup. Shape into 1-inch balls.
Brown in 2 tablespoons shortening.
Mix remaining soup with chili powder and water.
Pour over meat. Cover and bake in 350° oven about 30 minutes.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix dry pudding and pineapple.
Add Cool Whip and pecans. Refrigerate.

title: easy beef stew
directions: Mix in large pan and bake 5 hours at 250° covered.
I add a little thickening made from cornstarch and water before serving.

title: squash casserole
directions: Fry squash in "Fryin Magic" coating.
Saute onion and bell pepper in 2 tablespoons butter.
Add tomato soup, diluted with 1/2 can water.
Alternate layers of fried squash and tomato soup mixture.
Bake for approximately 30 minutes at 350°.
Top off with grated Cheddar cheese; put in oven until cheese melts.
Makes approximately 8 servings.

title: louisiana peppers
directions: In a large skillet, saute bacon until crisp.
Break up into small pieces and drain!
Save drippings.
Add peppers and oregano to skillet.
Cook until tender.
Stir in bacon.
Season and sprinkle with parsley.
Serve.

title: country captain
directions: Fry chicken.
While frying, make sauce with remaining ingredients. Place chicken in roaster.
Cover with sauce and cook slowly at 350° for 1 hour.
When done, place chicken on platter and serve over rice.

title: golden brownies
directions: Combine all ingredients in bowl.
Beat at low speed for 2 minutes.
Spread into greased pan and bake 25 minutes.
Cool.

title: parish cake
directions: Grease and flour a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan; line the bottom with waxed paper.
Combine eggs and sugar; beat until light and lemon colored.
Sift the dry ingredients together.
Chop the chocolate pieces the size of lima beans.
Add the chocolate with the dates, nuts and cherries to the dry ingredients, then fold in egg mixture.
Pour into the pan and bake at 325° for about 1 1/2 hours.
It's not exactly like a sponge cake; it's more like a fruit cake.
Delicious!

title: refrigerator tray pie
directions: Roll thin chocolate wafers with a rolling pin to make crumbs. Cream the butter; add crumbs and sugar; blend thoroughly.
Cover crumbs with ice cream, packing down well.
Press remaining crumbs firmly on top.
Garnish with whipped cream.
Return to refrigerator to freeze.

title: raspberry squares
directions: Mix shortening, sugar, flour, salt and baking powder with fork and knife.
Add 2 eggs and vanilla to mix and spread jar of raspberry jam over 1/2 of batter.
Spread rest of batter on top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cut into squares when cool.

title: cream cheese pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, condensed milk and lemon juice together and pour into graham cracker crust.
Chill and serve.

title: golden ham croquettes
directions: In a saucepan, melt butter; stir in flour and curry powder. Gradually add milk.
Cook, stirring, until bubbly.
Cook and stir 2 minutes longer.
Remove from heat and stir in mustard and onion. Add ham.
Mix well.
Cover and chill
thoroughly.
With wet hands, shape into 10 balls.
Roll in bread crumbs.
Shape each into a cone.
Dip each into egg mixture.
Roll again in crumbs. Heat oil in a deep fat fryer at 365°.
Fry a few at a time for 2 to 2 1/2 minutes.

title: apple angel pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine pie filling, pecans, spices, salt and egg yolks.
Fold in egg whites.
Spread in crumb crust. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Top with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: corn bread salad
directions: Cook corn bread mix like package says.
Let it cool.
Crumble up.
Put in large bowl and mix all ingredients together.
Let set in the refrigerator several hours before serving.
Keep in covered dish in refrigerator until eaten.

title: zucchini jam
directions: Boil
zucchini 6 minutes and drain well. Add pineapple, lemon juice and sugar.
Boil all together 10 minutes, then add jello. Mix
well.	Ladle
into
jars.
Put
wax on top or put flats
and rings
on
and
they will seal.
Tastes a lot like apricot jam.

title: easy french bread(2 loaves)
directions: Dissolve yeast and 1/2 teaspoon sugar in warm water.
Combine sugar, oil, salt and 2 cups boiling water.
Cool to lukewarm and add yeast mixture.
Stir in flour.
Knead 10 minutes.
Place in greased bowl.
Let rise until doubled.
Punch down and let rest 15 minutes.
Divide dough in half.
On floured surface, roll each half to 12 x 15-inch rectangle.
Roll up, starting at 15-inch edge. Place loaves on greased cookie sheet.
Make 4 or 5 slashes diagonally across tops.
Let rise until double.
Mix and brush on 1 egg, beaten and 2 tablespoons milk.
Sprinkle on if desired poppy or sesame seed.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: In large mixer bowl, combine cream cheese and peanut butter, beat with electric mixer until combined.
Add powdered sugar and milk, beat until combined.
Fold in whipped topping.
Spoon into pie shell.
Cover and chill in freezer for 15 minutes.
If desired, drizzle each serving with chocolate syrup.

title: crisp nut cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together with flour.
Add remaining ingredients in order given.
Sift baking soda and baking powder into flour.
Form into small balls on cookie sheet.
Flatten with fork.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: easy rich dessert
directions: Spread pie filling in 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Sprinkle dry cake mix on top.
Dribble melted oleo over mix.
Put chopped nuts on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
When cool, cut into squares.
If desired, serve with whipped topping.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Saute mushrooms and garlic in butter.
Add the flour, salt and pepper.
Then add 2 cups of chicken broth.
Slowly add 1 cup warmed heavy cream.
Add gradually beaten yolks, pimentos and parsley flakes.
Add chicken and keep warm.
Boil thin spaghetti in remaining chicken broth.
When done, pour drained spaghetti into large casserole dish.
Pour chicken mixture over spaghetti. Sprinkle Parmesan cheese and Cheddar cheese on top. Bake in a 350° oven until hot, approximately 15 to 20 minutes.

title: low fat eclair desert
directions: Make pudding with skim milk according to package directions. Fold in cool whip. In 13x9 pan layer 8 whole graham crackers; top with one half the pudding mixture. Layer 8 more crackers and remaining pudding. Layer with last crackers on top. Thin frosting with a little milk and spread on top. Chill at least 4 hours. Serves 15.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Combine sugar, water and corn syrup in a 2-quart saucepan. Cook over medium heat, stirring until sugar is completely dissolved.
Continue to cook without stirring, until candy thermometer reaches 260° or until a little dropped into very cold water forms a hard ball.

title: peanut butter or chocolate fudge
directions: Stir constantly first 4 ingredients until boiling; boil (full rolling) for 7 minutes.
In a large mixing bowl, combine marshmallows and peanut butter.
Pour hot mixture over marshmallows and beat with mixer until well blended.
Pour into buttered cookie sheet.
Let cool and cut.

title: meat balls and sauce(diet)
directions: Mix and make small balls.
Brown in skillet.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix together; make into balls.
Bake at 350° until brown. (Lightly brown and freeze for later.)
Makes approximately 100.

title: oreo smoosh
directions: Mix Oreos with melted butter (save 1 ounce without butter). Spread Oreos in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Press firmly in pan.
Spread softened vanilla ice cream over Oreos.
Spread 2 jars hot fudge on top of ice cream, saving some hot fudge for garnish.
Spread Cool Whip over hot fudge.
To garnish, sprinkle 1 ounce Oreos and drizzle remaining hot fudge on top of Cool Whip.
Cut into squares to serve.

title: glazed pecans
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients; set aside.
Beat egg white and cold water.
Mix pecans into egg white mixture coating well.
Mix with cinnamon mixture.
Place on buttered cookie sheet.
Bake at 225° for 1 hour.
Let cool.
Store in covered tins for Christmas.

title: minute fudge icing
directions: Combine ingredients and boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat. Beat until creamy enough to spread.

title: english toast
directions: Plug in toaster to most convenient electric outlet.
Place bread slices into slots on top of toaster (one in each slot). Press down on handle in front of toaster.
If handle returns to the up position immediately, along with bread, press down on handle again, only harder.
Wait.
When bread, now toasted, pops up from the slots, remove them.
Use knife to apply other ingredients as desired.

title: chicken stock
directions: Place chicken in large stock pot with enough water to cover. Add wine; put on lid.
Bring to a boil.
Scrape off any scum that may form.
Lower the heat; add vegetables, salt and pepper. Simmer for 1 hour.
Remove chicken; let cool.
Remove any meat on bones; reserve for other uses.
Return bones and skin to stockpot. Simmer for 2 hours.
Strain the stock into containers.
This will keep for 3 to 4 weeks in refrigerator.
Can be frozen.
Makes about 1 gallon.

title: instant spiced tea(hot or cold)
directions: To Use: 2 teaspoons mix to 1 cup hot or cold water.

title: mocha cake
directions: Preheat oven
to
Grease
two
9-inch round cake pans; coat bottoms and sides of pans lightly with cocoa.
Into a large bowl, measure 2/3 cup cocoa and remaining ingredients except frosting.
With
mixer
at
low
speed, beat until just mixed. Increase
speed to high;
beat 4 minutes.
Pour batter into pans. Bake
minutes
or
until toothpick inserted in center of cake comes out clean.
Cool cake pans on wire racks for 10
minutes. Remove
from pans; cool completely.
Prepare Mocha Butter Frosting.
Place one layer, rounded side down, on cake plate; spread
with
about
of
frosting.
Top with second cake layer, rounded side up; frost side and top of cake with remaining frosting.
Makes 16 servings.

title: fastnachts (dutch raised)
directions: Scald milk; add shortening and salt.
Cool to lukewarm, then add 2 yeast cakes and stir.
Add flour gradually, beating well after each addition.
Cover with towel; put in warm place until full of bubbles.
Mix sugar and nutmeg.
Combine with beaten eggs. Stir into first mix (when ready) an additional 4 to 5 cups flour. Knead well.
Cover and let rise for about 1 hour in a warm moist place.
When light and high, with floured hands, pull and roll to 1-inch thick.
Cut with a round can and a thimble to make a doughnut shape.
Place on cookie sheets in warm place, covered, until all are cut.
Fry in hot fat at 365°.
Turn so both sides gently brown.
Sugar or frost, then enjoy.

title: chicken and rice(light)
directions: Saute onion and mushrooms in margarine.
Add two cups chicken broth from cooked chicken.
Bring to boil.
Add converted rice and cook, covered, for 15 minutes.
Chop the celery and green pepper. Add to rice along with 2 cups chicken, milk, salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer 20 minutes, covered.

title: pumpkin swirl
directions: Heat oven to 375 degrees.
Line a jelly roll pan with wax paper and grease.
Beat eggs and sugar until fluffy.
Add pumpkin. Add dry ingredients and stir in.
Pour into pan.
Spread evenly and sprinkle with nuts.
Bake 13 to 15 minutes.
Invert pan onto towel sprinkled with confectioners sugar.
Roll up in towel and cool completely.
Unroll and spread with filling.
Reroll and refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: apple bars
directions: Mix flour, sugar and salt in bowl.
Cut in shortening as for pie crust.
Put egg yolk in measuring cup and fill with milk to 2/3 cup mark.
Add to pie crust mixture an blend just until mixed. Divide dough in half and roll half on floured cloth to fit into jelly roll pan, 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until soft and drain.
Saute onions with butter until soft.
Mix flour and water; add to onions.
Stir until thickened.
Stir in Cheez Whiz.
Add broccoli and stir in beaten eggs.
Melt butter with bread crumbs and cover.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: tri-color pasta with herbed butter
directions: Place pasta, margarine, herbs, garlic, salt and pepper in large serving bowl; toss until margarine is melted.
Makes 4 servings.
Each serving provides:
1FA, 2B.

title: pork chops and rice casserole
directions: Brown chops on both sides in lightly greased skillet.
Season with salt and pepper.
Combine rice, onion, celery, soup and water.
Put mixture in casserole dish or skillet.
Place chops on top of rice; cover.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until chops are done.
Serves 4.

title: drop dumplings(need broth from whatever meat using)
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Cut in shortening.
Add milk; have the broth boiling and drop by spoonfuls into it.
Cover and cook about 10 minutes.
The liquid must be kept boiling.
Stir occasionally to keep from sticking. Serve while hot.

title: whole candied yams
directions: Select and wash potatoes.
Put in pot. Cover with water.
Cook until skin will slip. Drain off hot water. Cover with cold water and peel.
Put the sugar, water, butter, vanilla and salt on stove.
Cook until thick as syrup.
Drop in peeled potatoes. Cook until syrup is thick. Turn potatoes once while cooking.

title: sausage balls
directions: Knead uncooked sausage, Bisquick and cheese.
Roll into bite size balls.
Cook until brown, or about 20 or 30 minutes.

title: tei tasseys
directions: Mix oleo, cream cheese and flour; put into small muffin pans. Mix brown sugar, eggs, vanilla, salt and nuts.
Spoon into crust mixture and bake at 350° until brown.

title: frozen salad
directions: Cream the cheese and salad dressing.
Chop fine the pineapple, cherries, dates and nuts and add to creamed cheese.
Whip the cream and fold into first mixture.
Pour into mold and freeze.

title: mexican lasagne
directions: Brown ground beef; drain off grease. Add beans and taco seasoning. Mix well. Place 4 noodles in bottom of 9 x 13 pan (lightly grease bottom of pan). Spread 1/2 beef mixture over noodles. Sprinkle with 1/4 cup cheese. Cover with remaining noodles; pour water over all, then salsa over top. Cover with foil and bake for 1 1/2 hours at 350° or until done.

title: orange pineapple zucchini marmalade
directions: Boil everything, except jello and peel, together for 15 minutes to a rolling boil, stirring often.
Add jello and orange peel last.
Put into sterile jars and seal.
Makes 9 (1/2 pint) jars.
Can use other fruit, such as berries or peaches (match jello).

title: peanut pudding torte
directions: With pastry blender, blend flour and butter.
Add chopped nuts.
Pat into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Cool thoroughly.

title: party casserole(makes 8 servings)
directions: Boil noodles in salted water. Chop eggs and pepper. Pour mushroom soup and milk in saucepan and heat; add cut up cheese. Stir until cheese melts. Add chopped eggs, pepper and tuna. Last, add egg noodles and pour into casserole dish. Top with cracker crumbs and pour melted butter over top. Bake 35 minutes in 350° oven. If casserole tends to be dry, pour a little milk over the top.

title: suckers
directions: Boil until it forms a hard ball in a cup of cold water. Remove from heat.
Add your choice of flavoring and food coloring.

title: dried apricot pie
directions: Cook apricots with 1 1/2 cups water in saucepan until tender. Blend sugar, salt, cornstarch and 3 tablespoons apricot liquid in small bowl.
Stir into apricots.
Cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Cool.
Spoon into pie shell.
Chill until serving time.

title: stockton's shrimp or crawfish etouffee
directions: Saute onions in butter; add tomatoes, water, tomato sauce, sugar, salt, pepper and bouillon granules.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Mix cornstarch and water and add to skillet with crawfish or shrimp. Simmer 5 minutes; add crab meat.
(One can white chicken can be substituted for crab meat.)
Simmer 5 more minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: cocoa drops (cookies)(sugar-free)
directions: Mix shortening and brown sugar together.
Add eggs and beat well.
Combine milk and vanilla extract.
Sift dry ingredients together and add alternately with milk to the batter.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes approximately 120 cookies.

title: breakfast quiche
