directions: Place bread in the bottom of a 13x9 inch lightly greased baking dish.
Layer sausage, then cheese.
Set aside.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Pour over bread and sausage mixture. Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° uncovered for 45 minutes. Serve with salsa.

title: eggs warner
directions: Hard boil the eggs.
Separate yolks and whites.
Chop up whites and crumble yolks, separately, with a fork.
Mix egg whites, onions and mushrooms into the sauce.
Serve on toast.
Sprinkle crumbled egg yolk on top.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Serve while hot.
Serves 6.

title: grandma josiah's cheesecake
directions: Combine cracker crumbs, cinnamon, sugar and butter.
Press on bottom and sides of a spring-form pan.
Beat eggs.
Add and beat well together cream cheese, sugar and extracts.
Blend in and mix until creamy the sour cream.
Pour into cracker mixture lined pan. Bake 45 minutes at 375°.
Chill well before serving.
Top slices with strawberries for a delicious dessert.

title: monkey bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Lightly grease 12-cup fluted tube pan. Mix sugar and cinnamon in plastic bag. Separate dough into 30 biscuits. Cut into quarters. Shake in bag to coat. Arrange in pan. Mix brown and butter. Pour over each piece. Bake 28 to 32 minutes or until golden brown and no longer doughy in center. Cool in pan 10 minutes. Turn upside down onto serve plate. Pull apart to serve. Serve warm. Makes 12 servings.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Cook sugar, milk, cocoa and salt to a soft ball stage.
Add butter and vanilla.
Cook to 110°.
Beat until fudge loses its shine.
Pour onto greased cookie sheet.
Cut into squares.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add beaten eggs, flour and soda.
Add mashed bananas and nuts.
Bake at 350° for about 35 minutes.

title: tomato macaroni
directions: Simmer all together 10 to 15 minutes, sprinkle with parmesan cheese.

title: cheddar cheese spread
directions: Fix the night before.
Serve at room temperature.

title: sweet raw potato pudding
directions: Beat eggs, add sugar, oleo, vanilla, salt and grated potatoes. Spray baking dish with Pam.
Pour in ingredients.
Set baking dish in pan of hot water.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: carrot souffle
directions: In mixing bowl, blend flour and melted butter or margarine. Add remaining ingredients. Pour mixture into a casserole dish, sprayed lightly with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: pea salad
directions: Drain peas well, then mix all together and let refrigerate for 24 hours before serving.

title: chocolate pecan candy balls
directions: Mix together ingredients except chocolate and paraffin wax. When mixed, refrigerate 30 minutes; roll into small balls. Refrigerate 30 minutes again.
Melt the chocolate and paraffin wax in double boiler.
Dip each ball and drop on wax paper.
Keep on low heat as wax will catch on fire.
Ice pick or small fork good to handle balls.

title: chili galore
directions: Saute ground beef, onion and green pepper in a large kettle. Add kidney beans, tomatoes and other drained beans.
Add all other ingredients.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to simmer and cook for 1/2 hour.
Serve with sprinkled cheese on top.
Great with garlic toast.
Serves approximately 6 to 8 people.
Best cooked the night before.

title: pea and bean casserole
directions: Place first four ingredients in a casserole dish. Place in 350° oven for 20 minutes. Remove from oven and tuck in cheese chunks and top with cracker crumbs. Place back in oven and bake until the crumbs are brown.

title: pepper steak
directions: In electric skillet, melt margarine.
Dredge steak in flour; brown.
Sprinkle with bouillon.
Add wine.
Cook at 325° until meat is tender (about 1 hour).
Add more wine if it becomes too dry.
Add onion, green pepper and mushrooms; cook until vegetables are done.
Add tomatoes; heat through.
Serve with rice or noodles.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Combine sweet potatoes, brown sugar, cream, milk, eggs, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg and ginger in a large mixing bowl; Pour into pastry shell. Bake in preheated 350 degree oven for 50 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean. Garnish with whipped cream.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Mix well.
Cook in an unbake pie shell at 350° until done.

title: blackberry jam
directions: Cook until bubbles come up and burst.
Fill hot jars and seal.

title: coconut pie
directions: Cream the sugar and oleo.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add buttermilk and vanilla, beating well, then add coconut.
Pour into the pie shell.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: rotel tomatoes
directions: Mix together; bring to a boil and boil 10 minutes.
Fill jars; process in hot water bath for 10 minutes.
Makes 9 pints.

title: harvest delight
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients and add egg yolks and milk.
Fold in egg whites with cream of tartar.
Place in lightly greased casserole (oblong).
Cook at 350° for about 45 minutes.
Test with a toothpick or wire tester until firm.
Serve with dribbles of warm maple syrup or heavy cream after pudding has cooled.
Enjoy.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut dough into 32 pieces.
Dip in oleo and roll in mixture of pudding, nuts, sugar and cinnamon.
Place in lightly greased Bundt pan (or angel food pan).
Drizzle leftover oleo and mix over top. Let rise 1 hour (or overnight in refrigerator).
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: spring tuna fish salad
directions: Mix spinach, scallions and olives.
Sprinkle with salt.
Mix tuna and French dressing and let stand 10 to 15 minutes.
Just before serving, toss spinach and tuna mixtures.
Serve with additional French dressing and hard-cooked eggs.
Makes 3 to 4 servings.

title: pecan butter brittle
directions: Microwave sugar, syrup and butter 3 minutes on High. Stir in paraffin to melt.
Stir in nuts.
Mix well and microwave on High 7 to 12 minutes, checking nuts several times to make sure they don't burn. Add soda, quickly stir and pour onto greased surface.
Cool and break into pieces.
Store in airtight container.

title: bacon wraparounds
directions: Combine soy sauce and sugar.
Marinate chestnuts in mixture for 30 minutes.
Wrap bacon slice around each chestnuts, fasten with a wooden pick.
Place on a rack in a shallow baking pan or broiler.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes until bacon is crisp. Serve hot.
Makes 20 appetizers.

title: baked cheese cake
directions: Using processor or blender.
Beat cottage cheese until creamy. Mix in the melted oleo.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add the sugar and milk.
Beat well.
Add the remaining ingredients, beating until smooth. Pour into crust.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 300°.
Cool and serve with fruit or Cool Whip.
This is a low calorie recipe.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Cream together first 3 ingredients.
Add next 5 ingredients. Put rhubarb on top of batter mixture.

title: tall pound cake
directions: Bake at 250°.
Start off in cold oven and bake 2 hours or more.
As soon as you take it from oven, take it up on a plate.

title: betty d. wine cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix with electric mixer for 5 minutes at medium speed.
Pour into greased angel food pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool in pan for 5 minutes, (do not turn upside down as this is a sponge cake), before turning out on rack. Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: company beef
directions: Brown meat and onions; drain. Boil 5 ounces of macaroni; drain. Mix all together with everything except cheese. Sprinkle cheese on top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: homemade pancakes
directions: Spoon into skillet of hot oil.
Cook approximately 3 minutes on each side.

title: ants in sandbox
directions: On each cracker, spread peanut butter and then sprinkle with raisins.
Makes 4 servings.

title: strawberry jelly
directions: Combine strawberries and sugar; cook 15 to 20 minutes.
Add lemon juice; cook 10 minutes more.
Pour into containers and freeze.

title: green bean salad
directions: Place beans, tomatoes, cheese and basil in a large bowl. Pour dressing over beans.
Refrigerate at least one hour.

title: poulet chasseur(hunters chicken)
directions: Heat oil and butter in frying pan; brown the chicken. Sprinkle with flour; let it brown.
Add the wine, water, spices and tomato paste.
Cook for 45 minutes.
Prepare mushrooms; saute in oil and add to chicken.
Cook for 15 minutes more.

title: baked pork chops
directions: Brown chops in trimmed pork fat; drain excess fat.
Season chops with salt and pepper.
Top with onion.

title: pasta sauce
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Mix in flour slowly; stir in milk, bringing slowly to a boil.
On low heat, in a separate pan, whisk whipping cream and half and half together with cornstarch.
Blend two mixtures together.

title: chocolate icing
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Cook on medium heat and bring to a rolling boil that won't stir down. Boil 1 minute, remove from heat and add 1 tsp. vanilla. Cool and beat until thick enough to spread.

title: creamy fruit salad
directions: Heat syrup until hot.
Pour over gelatin.
Mix all other ingredients.
Pour gelatin over salad.
Mix well.
Pour into shallow bowl.
Chill and serve each square in lettuce cup.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Pour into 2 greased bread pans. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: fresh fruit salad
directions: Pour canned pineapple juice over fruit.
It will keep for days without coloring.

title: bread pudding
directions: Combine milk and hot water; pour over bread.
Set aside to cool until lukewarm.
Stir in eggs, butter, salt and vanilla flavoring.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Set in shallow pan of hot water.
Bake at 350° until blade of knife inserted near the center comes out clean, about 1 hour.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Bake at 300° to 350° in 2 layers for 35 minutes.

title: company casserole
directions: Brown meat
and
onion in skillet.
Mix in large mixing bowl other
ingredients
except tortillas.
Add meat mixture. Cut tortillas into 1/4 pieces.
Layer tortillas and mixture in 2 casseroles,
ending with meat mixture on top.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: classic lasagna
directions: In large heavy pan, lightly brown beef and onion in oil.

Add tomatoes (put through blender or cut with edge of spoon), paste, water, mushrooms, parsley, salt, sugar, garlic powder, pepper and oregano; simmer uncovered, stirring occasionally, about 30 minutes.
Meanwhile, cook lasagna noodles as directed; drain.
In 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan, spread about 1 cup sauce.
Then alternate layers of lasagna, sauce, Ricotta, Mozzarella and Parmesan cheese, ending with sauce, Mozzarella and Parmesan.

title: carrot cake "moussie"
directions: In bowl, sift dry ingredients together. In another bowl, beat eggs; add oil. Add oil mixture to dry ingredients; mix thoroughly. Stir in grated carrots and toasted pecans, mixing well. Pour mixture into two 9-inch round cake pans, greased. Bake in preheated 300° oven for 50 to 60 minutes or until center is firm. Remove; let stand 15 minutes. Remove from pans.

title: date souffle salad
directions: Cream cheese; beat in syrup, lemon juice and banana.
Stir in pineapple, dates and nuts.
Fold in whipped cream.
Put paper bake cups in muffin tin and fill with salad.
Freeze until firm.
Let stand for 15 to 20 minutes at room temperature before serving. Serve on lettuce with pineapple slices and garnish with cherry.

title: kool-aid play dough
directions: Mix dry ingredients and add water and oil.
Stir quickly over medium heat mixing well.
When cool, mix with hands.
Wrap in small balls in Ziploc baggies.
Smells great and lasts "forever."

title: meat loaf roll
directions: Rinse frozen broccoli to separate.
Drain.
Mix hamburger, eggs, bread crumbs, catsup, milk, 1/2 teaspoon salt, pepper and oregano.
Pat hamburger mixture into rectangle, 12 x 10-inches, on piece of aluminum foil, 18 x 15-inches.
Arrange broccoli on hamburger mixture to within 1/2-inch of edges.
Sprinkle with 1 teaspoon salt. Arrange sausage on broccoli. Roll up rectangle carefully, beginning at 10-inch side and using foil to lift. Press edges and ends of roll to seal.
Place on rack in shallow roasting pan. Cook, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 1 1/4 hours. Overlap cheese on top.
Cook just until cheese begins to melt (about 1 minute longer).
(Center of meat loaf roll may be slightly pink due to sausage.)
Garnish with celery leaves, if desired.

title: three flavored soup
directions: Pare the winter squash and scoop out balls with melon ball scooper.
Cut the chicken legs through the bone into bite size pieces. Blanch the chicken pieces in boiling water.
Remove, drain and discard the water.
Soak the dried scallops in water for 1 hour. Remove and drain.
Place the remaining ingredients (except pepper) in a casserole. Stew over medium heat for 40 minutes. Add the black pepper.
Transfer to a serving bowl and serve.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream white sugar and brown sugar.
Beat in 2 eggs, vanilla and water.
Add dry ingredients.
Mix all together; add chocolate chips and mix well.
Drop by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 10 minutes and check in a 325° oven.

title: chicken and pasta
directions: Cut chicken into bite-size pieces.
Place olive oil and garlic in saute pan.
Add chicken and mushrooms.
Saute until tender. Add wine and reduce in half.
Add chicken stock and salt and pepper to taste.
Add water to flour to make a roux and add to sauce.
Heat until sauce thickens.
Add parsley.
Pour sauce over pasta and serve.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Take chicken off bone and tear in bite size pieces.
Place in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Melt margarine and add soups and milk. Pour over chicken.
Mix stuffing with broth and spoon over top. Do not stir layers together.
Bake at 425° for 25 minutes or until brown.

title: microwave aunt bills
directions: In a 3 - 5 quart dish, combine sugar, soda, butter and buttermilk.
Cover with plastic wrap; punch small holes in the plastic.
Microwave on 70% for 15 minutes.
Stir and continue cooking for 13-15 minutes, until soft-ball stage.
Add vanilla and beat with mixer until soft peaks form.
Stir in nuts and pour into buttered 12 x 7 dish.
Cool and cut into small pieces.

title: banana split pie
directions: Melt 1 stick butter, combine with graham cracker crumbs; press into pan.
Combine eggs, sugar, butter and vanilla.
Beat until smooth and spread over crumbs.
Cover with sliced bananas and a layer of pineapple.
Cover with whipped topping.
Sprinkle with nuts; chill.

title: mother's i-45 cream cheese cake
directions: Combine melted butter, 1 egg and cake mix.
Spread mixture into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan (will be thick).
Combine cream cheese, eggs, brown sugar, powdered sugar, vanilla and salt.
Beat until smooth.
Spread cream cheese mixture over cake mixture and bake at 325° for approximately 45 minutes or until golden brown. (Sprinkle with powdered sugar, if desired.)
Yield:
48 (1-inch) squares.

title: the black labrador's shepherd's pie
directions: *You may substitute 6 cups instant mashed potatoes made relatively stiff and seasoned with butter, salt, black and white ground pepper and a bit of garlic powder.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Brown bread crumbs in butter.
Spread crumbs in 9-inch baking dish.
Drain asparagus and gently place on crumbs.
Slice eggs and place on asparagus.
Pour mushroom soup over eggs.
Sprinkle some reserved crumbs over top.
Place in a 350° oven and cook until brown, about 20 minutes.

title: chicken breasts
directions: Place chicken breasts in glass baking pan.
Mix soups together and pour over chicken.
Cover pan with foil.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: shrimp toast
directions: Mix ingredients in bowl until fairly smooth.
Add some sesame seed (optional).
Cut off the crust of bread and quarter.
Spread shrimp mixture evenly on each piece of bread.
Deep-fry at medium heat 1 minute on each side, spread side down first.

title: lo-cal pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta until almost done and add vegetables for last 5 minutes of cooking.
Rinse well and add a no fat or low-fat dressing.
Very tasty.

title: sweet 'n' sour baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients and place in baking dish.
Bake for 40 minutes in 375° oven.

title: apple waldorf salad
directions: Stir all ingredients together.
Serve with Almond Cream Fruit Dressing or juice of a lemon and honey to taste and/or pineapple juice.

title: chow chow pickles
directions: Use old hand grinder (or food processor) to grind cabbage, tomatoes and peppers together.
Mix sugar, vinegar and spices in saucepan; bring to a boil for 5 minutes.
Add cabbage mixture and bring to a boil again.
Cook about 3 to 5 minutes.
Pour into pint jars and seal.

title: simple and delicious chicken divan
directions: Cook, bone and cube chicken breasts.
Add soup, Miracle Whip, lemon juice and curry powder.
Place broccoli spears in baking dish.
Pour chicken mixture over broccoli.
Layer grated cheese, sliced margarine and bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: creamy corn raita
directions: Combine in a medium bowl, cooled corn, yogurt, sour cream and salt.
In a small saucepan, combine oil, cumin seed, mustard seed and chili pepper.
Cook 5 minutes over low heat (do not overheat). Stir both mixtures together.
Serve immediately or cover and chill up to 4 hours.
Serve on lettuce leaves.
Sprinkle with chopped peppers, if desired.
Serves 4.

title: big chocolate chip cookie
directions: Combine ingredients and stir until moistened.
Place on a lightly greased cookie sheet or pizza pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until brown.

title: pub zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until fluffy; add sugar and beat well.
Add oil and vanilla; then add zucchini.
Add dry ingredients and blend together thoroughly.
Add walnuts.
Pour into approximately 10 1/2 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 2 hours.

title: peach salad
directions: Heat pineapple and juice to boiling.
Remove from heat and add jello.
Stir and let cool.
Add buttermilk and Cool Whip.
Pour into 9 x 12-inch pan and let congeal.

title: mother's cabbage
directions: Mix water, sugar and vinegar in large kettle.
Cut up cabbage in small pieces and break apart.
Place in kettle with bacon. Simmer for 3 hours.
Can also be cooked in crock-pot on low for 5 to 6 hours.

title: pork and bean soup
directions: Boil first 3 ingredients in 3 cups water.
Brown hamburger and add potatoes, soup and pork and beans.
Heat thoroughly to boiling and serve.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter a 11 1/2 x 7 1/2 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish.
Cook 2 1/2 cups macaroni by package directions. Drain.
While macaroni cooks, make cream sauce.
Melt butter, add flour and seasonings.
Stir in milk gradually.
Stir in half of the cheese cubes to melt in sauce.
Put half of macaroni in prepared pan; add cubed cheese and rest of macaroni.
Pour sauce over all macaroni and mix in.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Cook green beans according to package until almost tender. Drain and set aside.
Melt 2 tablespoons butter.
Add flour and cook until smooth.
Remove from heat and add sour cream, sugar, salt and onion.
Mix thoroughly; return to stove and cook until thickened.
Combine sauce and beans.
Place in buttered casserole. Sprinkle Swiss cheese over top.
Combine cornflake crumbs with melted butter and sprinkle over cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 35 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: baked chicken
directions: Cut whole chicken breasts in half.
Dip chicken in sour cream to coat breasts.
Put corn flake crumbs in plastic bag.
Drop coated chicken into crumbs and shake to coat.
Spray cookie sheet with Pam.
Place chicken in pan and sprinkle generously with paprika.
Bake in a 350° oven until crumbs turn gold, about 30 to 45 minutes.
Use 1/2 chicken breast per person.

title: balsamic vinaigrette
directions: Place all ingredients except parsley in a blender.
Blend 2 minutes or until emulsified.
Stir in parsley.
Use immediately or refrigerate up to 3 days.
Makes 1 cup.
Use as a marinade or on salads.
Delicious!

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Shape into loaf and place in loaf pan sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
If desired, top with extra tomato sauce.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Combine flour, sugar
and baking powder into mixing bowl.
Mix dry ingredients with wire whip except cinnamon.
Add 1 cup milk and mix thoroughly.
Pour melted butter into square pan, 8 x 8 x 2 1/2-inch.
Pour batter into same pan.
Layer fruit covering batter.
Sprinkle cinnamon on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until golden brown.

title: hot sausage and peppers
directions: Put all ingredients in a casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: shrimp fried rice
directions: Fry shrimp in oil in a deep frying pan for 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Add eggs, mushrooms, salt and pepper.
Fry over medium heat for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add rice and soy sauce; fry for 5 minutes, stirring frequently.
Mix with chopped scallions.
Serves 6.

title: cabbage pillows
directions: Heat cabbage leaves in boiling water for a few minutes until they are soft enough to roll, but if you have a microwave oven, put 4 or 5 leaves at a time in it for about 1 1/2 minutes to soften. Mix together ground beef, rice, egg and onion.
Season to taste. Place a small amount of this rice mixture on a cabbage leaf, closing ends and sealing with a round toothpick.
Continue process until all of the rice mixture is used.
Place sauerkraut in bottom of small roaster; top with cabbage pillows.
Pour tomatoes over all.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Uncover and continue baking for another 30 minutes.
Use a little tomato juice as extra liquid if the sauerkraut is exceptionally dry.

title: brownies
directions: Melt margarine and chocolate in a double boiler over low heat. Remove from heat and add sugar, vanilla, flour and baking powder. Blend well.
Add eggs and nuts last.
Pour into a greased 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
In 9 x 13-inch pan, bake 5 to 8 minutes longer.

title: banana bread
directions: To sugar, shortening
and
egg	mixture add milk.
In a separate bowl combine soda, baking powder and flour; add nuts. Mix thoroughly and
add
alternately
to sugar and egg mixture with mashed bananas.
Bake
in 2 greased loaf pans at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: pineapple drop cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add vanilla, eggs, coconut, pineapple and raisins (optional).
Add dry ingredients to creamed mixture; mix well.
Drop onto cookie sheet; bake at 350° for about 10 minutes.

title: chicken salad
directions: Cook chicken breasts in simmering, salted water.
Cool and chop real fine.
Add eggs, celery and salad cubes.
Mix well.
Add celery salt and mix with mayonnaise until you get the consistency you desire.

title: pork hash
directions: Brown meat.
Do not cook through.
Add vegetables.
Add tomatoes (chopped) with liquid.
Add seasonings.
Put all in a casserole.
Layer meat, vegetables, then noodles and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: tapioca pudding
directions: Cook together the first 4 ingredients for 2 minutes.
Cool, then add whipped topping and oranges.
Very simple and delicious!

title: fudgsicles
directions: You will need Tupperware molds for this recipe.

title: chicken salad supreme(serves 6)
directions: Put cooked, diced chicken in large bowl, sprinkle with salt and mix well.
Add grapes, almonds, scallions and lemon rind. Drizzle with lemon juice and mix gently.
Cover and chill.
To serve, toss with mayonnaise.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Whip all together and spoon into cookie crusts.
Put in refrigerator 4 to 6 hours or overnight. Top off with lemon wedges and a spoonful of whipped cream on each slice.

title: hawaiian-style bacon wraps
directions: Combine cream cheese and small amount of milk until smooth and creamy. Stir in pineapple and ham to spread consistency. Spread thinly on bread slices. Cut each in half, roll up, and wrap with half slice of bacon. Secure with toothpicks. Place on cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bacon is done, turning every 10 minutes to prevent burning.

title: chicken pilau
directions: Cook chicken in water, salt and pepper until tender.
Remove chicken and skim broth.
Combine broth, rice, carrot, raisins, salt and pepper in large pan.
Bring to a boil, stir briefly, cover and cook without stirring on very low heat until rice is almost done.
Place chicken pieces on top and finish cooking.
Add onion, garlic and curry.
You're done!!

title: pina colada
directions: Mix well in blender.
Garnish with pineapple and cherry. Serves 4.

title: barbecued spareribs
directions: Layer spareribs in slow cooker.
Combine soup, vinegar, brown sugar, soy sauce, celery seed, salt, chili powder and pepper. Pour over spareribs.
Cover and cook 6 to 8 hours at medium setting.
Skim fat from juice before serving.
Makes 4 servings.

title: zesty ham ball
directions: Grind your ham into very small pieces.
(You may use leftover baked ham or sliced sandwich meat.)
Set aside.
In a separate bowl, mix mayonnaise and cream cheese.
Stir in ham with a fork. When mixed well, shape mixture into a ball with hands.
Roll ball in parsley flakes.
Chill at least one hour before serving.

title: peanut butter surprise
directions: You will also need baking cups.

title: pineapple delight
directions: Mix the graham cracker crumbs and margarine together for the bottom crust.
Press tightly into bottom of pan.
Whip the Dream Whip with cold milk, then add the powdered sugar and the softened cream cheese.
Add vanilla. Spread half of the mixture on the graham cracker crust.
Spread pie filling over the Dream Whip mixture.
Add remaining Dream Whip mixture over the pineapple.

title: easy chicken and dressing
directions: Boil chicken and debone.
Add cup of water to broth.
Slice onion in broth.
Put seasoning packet from Stove Top stuffing in broth; bring to boil.
Take out a cup of the broth and add corn bread packet to your corn bread slowly.
Add sage and your chicken. Put in crock-pot until ready to serve (low heat).

title: carrot cake
directions: Cream sugar and oil.
Add eggs and beat well.
Mix dry ingredients in sugar and oil, a little at a time.
Add carrots. Bake at 350° in a greased pan.

title: monkey fritters
directions: Mix the pancake mix, milk, egg, vanilla and oil in bowl.
Cut bananas into 1-inch slices.
Coat with batter.
Drop into fryer until brown; drain.
Roll in sugar and cinnamon mixture.

title: chinese fried rice
directions: Heat skillet or wok over high heat, then add 2 tablespoons oil and garlic.
Saute garlic until lightly browned, about 1 minute.
Add egg and scramble until yolk is set but egg is not dry or overcooked.
Add white onion, green onions, cabbage and white pepper to taste.
(If skillet becomes dry and vegetables start to stick, add 1 more tablespoon oil.)
Add bacon to skillet and cook 1 to 2 minutes.
Fold in rice, gently mixing with egg and vegetables.
Cook, stirring, over high heat until rice is heated through, 2 to 4 minutes.
Add soy sauce and oyster sauce, and stir to coat rice.
Keep stirring until vegetables soften and rice starts to brown, 3 to 5 minutes.
Serve hot.
This recipe yields 4 servings.

title: poor man's steak
directions: Mix everything but soup and shape in a narrow loaf pan.
Let set in refrigerator overnight.
Slice in pieces and fry until brown.
Put slices in layers in pan and spread mushroom soup on each piece.
Make brown gravy in pan you fry in and mix with mushroom soup and pour over meat.
Bake at 300°
for 1 hour.

title: pecan bread
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Stir in nuts.
Combine egg, milk and shortening.
Add to flour mixture and blend only until all flour is moistened.
Bake in greased loaf pan in moderate oven at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
Store several hours or overnight before slicing.

title: stuffed pork tenderloin
directions: Brown ground pork with onion; drain. Stir in 1/2 can of soup, bread, egg and nutmeg.
Cut tenderloin in a half slit, almost through lengthwise. Stuff sides together.
Fasten with strings or skewers.
Wrap bacon around the roast.
Cook, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes per pound.

title: teresa's chicken salad
directions: Simmer pineapple and corn starch, remove from heat and all all other ingredients.
Serve with crackers.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: With electric mixer, combine eggs, sugars, vanilla, milk and butter.
Mix until well blended.
Stir in oats, coconut and pecans.
Stir to mix well.
Pour into unbaked crust.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: broiled grapefruit
directions: Cut grapefruit in half.
Cut in segments and remove core. Garnish with sugar or brown sugar.
Place in broiler for 10 minutes.

title: orange pound cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together, add an egg, beat well, add two tablespoons flour and beat.
Continue adding eggs and flour until all the eggs are added, then add orange juice.
Bake in a tube cake pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: crab quiche
directions: Bake at 425° the deep dish pie crust for 5 minutes.
Prick bottom and sides of pastry.
Sprinkle crabmeat, cheese, green onions and 1 tablespoon parsley evenly into pastry shell.
Combine next 4 ingredients; stir well.
Pour over crabmeat mixture.
Bake in 325° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Cream the cream cheese.
Add Eagle Brand milk, frozen lemonade and food coloring.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spoon in 9-inch baked crust to chill.

title: chocolate chip walnut cheesecake
directions: Beat softened cream cheese; add eggs and sugar and beat 15 minutes until smooth.
Add vanilla; beat 5 more minutes.
Add chocolate chips and walnuts.
Bake at 350° in a spring-form cheese cake pan until done (about 50 minutes).
Make several days prior to serving.
Excellent walnut flavor.
Keep refrigerated.

title: pickle sandwiches
directions: Mix together and spread on wheat bread.
Roll dill spear up in slice of bread.
Slice roll into quarters.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown beef (break up with fork) and onions until done. Add rest of ingredients. Let come to a good boil. Reduce heat to low and simmer a while until ready to eat. Serve over corn Tostitos. Also good with corn bread. Top with grated cheese.

title: impossible coconut pie
directions: Mix for about 30 to 45 seconds in a blender.
Bake at 350° until done.
Makes its own crust.
Delicious!

title: baked beans
directions: Mix brown sugar and mustard in bowl.
Layer in oven-safe dish 1 can of beans, 1/2 sugar mixture, 1 can beans, 1/2 sugar mixture and bacon pieces.
Pour ketchup over bacon and beans, enough to lightly coat.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: never-fail pie crust
directions: Cut flour, salt, sugar and shortening into pea size.
Beat egg, vinegar and water.
Sprinkle over dry ingredients.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix zucchini and vanilla well.
Sift flour and all dry ingredients together.
Add other ingredients.
Grease loaf pans. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: fantastic chicken
directions: Mix together sauce ingredients.
Place chicken in baking pan. Spoon sauce over chicken.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Uncover.
Bake 1/2 hour longer.
Better than barbecue.

title: dip
directions: Mix and serve with party crackers.

title: veggie mix(even kids love)
directions: Dice potatoes; boil until tender.
Dice carrots; boil until tender.
Set aside.
Add 1/4 cup butter.
Steam broccoli and cauliflower for 15 minutes.
Combine all in casserole dish.
Mix corn soup and milk; pour over veggies and mix slightly.
Sprinkle bread crumbs and cheese over top.
Bake at 350° for approximately 20 minutes, or until hot and cheese is melted.

title: "mexican" spoon bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat eggs.
Add cream, oil and salt. Stir baking powder with meal.
Add egg mixture.
Add corn and both peppers.
Mix well.
Pour half into a greased ovenproof 2 1/2 to 3-quart casserole.
Sprinkle half of the shredded cheese over top. Add remaining mixture and sprinkle other half of cheese over all. Bake 30 to 35 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: four seasons celebration punch
directions: In large pitcher or punch bowl, combine concentrates and water (2 1/2 or 3 cups of water can be added, if desired).
Just before serving, add ginger ale and ice (33 ounces of ginger ale can be added, if desired).
Stir to blend.
Garnish as desired.

title: crazy chocolate cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together except water.
Add water and mix well.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hot pork and noodles
directions: In skillet, heat oil.
Cook pork, celery, pepper and onion until tender.
In a large bowl, combine pork mixture, noodles, soups, corn and milk, salt and pepper; mix well.
Place in 13 x 9-inch baking dish; sprinkle with crumbs and butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: louisiana shrimp bake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Saute celery, onion and green pepper in medium saucepan, about 15 minutes.
Blend in flour and salt; cook until bubbly.
Stir in tomatoes, shrimp and sherry.
Bring to boil; simmer, covered, for 10 minutes.
Stir in 1/2 cup of the cheese. Add eggs.
Pour into 2-quart casserole.
Top with rice and sprinkle with remaining 1 cup cheese.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes. Serves 6 to 8.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add vanilla and mix well.
Add chips. Roll in lengths of pinky (long and thin).
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Chop and saut onion and pepper.
Mix with first four ingredients.
Line 13 x 9-inch pan with tortillas.
Spread with half of chicken mixture.
Sprinkle with half of the cheese and repeat layers beginning with tortillas.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: easy gravy
directions: In a small bowl, combine cornstarch and water until smooth. Set aside.
Remove all but 2 tablespoons of fat dripping from roasting pan.
Stir in broth or bouillon.
Cook over medium heat, stirring to loosen the browned bits.
Remove from heat.
Stir the cornstarch mixture into pan.
Add seasonings.
Stirring constantly, bring to a boil over medium heat and boil 1 minute.

title: sugar-free fruit bars
directions: Combine fruit and water; cook until thick.
Remove from fire and set aside to cool.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well. Bake at 350°.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: mixed mushroom bisque(serves 6)
directions: Saute onion in butter until soft, about 5 minutes.
Over high heat, stir in mushrooms.
Stir in flour and cloves; cook 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Stir in chicken stock.
Bring mixture to a boil; reduce to a simmer.
Simmer until mushrooms are cooked and soup has thickened slightly, about 15 minutes.
Stir in milk and creme fraiche.
Season with salt, pepper, nutmeg and cayenne pepper.
Heat, stirring constantly, until soup just begins to simmer.
Remove from heat.
Stir in lemon juice by drops. Serve garnished with enoki mushrooms and chives, sliced thinly.

title: tylor davis' favorite macaroni and cheese
directions: Bring water to a boil with salt and oil in a 2 1/2-quart cooker.
Add macaroni and cook until well done, about 5 minutes. Drain.
Add milk and margarine.
Cook until margarine melts and milk starts to bubble.
Add cheese.
Stir occasionally.
Cook on low heat for about 15 minutes or until milk cooks down and becomes creamy.

title: sponge candy
directions: Combine sugar, corn syrup and vinegar and cook over medium heat, stirring until sugar melts.
Cook, without stirring, until mixture is very brittle when placed in cold water.
Remove from heat and add baking soda.
Pour into a well-greased pan.
When hard, break into pieces.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Drain well.
Add spaghetti sauce.
Line a 9 x 13-inch pan with flattened canned biscuits.
Pour meat mixture onto biscuits.
Top with shredded Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at temperature indicated on biscuit can until biscuit crust is brown and cheese bubbles.

title: guacamole
directions: and proceed as before.
Or you can make up your own combination, using ingredients of this type.
The Mexicans might not think so, but it will all come out guacamole.

title: reese's cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar, brown sugar and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Add eggs; beat well.
Combine flour and baking soda; add to creamed mixture.
Stir in peanut butter chips and chocolate chips and nuts, if desired.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool slightly before removing from cookie sheet.
Yields about 5 dozen.

title: sweet mustard dressing
directions: Stir together gently.
Refrigerate overnight.
Good on most meats, sandwiches or slaw.
